66 /************************************************************************/
67 /* File manager section */
68 /************************************************************************/
69 
70 /************************************************************************/
71 /* File header section */
72 /************************************************************************/
73 
74 /* FILE_HEADER -
75  * This structure keeps meta-data on files in the file header page. The rest of the file header page, based on the type
76  * of files, is used by other tables.
77  */
78 typedef struct file_header FILE_HEADER;
79 struct file_header
80 {
81  INT64 time_creation; /* Time of file creation. */
82 
83  VFID self; /* Self VFID */
84  FILE_TABLESPACE tablespace; /* The table space definition */
85  FILE_DESCRIPTORS descriptor; /* File descriptor. Depends on file type. */
86 
87  /* Page counts. */
88  int n_page_total; /* File total page count. */
89  int n_page_user; /* User page count. */
90  int n_page_ftab; /* Page count used for file tables. */
91  int n_page_free; /* Free page count. Pages that were reserved on disk and can be allocated by user (or
92  * table) in the future. */
93  int n_page_mark_delete; /* used by numerable files to track marked deleted pages */
94 
95  /* Sector counts. */
96  int n_sector_total; /* File total sector count. */
97  int n_sector_partial; /* Partially allocated sectors count. */
98  int n_sector_full; /* Fully allocated sectors count. */
99  int n_sector_empty; /* Completely empty sectors count. Empty sectors are also considered partially
100  * allocated (so this is less or equal to n_sector_partial. */
101 
102  FILE_TYPE type; /* File type. */
103 
104  INT32 file_flags; /* File flags. */
105 
106  VOLID volid_last_expand; /* Last volume used for expansion. */
107 
108  INT16 offset_to_partial_ftab; /* Offset to partial sectors table. */
109  INT16 offset_to_full_ftab; /* Offset to full sectors table. */
110  INT16 offset_to_user_page_ftab; /* Offset to user pages table. */
111 
112  VPID vpid_sticky_first; /* VPID of first page (if it is sticky). This page should never be deallocated. */
113 
114  /* Temporary files. */
115  /* Temporary files are handled differently than permanent files for simplicity. Temporary file pages are never
116  * deallocated, they are deallocated when the file is destroyed or reclaimed when file is reset (but kept in cache).
117  * Therefore, we can just keep a cursor that tracks the location of last allocated page. This cursor has two
118  * components: the last page of partially allocated sectors and the offset to last sector in this page.
119  * When the sector becomes full, the cursor is incremented. When all page becomes full, the cursor is moved to next
120  * page. */
121  VPID vpid_last_temp_alloc; /* VPID of partial table page last used to allocate a page. */
122  int offset_to_last_temp_alloc; /* Sector offset in partial table last used to allocate a page. */
123 
124  /* Numerable files */
125  /* Numerable files have an additional property compared to regular files. The order of user page allocation is
126  * tracked and the user can get nth page according to this order. To optimize allocations, we keep the VPID of last
127  * page of user page table. Newly allocated page is appended here. */
128  VPID vpid_last_user_page_ftab;
129 
130  /* cache last file_numerable_find_nth page and index of its entry. used as an optimization for external sort files.
131  * the extensible hash case is not interesting for this optimization (because they are usually small files and because
132  * the access pattern is less predictable.
133  * the usual pattern external sort files is find nth, find nth+1, find nth+2 and so on. so we can cache the page and
134  * index of its first entry from last search to predict where the next file_numerable_find_nth will land.
135  *
136  * how it works:
137  * cache last search location for file_numerable_find_nth by saving user page table page VPID and index of first entry
138  * in page. next search will probably land in the same page (and it will just need to get to the right offset).
139  * if a page is deallocated, the cached location is reset (this is just a safe-guard since external sort does not
140  * deallocate pages currently.
141  * if a page is allocated, since it is appended at the end, will not affect the cached search location. current thread
142  * is actually the only one accessing the file so it can change it safely without promoting to write latch. to avoid
143  * safe-guards, we won't set the page dirty (it is hot anyway and likely to remain in memory).
144  */
145  VPID vpid_find_nth_last;
146  int first_index_find_nth_last;
147 
148  /* reserved area for future extension */
149  INT32 reserved0;
150  INT32 reserved1;
151  INT32 reserved2;
152  INT32 reserved3;
153 };
154 
155 /* Disk size of file header. */
156 #define FILE_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE ((INT16) (DB_ALIGN (sizeof (FILE_HEADER), MAX_ALIGNMENT)))
157 
158 /* File flags. */
159 #define FILE_FLAG_NUMERABLE 0x1 /* Is file numerable */
160 #define FILE_FLAG_TEMPORARY 0x2 /* Is file temporary */
161 
162 #define FILE_IS_NUMERABLE(fh) (((fh)->file_flags & FILE_FLAG_NUMERABLE) != 0)
163 #define FILE_IS_TEMPORARY(fh) (((fh)->file_flags & FILE_FLAG_TEMPORARY) != 0)
164 
165 #define FILE_CACHE_LAST_FIND_NTH(fh) \
166  (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fh) && FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fh) && (fh)->type == FILE_TEMP)
167 
168 /* Numerable file types. Currently, we used this property for extensible hashes and sort files. */
169 #define FILE_TYPE_CAN_BE_NUMERABLE(ftype) ((ftype) == FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH \
170  || (ftype) == FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH_DIRECTORY \
171  || (ftype) == FILE_TEMP)
172 #define FILE_TYPE_IS_ALWAYS_TEMP(ftype) ((ftype) == FILE_TEMP \
173  || (ftype) == FILE_QUERY_AREA)
174 #define FILE_TYPE_IS_SOMETIMES_TEMP(ftype) ((ftype) == FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH \
175  || (ftype) == FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH_DIRECTORY)
176 #define FILE_TYPE_IS_NEVER_TEMP(ftype) (!FILE_TYPE_IS_ALWAYS_TEMP (ftype) && !FILE_TYPE_IS_SOMETIMES_TEMP (ftype))
177 
178 /* Convert VFID to file header page VPID. */
179 #define FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID(vfid, vpid) (vpid)->volid = (vfid)->volid; (vpid)->pageid = (vfid)->fileid
180 
181 /* Get pointer to partial table in file header page */
182 #define FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB(fh, parttab) \
183  assert ((fh)->offset_to_partial_ftab >= FILE_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE && (fh)->offset_to_partial_ftab < DB_PAGESIZE); \
184  (parttab) = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) (((char *) fh) + (fh)->offset_to_partial_ftab)
185 /* Get pointer to full table in file header page */
186 #define FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB(fh, fulltab) \
187  assert (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fh)); \
188  assert ((fh)->offset_to_full_ftab>= FILE_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE && (fh)->offset_to_full_ftab < DB_PAGESIZE); \
189  (fulltab) = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) (((char *) fh) + (fh)->offset_to_full_ftab)
190 /* Get pointer to user page table in file header page */
191 #define FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB(fh, pagetab) \
192  assert (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fh)); \
193  assert ((fh)->offset_to_user_page_ftab >= FILE_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE && (fh)->offset_to_user_page_ftab < DB_PAGESIZE); \
194  (pagetab) = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) (((char *) fh) + (fh)->offset_to_user_page_ftab)
195 
196 /************************************************************************/
197 /* File extensible data section */
198 /************************************************************************/
199 
200 /* File extensible data is a generic format to keep theoretically unlimited data in multiple disk pages. Each page is
201  * a component of full data. Each component has a header which keeps a link to next page and useful information about
202  * this component. The header is followed by data.
203  *
204  * The data is considered a set of items. Items have constant size.
205  *
206  * File extensible data is designed to easily access and manipulate data items. It can be used for multiple purposes
207  * (e.g. file tables, file tracker).
208  *
209  * Items in extensible data can be ordered. The user must provide the right compare function. */
210 
211 /* FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA -
212  * This structure is actually the beginning of a extensible data component. It is usually accessed as a pointer in page.
213  */
214 typedef struct file_extensible_data FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA;
215 struct file_extensible_data
216 {
217  VPID vpid_next;
218  INT16 max_size;
219  INT16 size_of_item;
220  INT16 n_items;
221 };
222 /* Disk size for extensible data header */
223 #define FILE_EXTDATA_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE (DB_ALIGN (sizeof (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA), MAX_ALIGNMENT))
224 
225 /* FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA_SEARCH_CONTEXT -
226  * Helper used for searching an item in extensible data. */
227 typedef struct file_extensible_data_search_context FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA_SEARCH_CONTEXT;
228 struct file_extensible_data_search_context
229 {
230  const void *item_to_find; /* Pointer to item to find. */
231  int (*compare_func) (const void *, const void *); /* Compare function used to find the item. */
232  bool found; /* Set to true when item is found. */
233  int position; /* Saves the position of found item in its component */
234 };
235 
236 /* Functions for file_extdata_apply_funcs */
237 typedef int (*FILE_EXTDATA_FUNC) (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p,
238  const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, bool * stop, void *args);
239 typedef int (*FILE_EXTDATA_ITEM_FUNC) (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const void *data, int index, bool * stop, void *args);
240 
241 /************************************************************************/
242 /* Partially allocated sectors section */
243 /************************************************************************/
244 
245 /* Partial sector table (full name would be partially allocated sector table, but we will refer to them just by partial
246  * sectors) stores reserved sectors and bitmaps for allocated pages in these sectors. Usually, when all sector pages are
247  * allocated, the sector is removed from partial sector table. This rule does not apply to temporary files, which for
248  * simplicity, only use this partial sector table without moving its content to full table sector.
249  *
250  * Each bit in bitmap represents a page, and a page is considered allocated if its bit is set or free if the bit is not
251  * set.
252  */
253 
254 /* FILE_ALLOC_BITMAP -
255  * Type used to store allocation bitmap for sectors. */
256 typedef UINT64 FILE_ALLOC_BITMAP;
257 #define FILE_FULL_PAGE_BITMAP 0xFFFFFFFFFFFFFFFF /* Full allocation bitmap */
258 #define FILE_EMPTY_PAGE_BITMAP 0x0000000000000000 /* Empty allocation bitmap */
259 
260 #define FILE_ALLOC_BITMAP_NBITS ((int) (sizeof (FILE_ALLOC_BITMAP) * CHAR_BIT))
261 
262 /* FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR -
263  * Structure used by partially allocated sectors table. Store sector VSID and its allocation bitmap. */
264 typedef struct file_partial_sector FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR;
265 struct file_partial_sector
266 {
267  VSID vsid; /* Important - VSID must be first member of FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR. Sometimes, the
268  * FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR pointers in file table are reinterpreted as VSID. */
269  FILE_ALLOC_BITMAP page_bitmap;
270 };
271 #define FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR_INITIALIZER { VSID_INITIALIZER, 0 }
272

277 /* Table space default macro's */
278 #define FILE_TABLESPACE_DEFAULT_RATIO_EXPAND ((float) 0.01) /* 1% of current size */
279 #define FILE_TABLESPACE_DEFAULT_MIN_EXPAND (DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES * DB_PAGESIZE); /* one sector */
280 #define FILE_TABLESPACE_DEFAULT_MAX_EXPAND (DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES * DB_PAGESIZE * 1024); /* 1k sectors */
281 
282 #define FILE_TABLESPACE_FOR_PERM_NPAGES(tabspace, npages) \
283  ((FILE_TABLESPACE *) (tabspace))->initial_size = (INT64) MAX (1, npages) * DB_PAGESIZE; \
284  ((FILE_TABLESPACE *) (tabspace))->expand_ratio = FILE_TABLESPACE_DEFAULT_RATIO_EXPAND; \
285  ((FILE_TABLESPACE *) (tabspace))->expand_min_size = FILE_TABLESPACE_DEFAULT_MIN_EXPAND; \
286  ((FILE_TABLESPACE *) (tabspace))->expand_max_size = FILE_TABLESPACE_DEFAULT_MAX_EXPAND
287 
288 #define FILE_TABLESPACE_FOR_TEMP_NPAGES(tabspace, npages) \
289  ((FILE_TABLESPACE *) (tabspace))->initial_size = (INT64) MAX (1, npages) * DB_PAGESIZE; \
290  ((FILE_TABLESPACE *) (tabspace))->expand_ratio = 0; \
291  ((FILE_TABLESPACE *) (tabspace))->expand_min_size = 0; \
292  ((FILE_TABLESPACE *) (tabspace))->expand_max_size = 0
293 
294 /* FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR -

297 struct file_vsid_collector
298 {
299  VSID *vsids;
300  int n_vsids;
301 };

314 #define FILE_TABLESPACE_MSG \
315  "\ttablespace = { init_size = %lld, expand_ratio = %f, expand_min_size = %d, expand_max_size = %d } \n"
316 #define FILE_TABLESPACE_AS_ARGS(tabspace) \
317  (long long int) (tabspace)->initial_size, (tabspace)->expand_ratio, (tabspace)->expand_min_size, \
318  (tabspace)->expand_max_size

320 #define FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG \
321  "\tfile header: \n" \
322  "\t\tvfid = %d|%d \n" \
323  "\t\t%s \n" \
324  "\t\t%s \n" \
325  "\t\tpage: total = %d, user = %d, table = %d, free = %d \n" \
326  "\t\tsector: total = %d, partial = %d, full = %d, empty = %d \n"
327 #define FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS(fhead) \
328  VFID_AS_ARGS (&(fhead)->self), \
329  FILE_PERM_TEMP_STRING (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead)), \
330  FILE_NUMERABLE_REGULAR_STRING (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead)), \
331  (fhead)->n_page_total, (fhead)->n_page_user, (fhead)->n_page_ftab, (fhead)->n_page_free, \
332  (fhead)->n_sector_total, (fhead)->n_sector_partial, (fhead)->n_sector_full, (fhead)->n_sector_empty
333 
334 #define FILE_HEAD_FULL_MSG \
335  FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG \
336  "\t\ttime_creation = %lld, type = %s \n" \
337  "\t" FILE_TABLESPACE_MSG \
338  "\t\ttable offsets: partial = %d, full = %d, user page = %d \n" \
339  "\t\tvpid_sticky_first = %d|%d \n" \
340  "\t\tvpid_last_temp_alloc = %d|%d, offset_to_last_temp_alloc=%d \n" \
341  "\t\tvpid_last_user_page_ftab = %d|%d \n" \
342  "\t\tvpid_find_nth_last = %d|%d, first_index_find_nth_last = %d \n"
343 #define FILE_HEAD_FULL_AS_ARGS(fhead) \
344  FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead), \
345  (long long int) fhead->time_creation, file_type_to_string ((fhead)->type), \
346  FILE_TABLESPACE_AS_ARGS (&(fhead)->tablespace), \
347  (fhead)->offset_to_partial_ftab, (fhead)->offset_to_full_ftab, (fhead)->offset_to_user_page_ftab, \
348  VPID_AS_ARGS (&(fhead)->vpid_sticky_first), \
349  VPID_AS_ARGS (&(fhead)->vpid_last_temp_alloc), (fhead)->offset_to_last_temp_alloc, \
350  VPID_AS_ARGS (&(fhead)->vpid_last_user_page_ftab), \
351  VPID_AS_ARGS (&(fhead)->vpid_find_nth_last), (fhead)->first_index_find_nth_last
352 
353 #define FILE_EXTDATA_MSG(name) \
354  "\t" name ": { vpid_next = %d|%d, max_size = %d, item_size = %d, n_items = %d } \n"
355 #define FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS(extdata) \
356  VPID_AS_ARGS (&(extdata)->vpid_next), (extdata)->max_size, (extdata)->size_of_item, (extdata)->n_items
357 
358 #define FILE_PARTSECT_MSG(name) \

361 
362 #define FILE_ALLOC_TYPE_STRING(alloc_type) \
363  ((alloc_type) == FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE ? "alloc user page" : "alloc table page")

368  "\t\tfree entries: max = %d, count = %d \n"

384 /* FILE_ALLOC_TYPE -
385  * The internal workings of file manager may need disk pages to hold the header and data tables. these are considered
386  * file table pages and must also be tracked besides user pages (pages allocated using file_alloc) */

390  FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE,
391  FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE_FULL_SECTOR /* used to allocate a table page necessary for full sectors */
392 } FILE_ALLOC_TYPE;

427 #define FILE_USER_PAGE_MARK_DELETED(vpid) ((VPID *) vpid)->pageid |= FILE_USER_PAGE_MARK_DELETE_FLAG

504 typedef struct file_track_item FILE_TRACK_ITEM;
505 struct file_track_item
506 {
507  INT32 fileid; /* 4 bytes */
508  INT16 volid; /* 2 bytes */
509  INT16 type; /* 2 bytes */
510  FILE_TRACK_METADATA metadata; /* 8 bytes */
511 
512  /* total 16 bytes */
513 };
514

829 /*
830  * file_manager_init () - initialize file manager
831  */
832 int
833 file_manager_init (void)
834 {
835  file_Logging = prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_FILE_LOGGING);
836 
837  assert (FILE_DESCRIPTORS_SIZE == sizeof (FILE_DESCRIPTORS));
838 
839  return file_tempcache_init ();
840 }

852 /* File header section. */
853 /************************************************************************/
854 
855 /*
856  * file_header_init () - initialize file header
857  *
858  * return : void
859  * fhead (out) : output initialized file header
860  */
861 STATIC_INLINE void
862 file_header_init (FILE_HEADER * fhead)
863 {
864  VFID_SET_NULL (&fhead->self);
865 
866  fhead->tablespace.initial_size = 0;
867  fhead->tablespace.expand_ratio = 0;
868  fhead->tablespace.expand_min_size = 0;
869  fhead->tablespace.expand_max_size = 0;
870 
871  fhead->time_creation = 0;
872  fhead->type = FILE_UNKNOWN_TYPE;
873  fhead->file_flags = 0;
874  fhead->volid_last_expand = NULL_VOLDES;
875  VPID_SET_NULL (&fhead->vpid_last_temp_alloc);
876  fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc = NULL_OFFSET;
877  VPID_SET_NULL (&fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab);
878  VPID_SET_NULL (&fhead->vpid_find_nth_last);
879  fhead->first_index_find_nth_last = 0;
880  VPID_SET_NULL (&fhead->vpid_sticky_first);
881 
882  fhead->n_page_total = 0;
883  fhead->n_page_user = 0;
884  fhead->n_page_ftab = 0;
885  fhead->n_page_mark_delete = 0;
886 
887  fhead->n_sector_total = 0;
888  fhead->n_sector_partial = 0;
889  fhead->n_sector_full = 0;
890  fhead->n_sector_empty = 0;
891 
892  fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab = NULL_OFFSET;
893  fhead->offset_to_full_ftab = NULL_OFFSET;
894  fhead->offset_to_user_page_ftab = NULL_OFFSET;
895 
896  fhead->reserved0 = 0;
897  fhead->reserved1 = 0;
898  fhead->reserved2 = 0;
899  fhead->reserved3 = 0;
900 }
901 
902 /*
903  * file_header_sanity_check () - Debug function used to check the sanity of file header before and after certaion file
904  * file operations.
905  *
906  * return : Void.
907  * fhead (in) : File header.
908  */
909 STATIC_INLINE void
910 file_header_sanity_check (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_HEADER * fhead)
911 {
912 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
913  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *part_table;
914  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *full_table;
915  FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR collector;
916  int iter_vsid;
917 
918  if (prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_FORCE_RESTART_TO_SKIP_RECOVERY))
919  {
920  /* we cannot guarantee sanity of files headers */
921  return;
922  }
923 
924  assert (!VFID_ISNULL (&fhead->self));
925 
926  assert (fhead->n_page_total > 0);
927  assert (fhead->n_page_user >= 0);
928  assert (fhead->n_page_ftab > 0);
929  assert (fhead->n_page_free >= 0);
930  assert (fhead->n_page_free + fhead->n_page_user + fhead->n_page_ftab == fhead->n_page_total);
931  assert (fhead->n_page_mark_delete >= 0);
932  assert (fhead->n_page_mark_delete <= fhead->n_page_user);
933 
934  assert (fhead->n_sector_total > 0);
935  assert (fhead->n_sector_partial >= 0);
936  assert (fhead->n_sector_empty >= 0);
937  assert (fhead->n_sector_full >= 0);
938  assert (fhead->n_sector_empty <= fhead->n_sector_partial);
939  assert (fhead->n_sector_partial + fhead->n_sector_full == fhead->n_sector_total);
940 
941  if (fhead->n_page_free == 0)
942  {
943  assert (fhead->n_sector_total == fhead->n_sector_full);
944  }
945 
946  // in some scenario with many file manipulation operations, next checks may be too slow. They gradually stack and
947  // waiting times for file headers grow continuously.
948  // skip the check if there are waiters on file header.
949  // don't skip if file logging is activated. it means a bug in file manipulation is investigated and header checks may
950  // be valuable.
951  if (!prm_get_bool_value (PRM_ID_FILE_LOGGING) && pgbuf_has_any_waiters ((PAGE_PTR) fhead))
952  {
953  return;
954  }
955 
956  er_stack_push ();
957 
958  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, part_table);
959  if (fhead->n_sector_partial == 0)
960  {
961  assert (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead)
962  || (file_extdata_is_empty (part_table) && VPID_ISNULL (&part_table->vpid_next)));
963  }
964  else
965  {
966  int part_cnt = 0;
967 
968  assert (!file_extdata_is_empty (part_table) || !VPID_ISNULL (&part_table->vpid_next));
969 
970  if (file_extdata_all_item_count (thread_p, part_table, &part_cnt) != NO_ERROR)
971  {
972  /* thread might be interrupted; give up checking */
973  ASSERT_ERROR ();
974  goto exit;
975  }
976  assert (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead) || fhead->n_sector_partial == part_cnt);
977  }
978 
979  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
980  {
981  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, full_table);
982  if (fhead->n_sector_full == 0)
983  {
984  assert (file_extdata_is_empty (full_table) && VPID_ISNULL (&full_table->vpid_next));
985  }
986  else
987  {
988  int full_cnt = 0;
989 
990  assert (!file_extdata_is_empty (full_table) || !VPID_ISNULL (&full_table->vpid_next));
991 
992  if (file_extdata_all_item_count (thread_p, full_table, &full_cnt) != NO_ERROR)
993  {
994  /* thread might be interrupted; give up checking */
995  ASSERT_ERROR ();
996  goto exit;
997  }
998  assert (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead) || fhead->n_sector_full == full_cnt);
999  }
1000  }
1001 
1002  if (file_table_collect_all_vsids (thread_p, (PAGE_PTR) fhead, &collector) != NO_ERROR)
1003  {
1004  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1005  goto exit;
1006  }
1007 
1008  for (iter_vsid = 0; iter_vsid < collector.n_vsids - 1; iter_vsid++)
1009  {
1010  /* A VSID can't appears twice in tables. */
1011  assert (disk_compare_vsids (&collector.vsids[iter_vsid], &collector.vsids[iter_vsid + 1]) != 0);
1012  }
1013 
1014  if (collector.vsids != NULL)
1015  {
1016  db_private_free (thread_p, collector.vsids);
1017  }
1018 
1019 exit:
1020  /* forget any error of the function */
1021  er_stack_pop ();
1022 #endif /* !NDEBUG */
1023 }
1024 
1025 /*
1026  * file_rv_fhead_set_last_user_page_ftab () - Recovery of file header: set the VPID of last page in user page table.
1027  *
1028  * return : Error code
1029  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
1030  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
1031  */
1032 int
1033 file_rv_fhead_set_last_user_page_ftab (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
1034 {
1035  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = rcv->pgptr;
1036  VPID *vpid = (VPID *) rcv->data;
1037  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
1038 
1039  assert (rcv->pgptr != NULL);
1040  assert (rcv->length == sizeof (VPID));
1041 
1042  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
1043 
1044  /* the correct VPID is logged. */
1045 
1046  VPID_COPY (&fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab, vpid);
1047 
1048  file_log ("file_rv_fhead_set_last_user_page_ftab",
1049  "update vpid_last_user_page_ftab to %d|%d in file %d|%d, "
1050  "header page %d|%d, lsa %lld|%d ", VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid), VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self),
1051  PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_fhead));
1052 
1053  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
1054  return NO_ERROR;
1055 }
1056 
1057 /*
1058  * file_header_alloc () - Update stats in file header for page allocation.
1059  *
1060  * return : Void
1061  * fhead (in) : File header
1062  * alloc_type (in) : User/table page
1063  * was_empty (in) : True if sector was empty before allocation.
1064  * is_full (in) : True if sector is full after allocation.
1065  */
1066 STATIC_INLINE void
1067 file_header_alloc (FILE_HEADER * fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TYPE alloc_type, bool was_empty, bool is_full)
1068 {
1069  assert (fhead != NULL);
1070  assert (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE || alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE
1071  || alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE_FULL_SECTOR);
1072  assert (!was_empty || !is_full);
1073 
1074  fhead->n_page_free--;
1075  if (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE)
1076  {
1077  fhead->n_page_user++;
1078  }
1079  else
1080  {
1081  fhead->n_page_ftab++;
1082  }
1083 
1084  if (was_empty)
1085  {
1086  fhead->n_sector_empty--;
1087  }
1088 
1089  if (is_full)
1090  {
1091  fhead->n_sector_partial--;
1092  fhead->n_sector_full++;
1093  }
1094 }
1095 
1096 /*
1097  * file_header_dealloc () - Update stats in file header for page deallocation.
1098  *
1099  * return : Void
1100  * fhead (in) : File header
1101  * alloc_type (in) : User/table page
1102  * is_empty (in) : True if sector is empty after deallocation.
1103  * was_full (in) : True if sector was full before deallocation.
1104  */
1105 STATIC_INLINE void
1106 file_header_dealloc (FILE_HEADER * fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TYPE alloc_type, bool is_empty, bool was_full)
1107 {
1108  assert (fhead != NULL);
1109  assert (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE || alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE);
1110  assert (!is_empty || !was_full);
1111 
1112  fhead->n_page_free++;
1113  if (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE)
1114  {
1115  fhead->n_page_user--;
1116  }
1117  else
1118  {
1119  fhead->n_page_ftab--;
1120  }
1121 
1122  if (is_empty)
1123  {
1124  fhead->n_sector_empty++;
1125  }
1126 
1127  if (was_full)
1128  {
1129  fhead->n_sector_partial++;
1130  fhead->n_sector_full--;
1131  }
1132 }

1134 /*
1135  * file_rv_fhead_alloc () - Recovery for file header when a page is allocated.
1136  *
1137  * return : Error code
1138  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
1139  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
1140  */
1141 int
1142 file_rv_fhead_alloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
1143 {
1144  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = rcv->pgptr;
1145  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
1146  bool is_ftab_page;
1147  bool is_full;
1148  bool was_empty;
1149 
1150  assert (rcv->length == sizeof (bool) * 3);
1151 
1152  is_ftab_page = ((bool *) rcv->data)[0];
1153  was_empty = ((bool *) rcv->data)[1];
1154  is_full = ((bool *) rcv->data)[2];
1155 
1156  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
1157 
1158  file_header_alloc (fhead, is_ftab_page ? FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE : FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE, was_empty, is_full);
1159 
1160  file_log ("file_rv_fhead_alloc",
1161  "update header in file %d|%d, header page %d|%d, lsa %lld|%d, "
1162  "after %s, was_empty %s, is_full %s \n" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG,
1163  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_fhead),
1164  FILE_ALLOC_TYPE_STRING (is_ftab_page ? FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE : FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE),
1165  was_empty ? "true" : "false", is_full ? "true" : "false", FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead));
1166 
1167  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
1168 
1169  return NO_ERROR;
1170 }
1171

1173  * file_rv_fhead_dealloc () - Recovery for file header when a page is deallocated.

1177  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
1178  */
1179 int
1180 file_rv_fhead_dealloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)

1189 
1190  is_ftab_page = ((bool *) rcv->data)[0];
1191  is_empty = ((bool *) rcv->data)[1];
1192  was_full = ((bool *) rcv->data)[2];
1193 
1194  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
1195 
1196  file_header_dealloc (fhead, is_ftab_page ? FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE : FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE, is_empty, was_full);
1197 
1198  file_log ("file_rv_fhead_dealloc",
1199  "update header in file %d|%d, header page %d|%d, lsa %lld|%d, "
1200  "after de%s, is_empty %s, was_full %s \n" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG,

1204  is_empty ? "true" : "false", was_full ? "true" : "false", FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead));
1205 
1206  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
1207

1211 /*
1212  * file_log_fhead_alloc () - Log file header statistics update when a page is allocated.
1213  *
1214  * return : Void.
1215  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
1216  * page_fhead (in) : File header page.
1217  * alloc_type (in) : User/table page
1218  * was_empty (in) : True if sector was empty before allocation.
1219  * is_full (in) : True if sector is full after allocation.
1220  */
1221 STATIC_INLINE void
1222 file_log_fhead_alloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TYPE alloc_type, bool was_empty,
1223  bool is_full)
1224 {
1225 #define LOG_BOOL_COUNT 3
1226  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
1227  bool is_ftab_page = alloc_type != FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE;
1228  bool log_bools[3];
1229 
1230  assert (page_fhead != NULL);
1231  assert (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE || alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE
1232  || alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE_FULL_SECTOR);
1233  assert (!was_empty || !is_full);
1234 
1235  log_bools[0] = is_ftab_page;
1236  log_bools[1] = was_empty;
1237  log_bools[2] = is_full;
1238 
1239  addr.pgptr = page_fhead;
1240  log_append_undoredo_data (thread_p, RVFL_FHEAD_ALLOC, &addr, sizeof (log_bools), sizeof (log_bools),
1241  log_bools, log_bools);
1242  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
1243 
1244 #undef LOG_BOOL_COUNT
1245 }
1246 
1247 /*
1248  * file_log_fhead_dealloc () - Log file header statistics update when a page is deallocated.
1249  *
1250  * return : Void.
1251  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
1252  * page_fhead (in) : File header page.
1253  * alloc_type (in) : User/table page
1254  * is_empty (in) : True if sector is empty after deallocation.
1255  * was_full (in) : True if sector was full before deallocation.
1256  */
1257 STATIC_INLINE void
1258 file_log_fhead_dealloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TYPE alloc_type, bool is_empty,
1259  bool was_full)
1260 {
1261 #define LOG_BOOL_COUNT 3
1262  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
1263  bool is_ftab_page = (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE);
1264  bool log_bools[3];
1265 
1266  assert (page_fhead != NULL);
1267  assert (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE || alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE);
1268  assert (!is_empty || !was_full);
1269 
1270  log_bools[0] = is_ftab_page;
1271  log_bools[1] = is_empty;
1272  log_bools[2] = was_full;
1273 
1274  addr.pgptr = page_fhead;
1275  log_append_undoredo_data (thread_p, RVFL_FHEAD_DEALLOC, &addr, sizeof (log_bools), sizeof (log_bools),
1276  log_bools, log_bools);
1277  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
1278 
1279 #undef LOG_BOOL_COUNT
1280 }

1282 /*
1283  * file_header_update_mark_deleted () - Update mark deleted count in file header and log change.
1284  *
1285  * return : Void
1286  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
1287  * page_fhead (in) : File header page
1288  * delta (in) : Mark deleted delta
1289  */
1290 STATIC_INLINE void
1291 file_header_update_mark_deleted (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, int delta)
1292 {
1293  FILE_HEADER *fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
1294  int undo_delta = -delta;
1295 
1296  LOG_LSA save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
1297 
1298  fhead->n_page_mark_delete += delta;
1299 
1300  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
1301  {
1302  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVFL_FHEAD_MARK_DELETE, NULL,
1303  page_fhead, 0, sizeof (undo_delta), sizeof (delta), &undo_delta, &delta);
1304  }
1305  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
1306 
1307  file_log ("file_header_update_mark_deleted",
1308  "updated n_page_mark_delete by %d to %d in file %d|%d, "
1309  "header page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d ", delta,
1310  fhead->n_page_mark_delete, VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_lsa));
1311 }
1312 
1313 /*
1314  * file_rv_header_update_mark_deleted () - Recovery for mark deleted count in file header
1315  *
1316  * return : NO_ERROR
1317  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
1318  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
1319  */
1320 int
1321 file_rv_header_update_mark_deleted (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
1322 {
1323  int delta = *(int *) rcv->data;
1324  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = rcv->pgptr;
1325  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
1326 
1327  assert (page_fhead != NULL);
1328  assert (rcv->length == sizeof (int));
1329 
1330  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
1331  fhead->n_page_mark_delete += delta;
1332  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
1333 
1334  file_log ("file_rv_header_update_mark_deleted",
1335  "modified n_page_mark_delete by %d to %d in file %d|%d, "
1336  "header page %d|%d, lsa %lld|%d", delta,
1337  fhead->n_page_mark_delete, VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_fhead));
1338 
1339  return NO_ERROR;
1340 }

1342 /*
1343  * file_header_copy () - get a file header copy
1344  *
1345  * return : ERROR_CODE
1346  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
1347  * vfid (in) : file identifier
1348  * fhead_copy (out) : file header copy
1349  */
1350 STATIC_INLINE int
1351 file_header_copy (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, FILE_HEADER * fhead_copy)
1352 {
1353  VPID vpid_fhead;
1354  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
1355  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
1356  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
1357 
1358  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
1359  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
1360  if (page_fhead == NULL)
1361  {
1362  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
1363  return error_code;
1364  }
1365  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
1366  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
1367 
1368  *fhead_copy = *fhead;
1369 
1370  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
1371  return NO_ERROR;
1372 }

1374 /*
1375  * file_header_dump () - dump file header to file
1376  *
1377  * return : void
1378  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
1379  * fhead (in) : file header
1380  * fp (in) : output file
1381  */
1382 STATIC_INLINE void
1383 file_header_dump (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const FILE_HEADER * fhead, FILE * fp)
1384 {
1385  fprintf (fp, FILE_HEAD_FULL_MSG, FILE_HEAD_FULL_AS_ARGS (fhead));
1386  file_header_dump_descriptor (thread_p, fhead, fp);
1387 }
1388 
1389 /*
1390  * file_header_dump_descriptor () - dump descriptor in file header
1391  *
1392  * return : void
1393  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
1394  * fhead (in) : file header
1395  * fp (in) : output file
1396  */
1397 STATIC_INLINE void
1398 file_header_dump_descriptor (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const FILE_HEADER * fhead, FILE * fp)
1399 {
1400  switch (fhead->type)
1401  {
1402  case FILE_HEAP:
1403  case FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS:
1404  file_print_name_of_class (thread_p, fp, &fhead->descriptor.heap.class_oid);
1405  fprintf (fp, "\n");
1406  break;
1407 
1408  case FILE_MULTIPAGE_OBJECT_HEAP:
1409  fprintf (fp, "Overflow for HFID: %10d|%5d|%10d\n", HFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->descriptor.heap_overflow.hfid));
1410  break;
1411 
1412  case FILE_BTREE:
1413  {
1414  BTID btid;
1415  char *index_name = NULL;
1416  btid.vfid = fhead->self;
1417  btid.root_pageid = fhead->vpid_sticky_first.pageid;
1418 
1419  if (heap_get_indexinfo_of_btid (thread_p, &fhead->descriptor.btree.class_oid, &btid, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL,
1420  &index_name, NULL) == NO_ERROR)
1421  {
1422  file_print_name_of_class (thread_p, fp, &fhead->descriptor.btree.class_oid);
1423  fprintf (fp, ", %s, ATTRID: %5d \n", index_name != NULL ? index_name : "*UNKNOWN-INDEX*",
1424  fhead->descriptor.btree.attr_id);
1425  }
1426  }
1427  break;
1428 
1429  case FILE_BTREE_OVERFLOW_KEY:
1430  fprintf (fp, "Overflow keys for BTID: %10d|%5d|%10d\n",
1431  BTID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->descriptor.btree_key_overflow.btid));
1432  break;
1433 
1434  case FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH:
1435  case FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH_DIRECTORY:
1436  file_print_name_of_class (thread_p, fp, &fhead->descriptor.ehash.class_oid);
1437  fprintf (fp, ", ATTRID: %5d \n", fhead->descriptor.ehash.attr_id);
1438  break;
1439 
1440  case FILE_TRACKER:
1441  case FILE_CATALOG:
1442  case FILE_QUERY_AREA:
1443  case FILE_TEMP:
1444  case FILE_UNKNOWN_TYPE:
1445  case FILE_DROPPED_FILES:
1446  case FILE_VACUUM_DATA:
1447  default:
1448  break;
1449  }
1450 }
1451 
1452 /************************************************************************/
1453 /* File extensible data section. */
1454 /************************************************************************/
1455 
1456 /*
1457  * file_extdata_init () - Initialize extensible data component for the first time.
1458  *
1459  * return : Void.
1460  * item_size (in) : Size of an item.
1461  * max_size (in) : Desired maximum size for component.
1462  * extdata (out) : Output initialized extensible data.
1463  */
1464 STATIC_INLINE void
1465 file_extdata_init (INT16 item_size, INT16 max_size, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
1466 {
1467  assert (extdata != NULL);
1468  assert (item_size > 0);
1469  assert (max_size > 0);
1470 
1471  VPID_SET_NULL (&extdata->vpid_next);
1472  extdata->size_of_item = item_size;
1473  extdata->n_items = 0;
1474 
1475  /* Align to size of item */
1476  extdata->max_size = DB_ALIGN_BELOW (max_size - FILE_EXTDATA_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE, extdata->size_of_item);
1477  if ((INT16) DB_ALIGN (extdata->max_size, MAX_ALIGNMENT) != extdata->max_size)
1478  {
1479  /* We need max alignment */
1480  extdata->max_size = DB_ALIGN (extdata->max_size - extdata->size_of_item, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
1481  }
1482  /* Safe guard: we should fit at least one item. */
1483  assert (extdata->max_size >= extdata->size_of_item);
1484 }
1485 
1486 /*
1487  * file_extdata_max_size () - Get maximum size of this extensible data including header.
1488  *
1489  * return : Maximum size of extensible data.
1490  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1491  */
1492 STATIC_INLINE int
1493 file_extdata_max_size (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
1494 {
1495  return FILE_EXTDATA_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE + extdata->max_size;
1496 }
1497 
1498 /*
1499  * file_extdata_size () - Get current size of this extensible data including header.
1500  *
1501  * return : Current size of extensible data.
1502  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1503  */
1504 STATIC_INLINE int
1505 file_extdata_size (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
1506 {
1507  return FILE_EXTDATA_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE + extdata->n_items * extdata->size_of_item;
1508 }
1509 
1510 /*
1511  * file_extdata_start () - Get pointer to first item in extensible data.
1512  *
1513  * return : Pointer to first item.
1514  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1515  */
1516 STATIC_INLINE void *
1517 file_extdata_start (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
1518 {
1519  return ((char *) extdata) + FILE_EXTDATA_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE;
1520 }
1521 
1522 /*
1523  * file_extdata_end () - Get pointer to the end of extensible data (after last item).
1524  *
1525  * return : Pointer to end of extensible data.
1526  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1527  */
1528 STATIC_INLINE void *
1529 file_extdata_end (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
1530 {
1531  return ((char *) extdata) + file_extdata_size (extdata);
1532 }
1533 
1534 /*
1535  * file_extdata_is_full () - Is this extensible data full (not enough room foradditional item).
1536  *
1537  * return : True if full, false otherwise.
1538  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1539  */
1540 STATIC_INLINE bool
1541 file_extdata_is_full (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
1542 {
1543  assert (extdata->n_items * extdata->size_of_item <= extdata->max_size);
1544  return (extdata->n_items + 1) * extdata->size_of_item > extdata->max_size;
1545 }
1546 
1547 /*
1548  * file_extdata_is_empty () - Is this extensible data empty?
1549  *
1550  * return : True if empty, false otherwise.
1551  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1552  */
1553 STATIC_INLINE bool
1554 file_extdata_is_empty (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
1555 {
1556  assert (extdata->n_items >= 0);
1557  return (extdata->n_items <= 0);
1558 }
1559 
1560 /*
1561  * file_extdata_item_count () - Get the item count in this extensible data.
1562  *
1563  * return : Item count.
1564  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1565  */
1566 STATIC_INLINE INT16
1567 file_extdata_item_count (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
1568 {
1569  return extdata->n_items;
1570 }
1571 
1572 /*
1573  * file_extdata_remaining_capacity () - Get the remaining capacity (in number of items) of this extensible data.
1574  *
1575  * return : Remaining capacity.
1576  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1577  */
1578 STATIC_INLINE INT16
1579 file_extdata_remaining_capacity (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
1580 {
1581  return extdata->max_size / extdata->size_of_item - extdata->n_items;
1582 }
1583 
1584 /*
1585  * file_extdata_append () - Append an item to extensible data. Caller should have checked there is enough room.
1586  *
1587  * return : Void.
1588  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1589  * append_item (in) : Item to append.
1590  */
1591 STATIC_INLINE void
1592 file_extdata_append (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, const void *append_item)
1593 {
1594  assert (!file_extdata_is_full (extdata));
1595 
1596  memcpy (file_extdata_end (extdata), append_item, extdata->size_of_item);
1597  extdata->n_items++;
1598 }
1599 
1600 /*
1601  * file_extdata_append_array () - Append an array of items to extensible data. Caller should have checked there is
1602  * enough room.
1603  *
1604  * return : Void.
1605  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1606  * append_items (in) : Item array.
1607  * count (in) : Item count.
1608  */
1609 STATIC_INLINE void
1610 file_extdata_append_array (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, const void *append_items, INT16 count)
1611 {
1612  assert (file_extdata_remaining_capacity (extdata) >= count);
1613 
1614  memcpy (file_extdata_end (extdata), append_items, extdata->size_of_item * count);
1615  extdata->n_items += count;
1616 }
1617 
1618 /*
1619  * file_extdata_at () - Pointer to item at given index.
1620  *
1621  * return : Pointer to item.
1622  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1623  * index (in) : Item index.
1624  */
1625 STATIC_INLINE void *
1626 file_extdata_at (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, int index)
1627 {
1628  assert (index >= 0 && index <= extdata->n_items);
1629  return (char *) file_extdata_start (extdata) + extdata->size_of_item * index;
1630 }
1631 
1632 /*
1633  * file_extdata_can_merge () - Check if source extensible data component can be merged into destination extensible data.
1634  *
1635  * return : True if destination extensible data remaining capacity can cover all items in source extensible
1636  * data. False otherwise.
1637  * extdata_src (in) : Source extensible data.
1638  * extdata_dest (in) : Destination extensible data.
1639  */
1640 STATIC_INLINE bool
1641 file_extdata_can_merge (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_src, const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_dest)
1642 {
1643  return file_extdata_remaining_capacity (extdata_dest) >= extdata_src->n_items;
1644 }
1645 
1646 /*
1647  * file_extdata_merge_unordered () - Append source extensible data to destination extensible data.
1648  *
1649  * return : Void.
1650  * extdata_src (in) : Source extensible data.
1651  * extdata_dest (in/out) : Destination extensible data.
1652  */
1653 STATIC_INLINE void
1654 file_extdata_merge_unordered (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_src, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_dest)
1655 {
1656  file_extdata_append_array (extdata_dest, file_extdata_start (extdata_src), file_extdata_item_count (extdata_src));
1657 }
1658 
1659 /*
1660  * file_extdata_merge_ordered () - Merge source extensible data into destination extensible data and keep items ordered.
1661  *
1662  * return : Void.
1663  * extdata_src (in) : Source extensible data.
1664  * extdata_dest (in/out) : Destination extensible data.
1665  * compare_func (in) : Compare function (to order items).
1666  */
1667 STATIC_INLINE void
1668 file_extdata_merge_ordered (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_src, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_dest,
1669  int (*compare_func) (const void *, const void *))
1670 {
1671  char *dest_ptr;
1672  char *dest_end_ptr;
1673  const char *src_ptr;
1674  const char *src_end_ptr;
1675  const char *src_new_ptr;
1676  int memsize = 0;
1677 
1678 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
1679  char *debug_dest_end_ptr =
1680  (char *) file_extdata_end (extdata_dest) + extdata_src->n_items * extdata_src->size_of_item;
1681 #endif /* !NDEBUG */
1682 
1683  /* safe guard: destination has enough capacity to include all source items. */
1684  assert (file_extdata_remaining_capacity (extdata_dest) >= file_extdata_item_count (extdata_src));
1685 
1686  src_ptr = (const char *) file_extdata_start (extdata_src);
1687  src_end_ptr = (const char *) file_extdata_end (extdata_src);
1688 
1689  dest_ptr = (char *) file_extdata_start (extdata_dest);
1690  dest_end_ptr = (char *) file_extdata_end (extdata_dest);
1691 
1692  /* advance source and destination pointers based on item order. Stop when end of destination is reached. */
1693  while (dest_ptr < dest_end_ptr)
1694  {
1695  /* collect all items from source that are smaller than current destination item. */
1696  for (src_new_ptr = src_ptr; src_new_ptr < src_end_ptr; src_new_ptr += extdata_src->size_of_item)
1697  {
1698  assert (compare_func (src_new_ptr, dest_ptr) != 0);
1699  if (compare_func (src_new_ptr, dest_ptr) > 0)
1700  {
1701  break;
1702  }
1703  }
1704  if (src_new_ptr > src_ptr)
1705  {
1706  /* move to dest_ptr */
1707  memsize = (int) (src_new_ptr - src_ptr);
1708  /* make room for new data */
1709  memmove (dest_ptr + memsize, dest_ptr, dest_end_ptr - dest_ptr);
1710  memcpy (dest_ptr, src_ptr, memsize);
1711 
1712  dest_ptr += memsize;
1713  dest_end_ptr += memsize;
1714 
1715  src_ptr = src_new_ptr;
1716 
1717  assert (dest_end_ptr <= debug_dest_end_ptr);
1718  }
1719  if (src_ptr >= src_end_ptr)
1720  {
1721  /* source extensible data was consumed. */
1722  assert (src_ptr == src_end_ptr);
1723  break;
1724  }
1725  /* skip all items from destination smaller than current source item */
1726  for (; dest_ptr < dest_end_ptr; dest_ptr += extdata_dest->size_of_item)
1727  {
1728  assert (compare_func (src_ptr, dest_ptr) != 0);
1729  if (compare_func (src_ptr, dest_ptr) <= 0)
1730  {
1731  break;
1732  }
1733  }
1734  }
1735 
1736  if (src_ptr < src_end_ptr)
1737  {
1738  /* end of destination reached. append remaining source items into destination. */
1739  assert (dest_ptr == dest_end_ptr);
1740  memcpy (dest_end_ptr, src_ptr, src_end_ptr - src_ptr);
1741  assert (dest_end_ptr + (src_end_ptr - src_ptr) == debug_dest_end_ptr);
1742  }
1743  else
1744  {
1745  /* all source items were moved to destination */
1746  assert (debug_dest_end_ptr == dest_end_ptr);
1747  }
1748 
1749  extdata_dest->n_items += extdata_src->n_items;
1750  assert (debug_dest_end_ptr == file_extdata_end (extdata_dest));
1751 }
1752 
1753 /*
1754  * file_extdata_find_ordered () - Find position for given item. If item does not exist, return the position of first
1755  * bigger item.
1756  *
1757  * return : Void.
1758  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1759  * item_to_find (in) : Pointer to item to find.
1760  * compare_func (in) : Compare function used for binary search.
1761  * found (out) : Output true if item was found, false otherwise.
1762  * position (out) : Output the right position of item (found or not found).
1763  */
1764 static void
1765 file_extdata_find_ordered (const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, const void *item_to_find,
1766  int (*compare_func) (const void *, const void *), bool * found, int *position)
1767 {
1768  assert (found != NULL);
1769  assert (position != NULL);
1770 
1771  *position = util_bsearch (item_to_find, file_extdata_start (extdata), file_extdata_item_count (extdata),
1772  extdata->size_of_item, compare_func, found);
1773 }
1774 
1775 /*
1776  * file_extdata_insert_at () - Insert items at given position in extensible data.
1777  *
1778  * return : Void.
1779  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1780  * position (in) : Position to insert items.
1781  * count (in) : Item count.
1782  * data (in) : Items to insert.
1783  */
1784 STATIC_INLINE void
1785 file_extdata_insert_at (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, int position, int count, const void *data)
1786 {
1787  char *copy_at;
1788  int memmove_size;
1789 
1790  assert (extdata != NULL);
1791  assert (!file_extdata_is_full (extdata));
1792  assert (data != NULL);
1793  assert (position >= 0 && position <= file_extdata_item_count (extdata));
1794 
1795  /* move current items at desired position to the right. */
1796  memmove_size = (extdata->n_items - position) * extdata->size_of_item;
1797  copy_at = (char *) file_extdata_at (extdata, position);
1798  if (memmove_size > 0)
1799  {
1800  memmove (copy_at + extdata->size_of_item * count, copy_at, memmove_size);
1801  }
1802 
1803  /* copy new items at position */
1804  memcpy (copy_at, data, extdata->size_of_item * count);
1805 
1806  /* update item count */
1807  extdata->n_items += count;
1808 }
1809 
1810 /*
1811  * file_extdata_remove_at () - Remove items from give position in extensible data.
1812  *
1813  * return : Void.
1814  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1815  * position (in) : Position where items must be removed.
1816  * count (in) : Item count.
1817  */
1818 STATIC_INLINE void
1819 file_extdata_remove_at (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, int position, int count)
1820 {
1821  char *remove_at;
1822  int memmove_size;
1823 
1824  if (position < 0 || position >= extdata->n_items)
1825  {
1826  /* bad index. give up */
1827  assert_release (false);
1828  return;
1829  }
1830 
1831  /* remove items */
1832  remove_at = (char *) file_extdata_at (extdata, position);
1833  memmove_size = (extdata->n_items - count - position) * extdata->size_of_item;
1834  if (memmove_size > 0)
1835  {
1836  memmove (remove_at, remove_at + extdata->size_of_item * count, memmove_size);
1837  }
1838 
1839  /* update item count */
1840  extdata->n_items -= count;
1841 }
1842 
1843 /*
1844  * file_extdata_apply_funcs () - Process extensible data components and apply functions to each component and/or to each
1845  * item.
1846  *
1847  * return : Error code.
1848  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
1849  * extdata_in (in) : First extensible data component.
1850  * f_extdata (in) : Function to apply for each extensible data component (can be NULL).
1851  * f_extdata_args (in/out) : Argument for component function.
1852  * f_item (in) : Function to apply for each item (can be NULL).
1853  * f_item_args (in/out) : Argument for item function.
1854  * for_write (in) : Should page be fixed for write?
1855  * extdata_out (out) : Output current extensible data component if processing is stopped.
1856  * page_out (out) : Output page of current extensible data component if processing is stopped.
1857  */
1858 static int
1859 file_extdata_apply_funcs (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_in, FILE_EXTDATA_FUNC f_extdata,
1860  void *f_extdata_args, FILE_EXTDATA_ITEM_FUNC f_item, void *f_item_args,
1861  bool for_write, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA ** extdata_out, PAGE_PTR * page_out)
1862 {
1863  int i;
1864  bool stop = false; /* forces to stop processing extensible data */
1865  PAGE_PTR page_extdata = NULL; /* extensible data page */
1866  PGBUF_LATCH_MODE latch_mode = for_write ? PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE : PGBUF_LATCH_READ;
1867  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
1868  VPID vpid_next = VPID_INITIALIZER;
1869 
1870  if (page_out != NULL)
1871  {
1872  *page_out = NULL; /* make it sure for an error */
1873  }
1874 
1875  while (true)
1876  {
1877  /* catch infinite loop, if any */
1878  assert (page_extdata == NULL || !VPID_EQ (pgbuf_get_vpid_ptr (page_extdata), &extdata_in->vpid_next));
1879  if (f_extdata != NULL)
1880  {
1881  /* apply f_extdata */
1882  error_code = f_extdata (thread_p, extdata_in, &stop, f_extdata_args);
1883  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1884  {
1885  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1886  goto exit;
1887  }
1888  if (stop)
1889  {
1890  /* stop processing */
1891  goto exit;
1892  }
1893  }
1894 
1895  if (f_item != NULL)
1896  {
1897  /* iterate through all items in current page. */
1898  for (i = 0; i < file_extdata_item_count (extdata_in); i++)
1899  {
1900  /* apply f_item */
1901  error_code = f_item (thread_p, file_extdata_at (extdata_in, i), i, &stop, f_item_args);
1902  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
1903  {
1904  ASSERT_ERROR ();
1905  goto exit;
1906  }
1907  if (stop)
1908  {
1909  goto exit;
1910  }
1911  }
1912  }
1913 
1914  if (VPID_ISNULL (&extdata_in->vpid_next))
1915  {
1916  /* end of extensible data. */
1917  break;
1918  }
1919  vpid_next = extdata_in->vpid_next;
1920 
1921  /* advance to next page */
1922  if (page_extdata != NULL)
1923  {
1924  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_extdata);
1925  }
1926  page_extdata = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, latch_mode, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
1927  if (page_extdata == NULL)
1928  {
1929  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
1930  goto exit;
1931  }
1932  /* get component in next page */
1933  extdata_in = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_extdata;
1934  }
1935 
1936 exit:
1937  if (stop && page_out != NULL)
1938  {
1939  /* output current page */
1940  *page_out = page_extdata;
1941  }
1942  else if (page_extdata != NULL)
1943  {
1944  /* unfix current page */
1945  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_extdata);
1946  }
1947 
1948  if (stop && extdata_out != NULL)
1949  {
1950  /* output current extensible data component */
1951  *extdata_out = extdata_in;
1952  }
1953 
1954  return error_code;
1955 }
1956 
1957 /*
1958  * file_extdata_func_for_search_ordered () - Function callable by file_extdata_apply_funcs; binary search for an item
1959  * in ordered extensible data.
1960  *
1961  * return : NO_ERROR.
1962  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
1963  * extdata (in) : Extensible data.
1964  * stop (out) : Output true when item is found and search can be stopped.
1965  * args (in/out) : Search context.
1966  */
1967 static int
1968 file_extdata_func_for_search_ordered (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, bool * stop,
1969  void *args)
1970 {
1971  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA_SEARCH_CONTEXT *search_context = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA_SEARCH_CONTEXT *) args;
1972 
1973  assert (search_context != NULL);
1974 
1975  file_extdata_find_ordered (extdata, search_context->item_to_find, search_context->compare_func,
1976  &search_context->found, &search_context->position);
1977  if (search_context->found)
1978  {
1979  *stop = true;
1980  }
1981 
1982  return NO_ERROR;
1983 }
1984 
1985 /*
1986  * file_extdata_item_func_for_search () - Function callable by file_extdata_apply_funcs; searches item by comparing
1987  * extensible data item to the item in search context.
1988  *
1989  * return : NO_ERROR.
1990  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
1991  * item (in) : Item in extensible data.
1992  * index (in) : Index of item in extensible data.
1993  * stop (out) : Output true when item is found and search can be stopped.
1994  * args (in/out) : Search context.
1995  */
1996 static int
1997 file_extdata_item_func_for_search (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const void *item, int index, bool * stop, void *args)
1998 {
1999  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA_SEARCH_CONTEXT *search_context = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA_SEARCH_CONTEXT *) args;
2000 
2001  if (search_context->compare_func (search_context->item_to_find, item) == 0)
2002  {
2003  /* Found */
2004  search_context->found = true;
2005  search_context->position = index;
2006  *stop = true;
2007  }
2008  return NO_ERROR;
2009 }
2010 
2011 /*
2012  * file_extdata_search_item () - Search for item in extensible data.
2013  *
2014  * return : Error code.
2015  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
2016  * extdata (in/out) : Extensible data. First component as input, component where item was found as output.
2017  * item_to_find (in) : Searched item.
2018  * compare_func (in) : Compare function used to find item.
2019  * is_ordered (in) : True if items in extensible are ordered and can be searched using binary search. False otherwise
2020  * for_write (in) : Should page be fixed for write?
2021  * found (out) : Output true if item is found in extensible data, false otherwise.
2022  * position (out) : Output the position of found item (if found) in its extensible data component.
2023  * page_extdata (out) : Output page of extensible data component where item is found (if found).
2024  */
2025 static int
2026 file_extdata_search_item (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA ** extdata, const void *item_to_find,
2027  int (*compare_func) (const void *, const void *),
2028  bool is_ordered, bool for_write, bool * found, int *position, PAGE_PTR * page_extdata)
2029 {
2030  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA_SEARCH_CONTEXT search_context;
2031  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_in = *extdata;
2032  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
2033 
2034  search_context.item_to_find = item_to_find;
2035  search_context.compare_func = compare_func;
2036  search_context.found = false;
2037  search_context.position = -1;
2038 
2039  if (is_ordered)
2040  {
2041  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_in, file_extdata_func_for_search_ordered,
2042  &search_context, NULL, NULL, for_write, extdata, page_extdata);
2043  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
2044  {
2045  ASSERT_ERROR ();
2046  assert (*page_extdata == NULL);
2047  return error_code;
2048  }
2049  }
2050  else
2051  {
2052  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_in, NULL, NULL, file_extdata_item_func_for_search,
2053  &search_context, for_write, extdata, page_extdata);
2054  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
2055  {
2056  ASSERT_ERROR ();
2057  assert (*page_extdata == NULL);
2058  return error_code;
2059  }
2060  }
2061 
2062  if (found != NULL)
2063  {
2064  *found = search_context.found;
2065  }
2066 
2067  if (position != NULL)
2068  {
2069  *position = search_context.position;
2070  }
2071 
2072  return NO_ERROR;
2073 }
2074 
2075 /*
2076  * file_extdata_find_not_full () - Find an extensible data component that is not full.
2077  *
2078  * return : Error code.
2079  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
2080  * extdata (in/out) : Extensible data. First component as input, component where free space is found as output.
2081  * page_out (out) : Output page of component with free space.
2082  * found (out) : Output true if a component with free space is found.
2083  */
2084 static int
2085 file_extdata_find_not_full (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA ** extdata, PAGE_PTR * page_out, bool * found)
2086 {
2087  VPID vpid_next;
2088  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
2089 
2090  assert (extdata != NULL && *extdata != NULL);
2091  assert (page_out != NULL);
2092  assert (found != NULL);
2093 
2094  /* how it works:
2095  * we are looking for the first extensible data component that still has space for one additional item. the extensible
2096  * data and page where the space is found is then output.
2097  *
2098  * note: the input page is usually NULL. the input extensible data usually belongs to file header. this would unfix
2099  * page_out when it advances to next page and we don't want to unfix header page.
2100  * note: if all extensible data components are full, the last extensible data and page are output. the caller can
2101  * then use them to append a new page and a new extensible data component.
2102  */
2103 
2104  *found = false;
2105 
2106  while (file_extdata_is_full (*extdata))
2107  {
2108  VPID_COPY (&vpid_next, &(*extdata)->vpid_next);
2109  if (VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_next))
2110  {
2111  /* Not found. */
2112  return NO_ERROR;
2113  }
2114 
2115  /* Move to next page */
2116  if (*page_out != NULL)
2117  {
2118  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, *page_out);
2119  }
2120 
2121  *page_out = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
2122  if (*page_out == NULL)
2123  {
2124  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
2125  return error_code;
2126  }
2127 
2128  *extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) (*page_out);
2129  }
2130 
2131  /* Found not full */
2132  *found = true;
2133  return NO_ERROR;
2134 }
2135 
2136 /*
2137  * file_rv_extdata_set_next () - Recovery function to set extensible data next page.
2138  *
2139  * return : NO_ERROR.
2140  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
2141  * rcv (in) : Recovery data.
2142  */
2143 int
2144 file_rv_extdata_set_next (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
2145 {
2146  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = rcv->pgptr;
2147  VPID *vpid_next = (VPID *) rcv->data;
2148  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata = NULL;
2149 
2150  assert (page_ftab != NULL);
2151  assert (rcv->length == sizeof (VPID));
2152  assert (rcv->offset >= 0 && rcv->offset < DB_PAGESIZE);
2153 
2154  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) (page_ftab + rcv->offset);
2155  VPID_COPY (&extdata->vpid_next, vpid_next);
2156 
2157  file_log ("file_rv_extdata_set_next",
2158  "page %d|%d, lsa %lld|%d, changed extdata link \n"
2159  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("extdata after"), PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_ftab), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata));
2160 
2161  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_ftab, DONT_FREE);
2162  return NO_ERROR;
2163 }

2181 /*
2182  * file_rv_extdata_add () - Add items to extensible data for recovery.

2186  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
2187  */

2196  assert (rcv->offset >= 0 && rcv->offset < DB_PAGESIZE);
2197

2199  offset += sizeof (pos);
2200

2202  offset += sizeof (count);
2203

2212  PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_ftab), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata));
2213 
2214  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_ftab, DONT_FREE);
2215  return NO_ERROR;
2216 }

2303 /*
2304  * file_log_extdata_add () - Log adding items to extensible data
2305  *
2306  * return : Void
2307  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
2308  * extdata (in) : Extensible data
2309  * page (in) : Page of extensible data
2310  * position (in) : Position in extensible data where items are added
2311  * count (in) : Item count
2312  * data (in) : Item(s)
2313  */
2314 STATIC_INLINE void
2315 file_log_extdata_add (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p,
2316  const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, PAGE_PTR page, int position, int count, const void *data)
2317 {
2318  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
2319  LOG_CRUMB crumbs[3];
2320 
2321  addr.pgptr = page;
2322  addr.offset = (PGLENGTH) (((char *) extdata) - page);
2323 
2324  crumbs[0].data = &position;
2325  crumbs[0].length = sizeof (position);
2326 
2327  crumbs[1].data = &count;
2328  crumbs[1].length = sizeof (count);
2329 
2330  crumbs[2].data = data;
2331  crumbs[2].length = extdata->size_of_item * count;
2332 
2333  log_append_undoredo_crumbs (thread_p, RVFL_EXTDATA_ADD, &addr, 2, 3, crumbs, crumbs);
2334  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page, DONT_FREE);
2335 }

2337 /*
2338  * file_log_extdata_remove () - Log removing items from extensible data
2339  *
2340  * return : Void

2342  * extdata (in) : Extensible data
2343  * page (in) : Page of extensible data
2344  * position (in) : Position in extensible data from where items are removed
2345  * count (in) : Item count

2347 STATIC_INLINE void
2348 file_log_extdata_remove (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p,

2367  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page, DONT_FREE);
2368 }

2371  * file_log_extdata_set_next () - Log setting next page VPID into extensible data
2372  *
2373  * return : Void

2375  * extdata (in) : Extensible data
2376  * page (in) : Page of extensible data
2377  * vpid_next (in) : New value for next page VPID.

2379 STATIC_INLINE void
2380 file_log_extdata_set_next (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, PAGE_PTR page,
2381  const VPID * vpid_next)

2385

2388  /* extdata should belong to page */
2389  assert (addr.offset >= 0 && addr.offset < DB_PAGESIZE);

2393  vpid_next);

2397  "change extdata link to %d|%d, \n"
2398  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("extdata before"),
2399  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page, &save_lsa), VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_next), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata));
2400 
2401  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page, DONT_FREE);
2402 }
2403 
2404 /*
2405  * file_rv_extdata_merge () - recovery of merging extensible data components
2406  *
2407  * return : NO_ERROR
2408  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
2409  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
2410  */
2411 int
2412 file_rv_extdata_merge (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
2413 {
2414  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_in_page;
2415  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_in_rcv;
2416 
2417  assert (rcv->pgptr != NULL);
2418  assert (rcv->offset >= 0 && rcv->offset < DB_PAGESIZE);
2419 
2420  /* how it works:
2421  * the entire extensible data is logged before and after merge. so this is used for both undo and redo.
2422  */
2423 
2424  extdata_in_page = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) (rcv->pgptr + rcv->offset);
2425  extdata_in_rcv = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) rcv->data;
2426 
2427  assert (file_extdata_size (extdata_in_rcv) == rcv->length);
2428 
2429  /* overwrite extdata with recovery. */
2430  memcpy (extdata_in_page, extdata_in_rcv, rcv->length);
2431  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, rcv->pgptr, DONT_FREE);
2432 
2433  file_log ("file_rv_extdata_merge", PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_MSG ("extensible data page") FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("extdata after"),
2434  PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (rcv->pgptr), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_in_page));
2435 
2436  return NO_ERROR;
2437 }
2438 
2439 /*
2440  * file_extdata_update_item () - Update extensible data item and log the change.
2441  *
2442  * return : void
2443  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
2444  * page_extdata (in) : page of extensible data
2445  * item_newval (in) : new item value
2446  * index_item (in) : index to item being updated
2447  * extdata (in/out) : extensible data (one item is modified in this function)
2448  */
2449 STATIC_INLINE void
2450 file_extdata_update_item (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_extdata, const void *item_newval, int index_item,
2451  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata)
2452 {
2453  char *item_in_page = (char *) file_extdata_at (extdata, index_item);
2454  PGLENGTH offset_in_page = (PGLENGTH) (item_in_page - page_extdata);
2455 
2456  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVFL_EXTDATA_UPDATE_ITEM, NULL, page_extdata, offset_in_page,
2457  extdata->size_of_item, extdata->size_of_item, item_in_page, item_newval);
2458 
2459  memcpy (item_in_page, item_newval, extdata->size_of_item);
2460  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_extdata, DONT_FREE);
2461 }
2462 
2463 /*
2464  * file_extdata_merge_pages () - try to merge source extensible data page into destination extensible data page
2465  *
2466  * return : return true if pages have been merged, false otherwise
2467  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
2468  * extdata_src (in) : source extensible data
2469  * page_src (in) : source extensible data page
2470  * extdata_dest (in) : destination extensible data
2471  * page_dest (in) : destination extensible data page
2472  * compare_func (in) : compare function (required if items are ordered)
2473  * ordered (in) : true if items are ordered in pages (order must be preserved)
2474  */
2475 STATIC_INLINE bool
2476 file_extdata_merge_pages (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_src, const PAGE_PTR page_src,
2477  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_dest, PAGE_PTR page_dest,
2478  int (*compare_func) (const void *, const void *), bool ordered)
2479 {
2480  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
2481  LOG_LSA save_lsa = LSA_INITIALIZER;
2482 
2483  assert (extdata_dest != NULL && page_dest != NULL);
2484  assert ((char *) extdata_dest >= page_dest && (char *) extdata_dest < page_dest + DB_PAGESIZE);
2485  assert (extdata_src != NULL && page_src != NULL);
2486  assert ((char *) extdata_src >= page_src && (char *) extdata_src < page_src + DB_PAGESIZE);
2487  assert (!ordered || compare_func != NULL);
2488  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
2489 
2490  if (!file_extdata_can_merge (extdata_src, extdata_dest))
2491  {
2492  /* not enough space */
2493  return false;
2494  }
2495 
2496  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_dest);
2497  /* log previous extensible data */
2498  addr.pgptr = page_dest;
2499  addr.offset = (PGLENGTH) (((char *) extdata_dest) - page_dest);
2500  log_append_undo_data (thread_p, RVFL_EXTDATA_MERGE, &addr, file_extdata_size (extdata_dest), extdata_dest);
2501 
2502  if (ordered)
2503  {
2504  /* ordered merge */
2505  file_extdata_merge_ordered (extdata_src, extdata_dest, compare_func);
2506  }
2507  else
2508  {
2509  /* unordered merge */
2510  file_extdata_merge_unordered (extdata_src, extdata_dest);
2511  }
2512  /* update vpid_next */
2513  extdata_dest->vpid_next = extdata_src->vpid_next;
2514 
2515  /* log new extensible data */
2516  log_append_redo_data (thread_p, RVFL_EXTDATA_MERGE, &addr, file_extdata_size (extdata_dest), extdata_dest);
2517  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_dest, DONT_FREE);
2518 
2519  file_log ("file_extdata_merge_pages", "merged extensible data: \n" FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("extdata dest")
2520  "\t" PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_MSG ("page dest") "\n" FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("extdata src")
2521  "\t" PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_MSG ("page src") "\n", FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_dest),
2522  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_dest, &save_lsa), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_src),
2523  PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_src));
2524 
2525  /* successful merge */
2526  return true;
2527 }
2528 
2529 /*
2530  * file_extdata_find_and_remove_item () - find an item in extensible data and remove it. if possible, also merge
2531  * extensible data pages
2532  *
2533  * return : error code
2534  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
2535  * extdata_first (in) : first extensible data
2536  * page_first (in) : first extensible data page
2537  * item (in) : item to find
2538  * compare_func (in) : compare function
2539  * ordered (in) : true if each extensible data page is ordered
2540  * item_pop (out) : if not NULL it will output the item removed from extensible data.
2541  * vpid_merged (out) : output the vpid if merged extensible data page or NULL vpid.
2542  */
2543 static int
2544 file_extdata_find_and_remove_item (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata_first, PAGE_PTR page_first,
2545  const void *item, int (*compare_func) (const void *, const void *), bool ordered,
2546  void *item_pop, VPID * vpid_merged)
2547 {
2548  PAGE_PTR page_prev = NULL;
2549  PAGE_PTR page_crt = NULL;
2550  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_prev = NULL;
2551  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_crt = NULL;
2552  bool found = false;
2553  int pos = 0;
2554  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
2555  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
2556 
2557  assert (extdata_first != NULL);
2558  assert (page_first != NULL);
2559  assert (item != NULL);
2560  assert (compare_func != NULL);
2561  assert (vpid_merged != NULL);
2562  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
2563 
2564  /* how it works:
2565  *
2566  * first we must find the item in one of the extensible pages. we iterate through each page and try to find the item.
2567  * during page iteration we save the previous page (it is NULL when current page is first).
2568  *
2569  * if the items are ordered in each page, a binary search is executed. if not, items are compared one by one.
2570  *
2571  * when the item is found, it is removed from page. we also try to merge it with previous page or to merge next page
2572  * into current page. if merge is executed, the merged page vpid is output.
2573  *
2574  * if item_pop is not NULL, the removed item will be copied (note that the item is not always identical to search
2575  * item).
2576  */
2577 
2578  VPID_SET_NULL (vpid_merged);
2579 
2580  /* iterate through extensible data pages */
2581  extdata_crt = extdata_first;
2582  page_crt = page_first;
2583  while (true)
2584  {
2585  /* search item: do binary search if page is ordered, otherwise iterate through all until matched */
2586  if (ordered)
2587  {
2588  file_extdata_find_ordered (extdata_crt, item, compare_func, &found, &pos);
2589  }
2590  else
2591  {
2592  for (pos = 0; pos < file_extdata_item_count (extdata_crt); pos++)
2593  {
2594  if (compare_func (item, file_extdata_at (extdata_crt, pos)) == 0)
2595  {
2596  found = true;
2597  break;
2598  }
2599  }
2600  }
2601 
2602  if (found)
2603  {
2604  /* found item. remove it */
2605  assert (pos >= 0 && pos < file_extdata_item_count (extdata_crt));
2606 
2607  if (item_pop != NULL)
2608  {
2609  /* output item before removing */
2610  memcpy (item_pop, file_extdata_at (extdata_crt, pos), extdata_crt->size_of_item);
2611  }
2612 
2613  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_crt);
2614  file_log_extdata_remove (thread_p, extdata_crt, page_crt, pos, 1);
2615  file_extdata_remove_at (extdata_crt, pos, 1);
2616 
2617  file_log ("file_extdata_find_and_remove_item", "removed extensible data item: \n"
2618  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("extensible data") "\t" PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_MSG ("extensible data page") "\n"
2619  "\tposition = %d \n", FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_crt),
2620  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_crt, &save_lsa), pos);
2621 
2622  if (page_prev != NULL)
2623  {
2624  /* try to merge to previous page */
2625  assert (extdata_prev != NULL);
2626 
2627  if (file_extdata_merge_pages (thread_p, extdata_crt, page_crt, extdata_prev, page_prev, compare_func,
2628  ordered))
2629  {
2630  pgbuf_get_vpid (page_crt, vpid_merged);
2631  /* we are done here */
2632  goto exit;
2633  }
2634  }
2635  }
2636  if (VPID_ISNULL (&extdata_crt->vpid_next))
2637  {
2638  break;
2639  }
2640  if (page_prev != NULL && page_prev != page_first)
2641  {
2642  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_prev);
2643  }
2644  page_prev = page_crt;
2645  extdata_prev = extdata_crt;
2646  page_crt = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &extdata_prev->vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
2647  if (page_crt == NULL)
2648  {
2649  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
2650  goto exit;
2651  }
2652  extdata_crt = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_crt;
2653  if (found)
2654  {
2655  /* try to merge to previous page */
2656  if (file_extdata_merge_pages (thread_p, extdata_crt, page_crt, extdata_prev, page_prev, compare_func,
2657  ordered))
2658  {
2659  pgbuf_get_vpid (page_crt, vpid_merged);
2660  }
2661  break;
2662  }
2663  }
2664  if (!found)
2665  {
2666  /* item is missing which is unexpected */
2667  assert_release (false);
2668  error_code = ER_FAILED;
2669  goto exit;
2670  }
2671 
2672  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
2673 
2674 exit:
2675  assert (page_prev != page_crt);
2676 
2677  if (page_prev != NULL && page_prev != page_first)
2678  {
2679  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_prev);
2680  }
2681  if (page_crt != NULL && page_crt != page_first)
2682  {
2683  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_crt);
2684  }
2685  return error_code;
2686 }
2687

2724 /*
2725  * file_partsect_is_full () - Is partial sector full?
2726  *
2727  * return : True if partial sector is full, false otherwise.
2728  * partsect (in) : Partial sector.
2729  */
2730 STATIC_INLINE bool
2731 file_partsect_is_full (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR * partsect)
2732 {
2733  return partsect->page_bitmap == FILE_FULL_PAGE_BITMAP;
2734 }
2735 
2736 /*
2737  * file_partsect_is_empty () - Is partial sector empty?
2738  *
2739  * return : True if partial sector is empty, false otherwise.
2740  * partsect (in) : Partial sector.
2741  */
2742 STATIC_INLINE bool
2743 file_partsect_is_empty (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR * partsect)
2744 {
2745  return partsect->page_bitmap == FILE_EMPTY_PAGE_BITMAP;
2746 }
2747 
2748 /*
2749  * file_partsect_is_bit_set () - Is bit in partial sector bitmap set at offset?
2750  *
2751  * return : True if bit is set, false otherwise.
2752  * partsect (in) : Partial sector.
2753  * offset (in) : Offset to bit.
2754  */
2755 STATIC_INLINE bool
2756 file_partsect_is_bit_set (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR * partsect, int offset)
2757 {
2758  return bit64_is_set (partsect->page_bitmap, offset);
2759 }
2760 
2761 /*
2762  * file_partsect_set_bit () - Set bit in partial sector bitmap at offset. The bit is expected to be unset.
2763  *
2764  * return : Void.
2765  * partsect (in) : Partial sector.
2766  * offset (in) : Offset to bit.
2767  */
2768 STATIC_INLINE void
2769 file_partsect_set_bit (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR * partsect, int offset)
2770 {
2771  assert (!file_partsect_is_bit_set (partsect, offset));
2772 
2773  partsect->page_bitmap = bit64_set (partsect->page_bitmap, offset);
2774 }
2775 
2776 /*
2777  * file_partsect_clear_bit () - Clear bit in partial sector bitmap at offset. The bit is expected to be set.
2778  *
2779  * return : Void.
2780  * partsect (in) : Partial sector.
2781  * offset (in) : Offset to bit.
2782  */
2783 STATIC_INLINE void
2784 file_partsect_clear_bit (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR * partsect, int offset)
2785 {
2786  assert (file_partsect_is_bit_set (partsect, offset));
2787 
2788  partsect->page_bitmap = bit64_clear (partsect->page_bitmap, offset);
2789 }
2790 
2791 /*
2792  * file_partsect_pageid_to_offset () - Convert pageid to offset in sector bitmap.
2793  *
2794  * return : Offset to bit in bitmap.
2795  * partsect (in) : Partial sector.
2796  * pageid (in) : Page ID.
2797  */
2798 STATIC_INLINE int
2799 file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR * partsect, PAGEID pageid)
2800 {
2801  assert (SECTOR_FROM_PAGEID (pageid) == partsect->vsid.sectid);
2802 
2803  if (SECTOR_FROM_PAGEID (pageid) != partsect->vsid.sectid)
2804  {
2805  return -1;
2806  }
2807 
2808  return (int) (pageid - SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (partsect->vsid.sectid));
2809 }
2810 
2811 /*
2812  * file_partsect_alloc () - Try to allocate a page in partial sector.
2813  *
2814  * return : True if allocation was successful. False if the partial sector was actually full.
2815  * partsect (in/out) : Partial sector to allocate a page from. The allocated page bit is set afterwards.
2816  * vpid_out (out) : If not NULL, it outputs the VPID of allocated page.
2817  * offset_out (out) : If not NULL, it outputs the allocated page bit offset in bitmap.
2818  */
2819 STATIC_INLINE bool
2820 file_partsect_alloc (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR * partsect, VPID * vpid_out, int *offset_out)
2821 {
2822  int offset_to_zero = bit64_count_trailing_ones (partsect->page_bitmap);
2823 
2824  if (offset_to_zero >= FILE_ALLOC_BITMAP_NBITS)
2825  {
2826  assert (file_partsect_is_full (partsect));
2827  return false;
2828  }
2829 
2830  assert (offset_to_zero >= 0);
2831 
2832  file_partsect_set_bit (partsect, offset_to_zero);
2833  if (offset_out)
2834  {
2835  *offset_out = offset_to_zero;
2836  }
2837 
2838  if (vpid_out)
2839  {
2840  vpid_out->volid = partsect->vsid.volid;
2841  vpid_out->pageid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (partsect->vsid.sectid) + offset_to_zero;
2842  }
2843 
2844  return true;
2845 }
2846 
2847 /*
2848  * file_rv_partsect_update () - Set/clear bit in partial sector for recovery.
2849  *
2850  * return : Error code
2851  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
2852  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
2853  * set (in) : True if bit should be set, false if bit should be cleared
2854  */
2855 static int
2856 file_rv_partsect_update (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv, bool set)
2857 {
2858  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = rcv->pgptr;
2859  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *partsect;
2860  int offset;
2861 
2862  assert (page_ftab != NULL);
2863  assert (rcv->offset >= 0 && rcv->offset < DB_PAGESIZE);
2864 
2865  offset = *(int *) rcv->data;
2866  assert (rcv->length == sizeof (offset));
2867 
2868  partsect = (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) (page_ftab + rcv->offset);
2869  if (set)
2870  {
2871  file_partsect_set_bit (partsect, offset);
2872  }
2873  else
2874  {
2875  file_partsect_clear_bit (partsect, offset);
2876  }
2877 
2878  file_log ("file_rv_partsect_update",
2879  "recovery partial sector update in page %d|%d prev_lsa %lld|%d: "
2880  "%s bit at offset %d, partial sector offset %d \n"
2881  FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("partsect after rcv"),
2882  PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (rcv->pgptr), set ? "set" : "clear", offset, rcv->offset,
2883  FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (partsect));
2884 
2885  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_ftab, DONT_FREE);
2886  return NO_ERROR;
2887 }
2888 
2889 /*
2890  * file_rv_partsect_set () - Set bit in partial sector for recovery.
2891  *
2892  * return : Error code
2893  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
2894  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
2895  */
2896 int
2897 file_rv_partsect_set (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
2898 {
2899  return file_rv_partsect_update (thread_p, rcv, true);
2900 }
2901 
2902 /*
2903  * file_rv_partsect_clear () - Clear bit in partial sector for recovery.
2904  *
2905  * return : Error code
2906  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
2907  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
2908  */
2909 int
2910 file_rv_partsect_clear (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)

2913 }
