2919 /*
2920  * file_compare_vpids () - Compare two page identifiers.
2921  *
2922  * return : 1 if first page is bigger, -1 if first page is smaller and 0 if page ids are equal
2923  * first (in) : first page id
2924  * second (in) : second page id
2925  *
2926  * note: we need to ignore FILE_USER_PAGE_MARK_DELETED flag.
2927  */
2928 static int
2929 file_compare_vpids (const void *first, const void *second)
2930 {
2931  VPID first_vpid = *(VPID *) first;
2932  VPID second_vpid = *(VPID *) second;
2933 
2934  if (first_vpid.volid == second_vpid.volid)
2935  {
2936  FILE_USER_PAGE_CLEAR_MARK_DELETED (&first_vpid);
2937  FILE_USER_PAGE_CLEAR_MARK_DELETED (&second_vpid);
2938  return first_vpid.pageid - second_vpid.pageid;
2939  }
2940  else
2941  {
2942  return first_vpid.volid - second_vpid.volid;
2943  }
2944 }
2945 
2946 /*
2947  * file_compare_vfids () - Compare two file identifiers.
2948  *
2949  * return : positive if first file is bigger, negative if first file is smaller and 0 if page ids are equal
2950  * first (in) : first file id
2951  * second (in) : second file id
2952  *
2953  * note: we need to ignore FILE_USER_PAGE_MARK_DELETED flag.
2954  */
2955 static int
2956 file_compare_vfids (const void *first, const void *second)
2957 {
2958  VFID *first_vfid = (VFID *) first;
2959  VFID *second_vfid = (VFID *) second;
2960 
2961  if (first_vfid->volid > second_vfid->volid)
2962  {
2963  return 1;
2964  }
2965  if (first_vfid->volid < second_vfid->volid)
2966  {
2967  return -1;
2968  }
2969  return first_vfid->fileid - second_vfid->fileid;
2970 }
2971 
2972 /*
2973  * file_compare_track_items () - compare two file tracker items
2974  *
2975  * return : positive if first item is bigger, negative if first item is smaller, 0 if items are equal
2976  * first (in) : first item
2977  * second (in) : second item
2978  */
2979 static int
2980 file_compare_track_items (const void *first, const void *second)
2981 {
2982  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *first_item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) first;
2983  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *second_item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) second;
2984 
2985  if (first_item->volid > second_item->volid)
2986  {
2987  return 1;
2988  }
2989  if (first_item->volid < second_item->volid)
2990  {
2991  return -1;
2992  }
2993  return first_item->fileid - second_item->fileid;
2994 }

3115 /*
3116  * file_create_temp_internal () - common function to create files for temporary purpose. always try to use a cached
3117  * temporary file first. if there is no cached entry, create a new file.
3118  * in the end save the temp cache entry in transaction list of temporary files.
3119  *
3120  * return : error code
3121  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
3122  * npages (in) : desired number of pages (ignored when taking file from cache)
3123  * ftype (in) : file type
3124  * is_numerable (in) : true if file must be numerable, false if should be regular file
3125  * vfid_out (out) : VFID of file (obtained from cache or created).
3126  */
3127 STATIC_INLINE int
3128 file_create_temp_internal (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, int npages, FILE_TYPE ftype, bool is_numerable, VFID * vfid_out)
3129 {
3130  FILE_TABLESPACE tablespace;
3131  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *tempcache_entry = NULL;
3132  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
3133 
3134  assert (npages > 0);
3135 
3136  error_code = file_tempcache_get (thread_p, ftype, is_numerable, &tempcache_entry);
3137  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3138  {
3139  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3140  return error_code;
3141  }
3142  assert (tempcache_entry != NULL);
3143  assert (tempcache_entry->ftype == ftype);
3144 
3145  if (VFID_ISNULL (&tempcache_entry->vfid))
3146  {
3147  FILE_TABLESPACE_FOR_TEMP_NPAGES (&tablespace, npages);
3148  error_code = file_create (thread_p, ftype, &tablespace, NULL, true, is_numerable, vfid_out);
3149  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3150  {
3151  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3152  file_tempcache_retire_entry (tempcache_entry);
3153  return error_code;
3154  }
3155  tempcache_entry->vfid = *vfid_out;
3156  }
3157  else
3158  {
3159  /* we use the cached file */
3160  /* what about the number of pages? */
3161  *vfid_out = tempcache_entry->vfid;
3162  }
3163 
3164  /* save to transaction temporary file list */
3165  file_tempcache_push_tran_file (thread_p, tempcache_entry);
3166  return NO_ERROR;
3167 }

3266  * des (in) : File descriptor (based on file type).
3267  * is_temp (in) : True if file should be temporary.
3268  * is_numerable (in) : True if file should be numerable.
3269  * vfid (out) : Output new file identifier.
3270  */
3271 int
3272 file_create (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_TYPE file_type,
3273  FILE_TABLESPACE * tablespace, FILE_DESCRIPTORS * des, bool is_temp, bool is_numerable, VFID * vfid)
3274 {
3275  INT64 total_size;
3276  int n_sectors;
3277  VSID *vsids_reserved = NULL;
3278  bool was_temp_reserved = false;
3279  DB_VOLPURPOSE volpurpose = DISK_UNKNOWN_PURPOSE;
3280  VSID *vsid_iter = NULL;
3281  INT16 size = 0;
3282  VOLID volid_last_expand;
3283 
3284  /* File header vars */
3285  VPID vpid_fhead = VPID_INITIALIZER;
3286  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
3287  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
3288 
3289  /* File table vars */
3290  INT64 max_size_ftab;
3291  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *partsect_ftab = NULL;
3292  VPID vpid_ftab = VPID_INITIALIZER;
3293  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
3294  bool found_vfid_page = false;
3295  INT16 offset_ftab = 0;
3296 
3297  /* Partial table. */
3298  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR partsect;
3299 
3300  /* File extensible data */
3301  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab = NULL;
3302  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab_in_fhead = NULL;
3303  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_full_ftab = NULL;
3304  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_user_page_ftab = NULL;
3305 
3306  /* Recovery */
3307  bool is_sysop_started = false;
3308  bool do_logging = !is_temp;
3309 
3310  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
3311 
3312  assert (tablespace->initial_size > 0);
3313  assert (file_type != FILE_TEMP || is_temp);
3314  assert (vfid != NULL);
3315 
3316  /* Estimate the required size including file header & tables. */
3317  total_size = tablespace->initial_size;
3318 
3319  if (!is_numerable)
3320  {
3321  /* Partial & full sectors tables.
3322  * The worst case is when all sectors are partially allocated. The required size will be sizeof (SECTOR_ID) and
3323  * the size of bitmap (in bytes), which counts to 16 bytes, for each sector. The sector size will be at least
3324  * 4k * 64 => 256KB. So we need to increase the total size of file with 16 bytes per every 256KB, or 1 byte for
3325  * each 16KB. Then we need again to consider the additional space used by table (another 1 byte for 16KB x 16 KB).
3326  * This of course translates to an infinite series and we want to simplify that. So, adding 1 byte for each 8KB
3327  * from the start should cover any space required by file tables.
3328  */
3329  max_size_ftab = total_size / 8 / 1024;
3330  total_size += max_size_ftab;
3331  }
3332  else
3333  {
3334  /* Partial & full sectors tables + page table.
3335  * By applying the same logic above, we consider the worst case (which is impossible actually) all sectors are
3336  * partially allocated (16 bytes per sector) and all pages are allocated by user (64 * 8 byte per sector). This
3337  * totals to 528 bytes for each 256KB bytes of data. By doubling the estimated size of tables, we need an extra
3338  * 1 byte for each 256KB / 528 / 2, which is equivalent to 1 byte for each 8/33 KB.
3339  */
3340  max_size_ftab = total_size * 33 / 8 / 1024;
3341  total_size += max_size_ftab;
3342  }
3343 
3344  /* convert the disk size to number of sectors. */
3345  n_sectors = (int) CEIL_PTVDIV (total_size, DB_SECTORSIZE);
3346  assert (n_sectors > 0);
3347  /* allocate a buffer to store all reserved sectors */
3348  vsids_reserved = (VSID *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, n_sectors * sizeof (VSID));
3349  if (vsids_reserved == NULL)
3350  {
3351  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, n_sectors * sizeof (VSID));
3352  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
3353  goto exit;
3354  }
3355 
3356  if (do_logging)
3357  {
3358  /* start a system operation */
3359  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
3360  is_sysop_started = true;
3361  }
3362 
3363  /* reserve sectors on disk */
3364  volpurpose = is_temp ? DB_TEMPORARY_DATA_PURPOSE : DB_PERMANENT_DATA_PURPOSE;
3365 
3366  file_log ("file_create",
3367  "create %s file \n\t%s \n\t%s \n" FILE_TABLESPACE_MSG
3368  " \tnsectors = %d", file_type_to_string (file_type),
3369  FILE_PERM_TEMP_STRING (is_temp),
3370  FILE_NUMERABLE_REGULAR_STRING (is_numerable), FILE_TABLESPACE_AS_ARGS (tablespace), n_sectors);
3371 
3372  error_code = disk_reserve_sectors (thread_p, volpurpose, NULL_VOLID, n_sectors, vsids_reserved);
3373  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3374  {
3375  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3376  goto exit;
3377  }
3378  /* found enough sectors to reserve */
3379  was_temp_reserved = is_temp;
3380 
3381  /* sort sectors by VSID. but before sorting, remember last volume ID used for reservations. */
3382  volid_last_expand = vsids_reserved[n_sectors - 1].volid;
3383  qsort (vsids_reserved, n_sectors, sizeof (VSID), disk_compare_vsids);
3384 
3385  /* decide on what page to use as file header page (which is going to decide the VFID also). */
3386 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
3387  if (file_type == FILE_BTREE || file_type == FILE_HEAP || file_type == FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS)
3388  {
3389  /* we need to consider dropped files in vacuum's list. If we create a file with a duplicate VFID, we can run
3390  * into problems. */
3391  VSID *vsid_iter = vsids_reserved;
3392  VFID vfid_iter;
3393  VFID found_vfid = VFID_INITIALIZER;
3394  MVCCID tran_mvccid = logtb_get_current_mvccid (thread_p);
3395  /* we really have to have the VFID in the same volume as the first allocated page. this means we cannot change
3396  * volume when we look for a valid VFID. */
3397  VOLID first_volid = vsids_reserved[0].volid;
3398  bool is_file_dropped;
3399 
3400  for (vsid_iter = vsids_reserved;
3401  vsid_iter < vsids_reserved + n_sectors && VFID_ISNULL (&found_vfid)
3402  && vsid_iter->volid == first_volid; vsid_iter++)
3403  {
3404  vfid_iter.volid = vsid_iter->volid;
3405  for (vfid_iter.fileid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (vsid_iter->sectid);
3406  vfid_iter.fileid <= SECTOR_LAST_PAGEID (vsid_iter->sectid); vfid_iter.fileid++)
3407  {
3408  error_code = vacuum_is_file_dropped (thread_p, &is_file_dropped, &vfid_iter, tran_mvccid);
3409  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3410  {
3411  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3412  goto exit;
3413  }
3414 
3415  if (is_file_dropped == false)
3416  {
3417  /* Good we found a file ID that is not considered dropped. */
3418  found_vfid = vfid_iter;
3419  break;
3420  }
3421  }
3422  }
3423  if (VFID_ISNULL (&found_vfid))
3424  {
3425  /* this is ridiculous. */
3426  assert_release (false);
3427  error_code = ER_FAILED;
3428  goto exit;
3429  }
3430  *vfid = found_vfid;
3431  }
3432  else
3433 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
3434  {
3435  vfid->volid = vsids_reserved->volid;
3436  vfid->fileid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (vsids_reserved->sectid);
3437  }
3438 
3439  assert (!VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
3440  vpid_fhead.volid = vfid->volid;
3441  vpid_fhead.pageid = vfid->fileid;
3442 
3443  file_log ("file_create", "chose VFID = %d|%d.", VFID_AS_ARGS (vfid));
3444 
3445  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, NEW_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
3446  if (page_fhead == NULL)
3447  {
3448  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
3449  goto exit;
3450  }
3451 
3452  memset (page_fhead, 0, DB_PAGESIZE);
3453  pgbuf_set_page_ptype (thread_p, page_fhead, PAGE_FTAB);
3454  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
3455 
3456  /* initialize header */
3457  fhead->self = *vfid;
3458  fhead->tablespace = *tablespace;
3459  if (des != NULL)
3460  {
3461  fhead->descriptor = *des;
3462  }
3463  fhead->time_creation = time (NULL);
3464  fhead->type = file_type;
3465  fhead->file_flags = 0;
3466  if (is_numerable)
3467  {
3468  fhead->file_flags |= FILE_FLAG_NUMERABLE;
3469  }
3470  if (is_temp)
3471  {
3472  fhead->file_flags |= FILE_FLAG_TEMPORARY;
3473  }
3474 
3475  fhead->volid_last_expand = volid_last_expand;
3476  VPID_SET_NULL (&fhead->vpid_last_temp_alloc);
3477  fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc = NULL_OFFSET;
3478  VPID_SET_NULL (&fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab);
3479  VPID_SET_NULL (&fhead->vpid_find_nth_last);
3480  fhead->first_index_find_nth_last = 0;
3481  VPID_SET_NULL (&fhead->vpid_sticky_first);
3482 
3483  fhead->n_page_total = 0;
3484  fhead->n_page_user = 0;
3485  fhead->n_page_ftab = 1; /* file header */
3486  fhead->n_page_free = 0;
3487  fhead->n_page_mark_delete = 0;
3488 
3489  fhead->n_sector_total = 0;
3490  fhead->n_sector_partial = 0;
3491  fhead->n_sector_full = 0;
3492  fhead->n_sector_empty = 0;
3493 
3494  fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab = NULL_OFFSET;
3495  fhead->offset_to_full_ftab = NULL_OFFSET;
3496  fhead->offset_to_user_page_ftab = NULL_OFFSET;
3497 
3498  fhead->reserved0 = 0;
3499  fhead->reserved1 = 0;
3500  fhead->reserved2 = 0;
3501  fhead->reserved3 = 0;
3502 
3503  /* start with a negative empty sector (because we have allocated header). */
3504  fhead->n_sector_empty--;
3505 
3506  /* start creating required file tables.
3507  * file tables depend of the properties of permanent/temporary and numerable.
3508  * temporary files do not use full table, only partial table. permanent files use both partial and full tables.
3509  * numerable files (which can be both permanent or temporary) also require user page table.
3510  */
3511  offset_ftab = FILE_HEADER_ALIGNED_SIZE;
3512  if (is_numerable)
3513  {
3514  if (is_temp)
3515  {
3516  /* split the header page space into: 1/16 for partial table and 15/16 for user page table */
3517  fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab = offset_ftab;
3518  assert ((INT16) DB_ALIGN (fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab, MAX_ALIGNMENT) == fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab);
3519  size = (DB_PAGESIZE - offset_ftab) / 16;
3520  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
3521  file_extdata_init (sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR), size, extdata_part_ftab);
3522 
3523  offset_ftab += file_extdata_max_size (extdata_part_ftab);
3524  }
3525  else
3526  {
3527  /* split the header space into three: 1/32 for each partial and full sector tables and the rest (15/16) for
3528  * user page table. */
3529 
3530  /* partial table. */
3531  fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab = offset_ftab;
3532  assert ((INT16) DB_ALIGN (fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab, MAX_ALIGNMENT) == fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab);
3533  size = (DB_PAGESIZE - offset_ftab) / 32;
3534  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
3535  file_extdata_init (sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR), size, extdata_part_ftab);
3536 
3537  /* full table. */
3538  offset_ftab += file_extdata_max_size (extdata_part_ftab);
3539  fhead->offset_to_full_ftab = offset_ftab;
3540  assert ((INT16) DB_ALIGN (fhead->offset_to_full_ftab, MAX_ALIGNMENT) == fhead->offset_to_full_ftab);
3541  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_full_ftab);
3542  file_extdata_init (sizeof (VSID), size, extdata_full_ftab);
3543 
3544  offset_ftab += file_extdata_max_size (extdata_full_ftab);
3545  }
3546 
3547  /* user page table - consume remaining space. */
3548  fhead->offset_to_user_page_ftab = offset_ftab;
3549  assert ((INT16) DB_ALIGN (fhead->offset_to_user_page_ftab, MAX_ALIGNMENT) == fhead->offset_to_user_page_ftab);
3550  size = DB_PAGESIZE - offset_ftab;
3551  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_user_page_ftab);
3552  file_extdata_init (sizeof (VPID), size, extdata_user_page_ftab);
3553  }
3554  else
3555  {
3556  if (is_temp)
3557  {
3558  /* keep only partial table. */
3559  fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab = offset_ftab;
3560  assert ((INT16) DB_ALIGN (fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab, MAX_ALIGNMENT) == fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab);
3561  size = DB_PAGESIZE - offset_ftab;
3562  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
3563  file_extdata_init (sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR), size, extdata_part_ftab);
3564  }
3565  else
3566  {
3567  /* split the header space into two: half for partial table and half for full table. */
3568 
3569  /* partial table. */
3570  fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab = offset_ftab;
3571  assert ((INT16) DB_ALIGN (fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab, MAX_ALIGNMENT) == fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab);
3572  size = (DB_PAGESIZE - offset_ftab) / 2;
3573  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
3574  file_extdata_init (sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR), size, extdata_part_ftab);
3575 
3576  /* full table. */
3577  offset_ftab += file_extdata_max_size (extdata_part_ftab);
3578  fhead->offset_to_full_ftab = offset_ftab;
3579  assert ((INT16) DB_ALIGN (fhead->offset_to_full_ftab, MAX_ALIGNMENT) == fhead->offset_to_full_ftab);
3580  size = DB_PAGESIZE - offset_ftab;
3581  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_full_ftab);
3582  file_extdata_init (sizeof (VSID), size, extdata_full_ftab);
3583  }
3584  }
3585  /* all required tables are created */
3586  /* all files must have partial table */
3587  assert (fhead->offset_to_partial_ftab != NULL_OFFSET);
3588 
3589  /* start populating partial table */
3590  /* partial sectors are initially added to the table in header. if the file is really big, and the table needs to
3591  * extend on other pages, we will keep track of pages/sectors used for file table using extdata_part_ftab.
3592  */
3593  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
3594  extdata_part_ftab_in_fhead = extdata_part_ftab;
3595  for (vsid_iter = vsids_reserved; vsid_iter < vsids_reserved + n_sectors; vsid_iter++)
3596  {
3597  if (file_extdata_is_full (extdata_part_ftab))
3598  {
3599  /* a new page for file table is required */
3600 
3601  /* allocate a page from partial table. */
3602  if (partsect_ftab == NULL)
3603  {
3604  /* This is first page. */
3605  assert (!file_extdata_is_empty (extdata_part_ftab));
3606  partsect_ftab = (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) file_extdata_start (extdata_part_ftab);
3607  vpid_ftab.pageid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (partsect_ftab->vsid.sectid);
3608  vpid_ftab.volid = partsect_ftab->vsid.volid;
3609 
3610  if (!VSID_IS_SECTOR_OF_VPID (&partsect_ftab->vsid, &vpid_fhead))
3611  {
3612  /* another non-empty sector. */
3613  fhead->n_sector_empty--;
3614  }
3615  else
3616  {
3617  /* this non-empty sector was already counted */
3618  }
3619  }
3620  else if (file_partsect_is_full (partsect_ftab))
3621  {
3622  /* move to next partial sector. */
3623  partsect_ftab++;
3624  if ((void *) partsect_ftab >= file_extdata_end (extdata_part_ftab_in_fhead))
3625  {
3626  /* This is not possible! */
3627  assert_release (false);
3628  error_code = ER_FAILED;
3629  goto exit;
3630  }
3631  vpid_ftab.pageid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (partsect_ftab->vsid.sectid);
3632  vpid_ftab.volid = partsect_ftab->vsid.volid;
3633 
3634  if (!VSID_IS_SECTOR_OF_VPID (&partsect_ftab->vsid, &vpid_fhead))
3635  {
3636  /* another non-empty sector. */
3637  fhead->n_sector_empty--;
3638  }
3639  else
3640  {
3641  /* this non-empty sector was already counted */
3642  }
3643 
3644  fhead->n_sector_full++;
3645  }
3646  else
3647  {
3648  vpid_ftab.pageid++;
3649  }
3650 
3651  if (VPID_EQ (&vpid_fhead, &vpid_ftab))
3652  {
3653  /* Go to next page. This can't be last page in sector, because the sector bitmap would have been full */
3654  assert (file_partsect_is_bit_set (partsect_ftab,
3655  file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (partsect_ftab, vpid_fhead.pageid)));
3656  vpid_ftab.pageid++;
3657  found_vfid_page = true;
3658  }
3659  /* Set bit in sector bitmap */
3660  file_partsect_set_bit (partsect_ftab, file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (partsect_ftab, vpid_ftab.pageid));
3661 
3662  /* Save link in previous page. */
3663  extdata_part_ftab->vpid_next = vpid_ftab;
3664  if (page_ftab != NULL)
3665  {
3666  if (do_logging)
3667  {
3668  pgbuf_log_new_page (thread_p, page_ftab, file_extdata_size (extdata_part_ftab), PAGE_FTAB);
3669  }
3670  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_ftab, FREE);
3671  }
3672  page_ftab = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_ftab, NEW_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
3673  if (page_ftab == NULL)
3674  {
3675  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
3676  goto exit;
3677  }
3678  pgbuf_set_page_ptype (thread_p, page_ftab, PAGE_FTAB);
3679  memset (page_ftab, 0, DB_PAGESIZE);
3680  extdata_part_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
3681  file_extdata_init (sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR), DB_PAGESIZE, extdata_part_ftab);
3682 
3683  fhead->n_page_ftab++;
3684  }
3685  assert (!file_extdata_is_full (extdata_part_ftab));
3686 
3687  partsect.vsid = *vsid_iter;
3688  partsect.page_bitmap = FILE_EMPTY_PAGE_BITMAP;
3689  if (partsect.vsid.sectid == SECTOR_FROM_PAGEID (vpid_fhead.pageid) && partsect.vsid.volid == vpid_fhead.volid)
3690  {
3691  /* Set bit for file header page. */
3692  file_partsect_set_bit (&partsect, file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (&partsect, vpid_fhead.pageid));
3693  }
3694  file_extdata_append (extdata_part_ftab, &partsect);
3695  }
3696 
3697  if (page_ftab != NULL)
3698  {
3699  if (do_logging)
3700  {
3701  pgbuf_log_new_page (thread_p, page_ftab, file_extdata_size (extdata_part_ftab), PAGE_FTAB);
3702  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
3703  }
3704  else
3705  {
3706  pgbuf_set_dirty_and_free (thread_p, page_ftab);
3707  }
3708  }
3709 
3710  if (partsect_ftab == NULL)
3711  {
3712  /* all partial sectors were fitted in header page */
3713  assert (fhead->n_sector_full == 0);
3714  }
3715  else
3716  {
3717  if (file_partsect_is_full (partsect_ftab))
3718  {
3719  partsect_ftab++;
3720  fhead->n_sector_full++;
3721  }
3722  if (!is_temp && fhead->n_sector_full > 0)
3723  {
3724  /* move sectors fully used by file table to full table */
3725  int i;
3726  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *partsect_iter;
3727  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
3728  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_full_ftab);
3729 
3730  for (i = 0; i < fhead->n_sector_full; i++)
3731  {
3732  partsect_iter = (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) file_extdata_at (extdata_part_ftab, i);
3733  if (file_extdata_is_full (extdata_full_ftab))
3734  {
3735  /* Not possible. */
3736  assert_release (false);
3737  error_code = ER_FAILED;
3738  goto exit;
3739  }
3740  file_extdata_append (extdata_full_ftab, &partsect_iter->vsid);
3741  }
3742  /* Remove full sectors from partial table. */
3743  file_extdata_remove_at (extdata_part_ftab, 0, fhead->n_sector_full);
3744  assert (fhead->n_sector_full == file_extdata_item_count (extdata_full_ftab));
3745  }
3746  }
3747 
3748  if (is_temp)
3749  {
3750  /* temporary files do not keep separate tables for partial and full sectors. just set last allocation location. */
3751  VPID_COPY (&fhead->vpid_last_temp_alloc, &vpid_fhead);
3752  fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc = fhead->n_sector_full;
3753  }
3754 
3755  if (is_numerable)
3756  {
3757  /* set last user page table VPID to header */
3758  fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab = vpid_fhead;
3759  fhead->vpid_find_nth_last = vpid_fhead;
3760  }
3761 
3762  /* set all stats */
3763  /* sector stats; full stats already counted, empty stats are negative (we need to add partial sectors) */
3764  fhead->n_sector_total = n_sectors;
3765  fhead->n_sector_partial = fhead->n_sector_total - fhead->n_sector_full;
3766  fhead->n_sector_empty += fhead->n_sector_partial;
3767  /* page stats; file table pages already counted; user pages remain 0 */
3768  fhead->n_page_total = fhead->n_sector_total * DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES;
3769  fhead->n_page_free = fhead->n_page_total - fhead->n_page_ftab;
3770 
3771  /* File header ready. */
3772  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
3773 
3774  file_log ("file_create", "finished creating file. \n" FILE_HEAD_FULL_MSG, FILE_HEAD_FULL_AS_ARGS (fhead));
3775 
3776  if (do_logging)
3777  {
3778  pgbuf_log_new_page (thread_p, page_fhead, DB_PAGESIZE, PAGE_FTAB);
3779  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_fhead);
3780  }
3781  else
3782  {
3783  pgbuf_set_dirty_and_free (thread_p, page_fhead);
3784  }
3785 
3786  if (!is_temp && file_type != FILE_TRACKER)
3787  {
3788  /* add to tracker */
3789  error_code = file_tracker_register (thread_p, vfid, file_type, NULL);
3790  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3791  {
3792  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3793  goto exit;
3794  }
3795  }
3796 
3797  if (is_temp)
3798  {
3799  /* update stats */
3800  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.nfile, 1);
3801  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_ftab, fhead->n_page_ftab);
3802  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_user, fhead->n_page_user);
3803  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_reserved, fhead->n_page_free);
3804  }
3805 
3806  /* Fall through to exit */
3807 exit:
3808 
3809  if (page_ftab != NULL)
3810  {
3811  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab);
3812  }
3813  if (page_fhead != NULL)
3814  {
3815  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
3816  }
3817 
3818  if (is_sysop_started)
3819  {
3820  assert (do_logging);
3821  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3822  {
3823  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3824  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
3825  }
3826  else
3827  {
3828  ASSERT_NO_ERROR ();
3829  log_sysop_end_logical_undo (thread_p, RVFL_DESTROY, NULL, sizeof (*vfid), (char *) vfid);
3830  }
3831  }
3832 
3833  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3834  {
3835  /* make sure we don't output a bad VFID. */
3836  VFID_SET_NULL (vfid);
3837 
3838  if (was_temp_reserved)
3839  {
3840  /* recovery won't free reserved sectors. we have to manually handle the unreserve */
3841  bool save_check_interrupt = logtb_set_check_interrupt (thread_p, false);
3842 
3843  /* make sure sectors are sorted */
3844  qsort (vsids_reserved, n_sectors, sizeof (VSID), disk_compare_vsids);
3845  if (disk_unreserve_ordered_sectors (thread_p, DB_TEMPORARY_DATA_PURPOSE, n_sectors, vsids_reserved)
3846  != NO_ERROR)
3847  {
3848  /* sectors are leaked */
3849  assert_release (false);
3850  /* fall through */
3851  }
3852  (void) logtb_set_check_interrupt (thread_p, save_check_interrupt);
3853  }
3854  }
3855 
3856  if (vsids_reserved != NULL)
3857  {
3858  /* Deallocate reserved_sectors */
3859  db_private_free (thread_p, vsids_reserved);
3860  }
3861 
3862  return error_code;
3863 }
3864 
3865 /*
3866  * file_table_collect_vsid () - Function callable by file_extdata_apply_funcs. Used to collect sector ID's from file
3867  * tables.
3868  *
3869  * return : NO_ERROR
3870  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
3871  * item (in) : Item in extensible data (VSID or FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR which starts with a VSID)
3872  * index_unused (in) : Unused
3873  * stop (out) : Unused
3874  * args (in/out) : VSID collector
3875  */
3876 static int
3877 file_table_collect_vsid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const void *item, int index_unused, bool * stop, void *args)
3878 {
3879  const VSID *vsid = (VSID *) item;
3880  FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR *collector = (FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR *) args;
3881 
3882  collector->vsids[collector->n_vsids++] = *vsid;
3883 
3884  return NO_ERROR;
3885 }
3886 
3887 /*
3888  * file_table_collect_all_vsids () - collect all sectors from file table
3889  *
3890  * return : error code
3891  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
3892  * page_fhead (in) : file header page
3893  * collector_out (out) : output VSID collector
3894  */
3895 STATIC_INLINE int
3896 file_table_collect_all_vsids (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR * collector_out)
3897 {
3898  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
3899  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_ftab;
3900  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
3901 
3902  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
3903 
3904  collector_out->vsids = (VSID *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, fhead->n_sector_total * sizeof (VSID));
3905  if (collector_out->vsids == NULL)
3906  {
3907  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
3908  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, error_code, 1, fhead->n_sector_total * sizeof (VSID));
3909  return error_code;
3910  }
3911  collector_out->n_vsids = 0;
3912 
3913  /* Collect from partial table */
3914  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
3915  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, NULL, NULL, file_table_collect_vsid, collector_out,
3916  false, NULL, NULL);
3917  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3918  {
3919  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3920  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, collector_out->vsids);
3921  return error_code;
3922  }
3923 
3924  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
3925  {
3926  /* Collect from full table. */
3927  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
3928  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, NULL, NULL, file_table_collect_vsid,
3929  collector_out, false, NULL, NULL);
3930  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
3931  {
3932  ASSERT_ERROR ();
3933  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, collector_out->vsids);
3934  return error_code;
3935  }
3936  }
3937 
3938  if (collector_out->n_vsids != fhead->n_sector_total)
3939  {
3940  assert_release (false);
3941  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, collector_out->vsids);
3942  return ER_FAILED;
3943  }
3944 
3945  qsort (collector_out->vsids, fhead->n_sector_total, sizeof (VSID), disk_compare_vsids);
3946 
3947  return NO_ERROR;
3948 }
3949 
3950 /*
3951  * file_sector_map_dealloc () - FILE_EXTDATA_ITEM_FUNC to deallocate user pages
3952  *
3953  * return : error code
3954  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
3955  * data (in) : FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR * or VSID *
3956  * index (in) : unused
3957  * stop (in) : unused
3958  * args (in) : is_partial
3959  */
3960 static int
3961 file_sector_map_dealloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const void *data, int index, bool * stop, void *args)
3962 {
3963  bool is_partial = *(bool *) args;
3964  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR partsect = FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR_INITIALIZER;
3965  int offset = 0;
3966  VPID vpid;
3967  PAGE_PTR page = NULL;
3968  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
3969 
3970  if (is_partial)
3971  {
3972  partsect = *(FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) data;
3973  }
3974  else
3975  {
3976  partsect.vsid = *(VSID *) data;
3977  }
3978 
3979  vpid.volid = partsect.vsid.volid;
3980  for (offset = 0, vpid.pageid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (partsect.vsid.sectid); offset < DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES;
3981  offset++, vpid.pageid++)
3982  {
3983  if (is_partial && !file_partsect_is_bit_set (&partsect, offset))
3984  {
3985  /* not allocated */
3986  continue;
3987  }
3988 
3989  page = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
3990  if (page == NULL)
3991  {
3992  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
3993  return error_code;
3994  }
3995 
3996  if (pgbuf_get_page_ptype (thread_p, page) == PAGE_FTAB)
3997  {
3998  /* table page, do not deallocate yet */
3999  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page);
4000  continue;
4001  }
4002  pgbuf_dealloc_page (thread_p, page);
4003  page = NULL;
4004  }
4005 
4006  return NO_ERROR;
4007 }
4008 
4009 /*
4010  * file_destroy () - Destroy file - unreserve all sectors used by file on disk.
4011  *
4012  * return : Error code
4013  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
4014  * vfid (in) : File identifier
4015  * is_temp (in) : True for temporary, false otherwise. Caller must know. It relevant information before fixing the file
4016  * header page, whe, if not temporary, we need to remove from file tracker.
4017  */
4018 int
4019 file_destroy (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, bool is_temp)
4020 {
4021  VPID vpid_fhead;
4022  PAGE_PTR page_fhead;
4023  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
4024  FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR vsid_collector;
4025  FILE_FTAB_COLLECTOR ftab_collector;
4026  DB_VOLPURPOSE volpurpose;
4027  bool save_check_interrupt = false;
4028  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4029 
4030  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
4031 
4032  if (is_temp)
4033  {
4034  /* do not interrupt destroying temporary files. it will leak pages. */
4035  save_check_interrupt = logtb_set_check_interrupt (thread_p, false);
4036  }
4037  else
4038  {
4039  /* permanent files are first removed from tracker */
4040  error_code = file_tracker_unregister (thread_p, vfid);
4041  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4042  {
4043  assert_release (false);
4044  goto exit;
4045  }
4046  }
4047 
4048  vsid_collector.vsids = NULL;
4049  ftab_collector.partsect_ftab = NULL;
4050 
4051  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
4052  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
4053  if (page_fhead == NULL)
4054  {
4055  assert_release (!is_temp);
4056  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4057  goto exit;
4058  }
4059 
4060  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
4061 
4062  assert (is_temp == FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
4063  assert (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead) || log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
4064 
4065  error_code = file_table_collect_all_vsids (thread_p, page_fhead, &vsid_collector);
4066  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4067  {
4068  assert_release (false);
4069  goto exit;
4070  }
4071  volpurpose = FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead) ? DB_TEMPORARY_DATA_PURPOSE : DB_PERMANENT_DATA_PURPOSE;
4072 
4073  file_log ("file_destroy",
4074  "file %d|%d unreserve %d sectors \n" FILE_HEAD_FULL_MSG,
4075  VFID_AS_ARGS (vfid), fhead->n_sector_total, FILE_HEAD_FULL_AS_ARGS (fhead));
4076 
4077  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
4078  {
4079  /* we need to deallocate pages */
4080  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_ftab = NULL;
4081  bool is_partial;
4082  int iter_sects;
4083  int offset;
4084  VPID vpid_ftab;
4085  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
4086 
4087  ftab_collector.npages = 0;
4088  ftab_collector.nsects = 0;
4089  ftab_collector.partsect_ftab =
4090  (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, fhead->n_page_ftab * sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR));
4091  if (ftab_collector.partsect_ftab == NULL)
4092  {
4093  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
4094  fhead->n_page_ftab * sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR));
4095  error_code = ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
4096  goto exit;
4097  }
4098 
4099  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
4100  is_partial = true;
4101  error_code =
4102  file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, file_extdata_collect_ftab_pages, &ftab_collector,
4103  file_sector_map_dealloc, &is_partial, true, NULL, NULL);
4104  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4105  {
4106  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4107  goto exit;
4108  }
4109 
4110  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
4111  is_partial = false;
4112  error_code =
4113  file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, file_extdata_collect_ftab_pages, &ftab_collector,
4114  file_sector_map_dealloc, &is_partial, true, NULL, NULL);
4115  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4116  {
4117  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4118  goto exit;
4119  }
4120 
4121  /* deallocate table pages - other than header page */
4122  for (iter_sects = 0; iter_sects < ftab_collector.nsects; iter_sects++)
4123  {
4124  vpid_ftab.volid = ftab_collector.partsect_ftab[iter_sects].vsid.volid;
4125  for (offset = 0,
4126  vpid_ftab.pageid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (ftab_collector.partsect_ftab[iter_sects].vsid.sectid);
4127  offset < DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES; offset++, vpid_ftab.pageid++)
4128  {
4129  if (file_partsect_is_bit_set (&ftab_collector.partsect_ftab[iter_sects], offset))
4130  {
4131  page_ftab = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_ftab, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
4132  if (page_ftab == NULL)
4133  {
4134  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
4135  goto exit;
4136  }
4137  pgbuf_dealloc_page (thread_p, page_ftab);
4138  page_ftab = NULL;
4139  }
4140  }
4141  }
4142  /* deallocate header page */
4143  pgbuf_dealloc_page (thread_p, page_fhead);
4144  page_fhead = NULL;
4145  }
4146  else
4147  {
4148  /* todo: invalidate pages in page buffer. actually move them to the bottom of LRU lists. */
4149  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.nfile, -1);
4150  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_ftab, -fhead->n_page_ftab);
4151  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_user, -fhead->n_page_user);
4152  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_reserved, -fhead->n_page_free);
4153  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_fhead);
4154  }
4155 
4156  /* release occupied sectors on disk */
4157  error_code = disk_unreserve_ordered_sectors (thread_p, volpurpose, vsid_collector.n_vsids, vsid_collector.vsids);
4158  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4159  {
4160  assert_release (false);
4161  goto exit;
4162  }
4163 
4164  /* Done */
4165  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
4166 
4167 exit:
4168  if (page_fhead != NULL)
4169  {
4170  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
4171  }
4172  if (vsid_collector.vsids != NULL)
4173  {
4174  db_private_free (thread_p, vsid_collector.vsids);
4175  }
4176  if (ftab_collector.partsect_ftab != NULL)
4177  {
4178  db_private_free (thread_p, ftab_collector.partsect_ftab);
4179  }
4180  if (is_temp)
4181  {
4182  (void) logtb_set_check_interrupt (thread_p, save_check_interrupt);
4183  }
4184  return error_code;
4185 }

4187 /*
4188  * file_rv_destroy () - Recovery function used to destroy files.
4189  *
4190  * return : Error code.
4191  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
4192  * rcv (in) : Recovery data.
4193  *
4194  * NOTE: This can be used in one of two contexts:
4195  * 1. Logical undo of create file. Should be under a system operation that ends with commit and compensate.
4196  * 2. Run postpone for postponed file destroy. Again, this should be under a system operation, but it should end
4197  * with a commit and run postpone (of course).
4198  */
4199 int
4200 file_rv_destroy (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
4201 {
4202  VFID *vfid = (VFID *) rcv->data;
4203  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4204 
4205  assert (sizeof (*vfid) == rcv->length);
4206 
4207  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
4208 
4209  error_code = file_destroy (thread_p, vfid, false);
4210  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4211  {
4212  /* Not acceptable. */
4213  assert_release (false);
4214  return error_code;
4215  }
4216 
4217  return NO_ERROR;
4218 }
4219 
4220 /*
4221  * file_postpone_destroy () - Declare intention of destroying file. File will be destroyed on postpone phase, when the
4222  * transaction commit is confirmed. This is the usual (if not only) way of destroying
4223  * permanent files.
4224  *
4225  * return : Void
4226  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
4227  * vfid (in) : File identifier
4228  */
4229 void
4230 file_postpone_destroy (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid)
4231 {
4232  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
4233 
4234 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
4235  /* This should be used for permanent files! */
4236  {
4237  VPID vpid_fhead;
4238  PAGE_PTR page_fhead;
4239  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
4240 
4241  vpid_fhead.volid = vfid->volid;
4242  vpid_fhead.pageid = vfid->fileid;
4243  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
4244  if (page_fhead == NULL)
4245  {
4246  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4247  return;
4248  }
4249  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
4250  assert (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
4251  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_fhead);
4252  }
4253 #endif /* !NDEBUG */
4254 
4255  log_append_postpone (thread_p, RVFL_DESTROY, &addr, sizeof (*vfid), vfid);
4256 }

4258 /*
4259  * file_temp_retire () - retire temporary file (must not be preserved)
4260  *
4261  * return : error code
4262  * thread_p (in) : thread entry

4264  */
4265 int
4266 file_temp_retire (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid)
4267 {
4268  return file_temp_retire_internal (thread_p, vfid, false);
4269 }
4270 
4271 /*
4272  * file_temp_retire_preserved () - retire temporary file that was preserved
4273  *
4274  * return : error code
4275  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
4276  * vfid (in) : file identifier
4277  */
4278 int
4279 file_temp_retire_preserved (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid)
4280 {
4281  return file_temp_retire_internal (thread_p, vfid, true);
4282 }
4283 
4284 /*
4285  * file_temp_retire_internal () - retire temporary file. put it in cache is possible or destroy the file.
4286  *
4287  * return : error code
4288  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
4289  * vfid (in) : file identifier
4290  * was_preserved (in) : true if entry was preserved in session. it is important to know because we cannot find it in
4291  * transaction list.
4292  */
4293 STATIC_INLINE int
4294 file_temp_retire_internal (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, bool was_preserved)
4295 {
4296  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *entry = NULL;
4297  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4298 
4299  if (was_preserved)
4300  {
4301  file_tempcache_lock ();
4302  error_code = file_tempcache_alloc_entry (&entry);
4303  file_tempcache_unlock ();
4304  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4305  {
4306  assert (false);
4307  }
4308  if (entry != NULL)
4309  {
4310  entry->vfid = *vfid;
4311  /* type will be set later */
4312  }
4313  else
4314  {
4315  assert (false);
4316  }
4317  }
4318  else
4319  {
4320  entry = file_tempcache_pop_tran_file (thread_p, vfid);
4321  assert (entry != NULL);
4322  }
4323 
4324  if (entry != NULL && file_tempcache_put (thread_p, entry))
4325  {
4326  /* cached */
4327  return NO_ERROR;
4328  }
4329 
4330  /* was not cached. destroy */
4331  /* don't allow interrupt to avoid file leak */
4332  error_code = file_destroy (thread_p, vfid, true);
4333  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4334  {
4335  /* we should not have errors */
4336  assert_release (false);
4337  }
4338 
4339  if (entry != NULL)
4340  {
4341  file_tempcache_retire_entry (entry);
4342  }
4343  return error_code;
4344 }
4345 
4346 /*
4347  * file_rv_perm_expand_undo () - Undo permanent file expansion.
4348  *
4349  * return : NO_ERROR
4350  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
4351  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
4352  */
4353 int
4354 file_rv_perm_expand_undo (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
4355 {
4356  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = rcv->pgptr;
4357  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
4358  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *part_table;
4359  DKNSECTS save_nsects;
4360 
4361  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
4362  assert (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
4363 
4364  /* how is this done:
4365  * when the file was expanded, all newly reserved sectors have been added to partial table in file header, which was
4366  * empty before.
4367  * we will empty it back, and update statistics (sector count and free page count). */
4368 
4369  /* empty partial table */
4370  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, part_table);
4371  assert (file_extdata_item_count (part_table) == fhead->n_sector_partial);
4372  assert (VPID_ISNULL (&part_table->vpid_next));
4373  part_table->n_items = 0;
4374 
4375  /* update fhead */
4376  assert (fhead->n_page_free == fhead->n_sector_empty * DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES);
4377  fhead->n_page_total -= fhead->n_page_free;
4378  fhead->n_page_free = 0;
4379  fhead->n_sector_total -= fhead->n_sector_empty;
4380  save_nsects = fhead->n_sector_empty;
4381  fhead->n_sector_partial = 0;
4382  fhead->n_sector_empty = 0;
4383 
4384  file_log ("file_rv_perm_expand_undo",
4385  "removed expanded sectors from partial table and file header in file %d|%d, "
4386  "page header %d|%d, lsa %lld|%d, number of sectors %d \n"
4387  FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG, VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self),
4388  PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_fhead), save_nsects, FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead));
4389 
4390  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
4391 
4392  return NO_ERROR;
4393 }
4394 
4395 /*
4396  * file_rv_perm_expand_redo () - Redo permanent file expansion.
4397  *
4398  * return : Error code
4399  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
4400  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
4401  */
4402 int
4403 file_rv_perm_expand_redo (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
4404 {
4405  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = rcv->pgptr;
4406  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
4407  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_table;
4408  int count_vsids;
4409  VSID *vsids, *vsid_iter;
4410  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR partsect;
4411 
4412  /* how is this done:
4413  * file expansion means a number of sectors have been added to partial table in file header, which was empty before.
4414  * recovery data includes the sector ID's of all new sectors.
4415  * append empty sectors to partial table in file header. */
4416 
4417  vsids = (VSID *) rcv->data;
4418  count_vsids = rcv->length / sizeof (VSID);
4419  assert (count_vsids * (int) sizeof (VSID) == rcv->length);
4420 
4421  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
4422  assert (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
4423 
4424  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_table);
4425  assert (file_extdata_is_empty (extdata_part_table));
4426  /* bitmaps will be empty */
4427  partsect.page_bitmap = FILE_EMPTY_PAGE_BITMAP;
4428  for (vsid_iter = vsids; vsid_iter < vsids + count_vsids; vsid_iter++)
4429  {
4430  partsect.vsid = *vsid_iter;
4431  file_extdata_append (extdata_part_table, &partsect);
4432  }
4433 
4434  fhead->n_sector_total += count_vsids;
4435  assert (fhead->n_sector_empty == 0);
4436  fhead->n_sector_empty = count_vsids;
4437  assert (fhead->n_sector_partial == 0);
4438  fhead->n_sector_partial = count_vsids;
4439 
4440  assert (fhead->n_page_free == 0);
4441  fhead->n_page_free = count_vsids * DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES;
4442  fhead->n_page_total += fhead->n_page_free;
4443 
4444  file_log ("file_rv_perm_expand_redo",
4445  "recovery expand in file %d|%d, file header %d|%d, lsa %lld|%d \n"
4446  FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("partial table after"),
4447  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_fhead),
4448  FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_table));
4449 
4450  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
4451  return NO_ERROR;
4452 }
4453 
4454 /*
4455  * file_perm_expand () - Expand permanent file by reserving new sectors.
4456  *
4457  * return : Error code
4458  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
4459  * page_fhead (in) : File header page
4460  */
4461 static int
4462 file_perm_expand (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead)
4463 {
4464  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
4465  int expand_min_size_in_sectors;
4466  int expand_max_size_in_sectors;
4467  int expand_size_in_sectors;
4468  VSID *vsids_reserved = NULL;
4469  VSID *vsid_iter = NULL;
4470  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab;
4471  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR partsect;
4472  bool is_sysop_started = false;
4473  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
4474  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4475 
4476  /* caller should have started a system operation */
4477  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
4478 
4479  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
4480  assert (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
4481 
4482  /* compute desired expansion size. we should consider ratio, minimum size and maximum size. also, maximum size cannot
4483  * exceed the capacity of partial table in file header. we want to avoid the headache of allocating file table pages
4484  */
4485  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
4486  expand_min_size_in_sectors = MAX (fhead->tablespace.expand_min_size / DB_SECTORSIZE, 1);
4487  expand_max_size_in_sectors =
4488  MIN (fhead->tablespace.expand_max_size / DB_SECTORSIZE, file_extdata_remaining_capacity (extdata_part_ftab));
4489  assert (expand_min_size_in_sectors <= expand_max_size_in_sectors);
4490 
4491  expand_size_in_sectors = (int) ((float) fhead->n_sector_total * fhead->tablespace.expand_ratio);
4492  expand_size_in_sectors = MAX (expand_size_in_sectors, expand_min_size_in_sectors);
4493  expand_size_in_sectors = MIN (expand_size_in_sectors, expand_max_size_in_sectors);
4494 
4495  file_log ("file_perm_expand",
4496  "expand file %d|%d by %d sectors. \n" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG FILE_TABLESPACE_MSG,
4497  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), expand_size_in_sectors, FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead),
4498  FILE_TABLESPACE_AS_ARGS (&fhead->tablespace));
4499 
4500  /* allocate a buffer to hold the new sectors */
4501  vsids_reserved = (VSID *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, expand_size_in_sectors * sizeof (VSID));
4502  if (vsids_reserved == NULL)
4503  {
4504  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, expand_size_in_sectors * sizeof (VSID));
4505  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
4506  }
4507 
4508  /* before we start, we need to open a new system operation that gets committed. it is hard to undo file expansion,
4509  * because we would have to search for each VSID we added individually. moreover, it is very likely to need to expand
4510  * the file again. therefore, we should make the expansion permanent. */
4511  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
4512  is_sysop_started = true;
4513 
4514  /* reserve disk sectors */
4515  error_code =
4516  disk_reserve_sectors (thread_p, DB_PERMANENT_DATA_PURPOSE, fhead->volid_last_expand, expand_size_in_sectors,
4517  vsids_reserved);
4518  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4519  {
4520  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4521  goto exit;
4522  }
4523 
4524  /* sort VSID's. */
4525  qsort (vsids_reserved, expand_size_in_sectors, sizeof (VSID), disk_compare_vsids);
4526 
4527  /* save in file header partial table. all sectors will be empty */
4528  partsect.page_bitmap = FILE_EMPTY_PAGE_BITMAP;
4529  for (vsid_iter = vsids_reserved; vsid_iter < vsids_reserved + expand_size_in_sectors; vsid_iter++)
4530  {
4531  partsect.vsid = *vsid_iter;
4532  file_extdata_append (extdata_part_ftab, &partsect);
4533  }
4534 
4535  /* update header stats */
4536  fhead->n_sector_total += expand_size_in_sectors;
4537  assert (fhead->n_sector_empty == 0);
4538  fhead->n_sector_empty = expand_size_in_sectors;
4539  assert (fhead->n_sector_partial == 0);
4540  fhead->n_sector_partial = expand_size_in_sectors;
4541 
4542  assert (fhead->n_page_free == 0);
4543  fhead->n_page_free = expand_size_in_sectors * DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES;
4544  fhead->n_page_total += fhead->n_page_free;
4545 
4546  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
4547 
4548  /* file extended successfully. log the change. */
4549  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVFL_EXPAND, NULL, page_fhead, 0, 0,
4550  expand_size_in_sectors * sizeof (VSID), NULL, vsids_reserved);
4551 
4552  file_log ("file_perm_expand",
4553  "expand file %d|%d, page header %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d; "
4554  "first sector %d|%d \n" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("partial table"),
4555  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_lsa),
4556  VSID_AS_ARGS (vsids_reserved), FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_ftab));
4557 
4558  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
4559 
4560 exit:
4561  if (is_sysop_started)
4562  {
4563  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4564  {
4565  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
4566  }
4567  else
4568  {
4569  log_sysop_commit (thread_p);
4570  }
4571  }
4572  if (vsids_reserved != NULL)
4573  {
4574  db_private_free (thread_p, vsids_reserved);
4575  }
4576  return error_code;
4577 }
4578 
4579 /*
4580  * file_table_move_partial_sectors_to_header () - Move partial sectors from first page of partial table to header
4581  * section of partial table
4582  *
4583  * return : error code
4584  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
4585  * page_fhead (in) : file header page
4586  * alloc_type (in) : page allocation type
4587  * vpid_alloc_out (out) : output VPID of page removed from partial table and reused for new allocation
4588  */
4589 static int
4590 file_table_move_partial_sectors_to_header (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TYPE alloc_type,
4591  VPID * vpid_alloc_out)
4592 {
4593  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
4594  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab_head = NULL;
4595  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab_first = NULL;
4596  PAGE_PTR page_part_ftab_first = NULL;
4597  int n_items_to_move;
4598  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
4599  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4600 
4601  /* how it works:
4602  * when we have an empty section in header partial table, but we still have partial sectors in other pages, we move
4603  * some or all partial sectors in first page (all are moved if they fit header section).
4604  *
4605  * if all partial sectors in first page have been moved, then first page is removed from partial table. we used to
4606  * deallocate the page, but to solve some strange corner cases (see CBRD-21242), it proved more convenient to reuse
4607  * the page.
4608  */
4609 
4610  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
4611  assert (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
4612 
4613  /* Caller should have checked */
4614  assert (fhead->n_sector_partial > 0);
4615 
4616  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab_head);
4617  if (VPID_ISNULL (&extdata_part_ftab_head->vpid_next))
4618  {
4619  /* caller should have checked and we should not be here */
4620  assert (false);
4621  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4622  goto exit;
4623  }
4624 
4625  /* get first page of partial table */
4626  page_part_ftab_first =
4627  pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &extdata_part_ftab_head->vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
4628  if (page_part_ftab_first == NULL)
4629  {
4630  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
4631  goto exit;
4632  }
4633 
4634  /* get partial table extensible data in first page and let's see how many items we can move */
4635  extdata_part_ftab_first = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_part_ftab_first;
4636 
4637  file_log ("file_table_move_partial_sectors_to_header",
4638  "file %d|%d \n" FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("header (destination)")
4639  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("first page (source)"),
4640  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self),
4641  FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_ftab_head), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_ftab_first));
4642 
4643  n_items_to_move = file_extdata_item_count (extdata_part_ftab_first);
4644  if (n_items_to_move == 0)
4645  {
4646  /* not expected. */
4647  assert_release (false);
4648  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4649  goto exit;
4650  }
4651 
4652  /* get partial table extensible data in header page */
4653  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab_head);
4654  if (!file_extdata_is_empty (extdata_part_ftab_head))
4655  {
4656  /* we shouldn't be here. release version will still work. */
4657  assert (false);
4658  goto exit;
4659  }
4660  /* we cannot move more than the capacity of extensible data in header page */
4661  n_items_to_move = MIN (n_items_to_move, file_extdata_remaining_capacity (extdata_part_ftab_head));
4662 
4663  /* copy items to header section */
4664  file_extdata_append_array (extdata_part_ftab_head,
4665  file_extdata_start (extdata_part_ftab_first), (INT16) n_items_to_move);
4666  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
4667  /* log changes to extensible data in header page */
4668  file_log_extdata_add (thread_p, extdata_part_ftab_head, page_fhead, 0,
4669  n_items_to_move, file_extdata_start (extdata_part_ftab_first));
4670 
4671  file_log ("file_table_move_partial_sectors_to_header",
4672  "moved %d items from first page to header page file table. \n"
4673  "file %d|%d, header page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d \n"
4674  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("header partial table"), n_items_to_move,
4675  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_lsa),
4676  FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_ftab_head));
4677 
4678  /* now remove from first page. if all items have been moved, we can deallocate first page. */
4679  if (n_items_to_move < file_extdata_item_count (extdata_part_ftab_first))
4680  {
4681  /* Remove copied entries. */
4682  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_part_ftab_first);
4683  file_log_extdata_remove (thread_p, extdata_part_ftab_first, page_part_ftab_first, 0, n_items_to_move);
4684  file_extdata_remove_at (extdata_part_ftab_first, 0, n_items_to_move);
4685 
4686  file_log ("file_table_move_partial_sectors_to_header",
4687  "removed %d items from first page partial table \n"
4688  "file %d|%d, page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d \n"
4689  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("first page partial table"),
4690  n_items_to_move, VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_part_ftab_first, &save_lsa),
4691  FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_ftab_first));
4692  }
4693  else
4694  {
4695  /* we can remove first page. but do not deallocate it completely. this is called in the context of
4696  * file_perm_alloc, so we can just use this page. output its VPID and file_perm_alloc will know what to do. */
4697  VPID save_next = extdata_part_ftab_head->vpid_next;
4698  file_log_extdata_set_next (thread_p, extdata_part_ftab_head, page_fhead, &extdata_part_ftab_first->vpid_next);
4699  VPID_COPY (&extdata_part_ftab_head->vpid_next, &extdata_part_ftab_first->vpid_next);
4700 
4701  file_log ("file_table_move_partial_sectors_to_header",
4702  "remove first partial table page %d|%d\n", VPID_AS_ARGS (&save_next));
4703 
4704  *vpid_alloc_out = save_next;
4705  /* callers usually expect a "deallocated" page. we need to simulate that.
4706  * note that maybe we can do without really deallocating. a page type update would be enough. this is however the
4707  * safest way to do it, even though not optimal. the case will not affect performance in any benchmark or
4708  * production scenario anyway. */
4709  pgbuf_dealloc_page (thread_p, page_part_ftab_first);
4710  page_part_ftab_first = NULL;
4711 
4712  if (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE_FULL_SECTOR)
4713  {
4714  /* special case: file_perm_alloc also initializes & appends the new full table page. */
4715  error_code = file_table_append_full_sector_page (thread_p, page_fhead, vpid_alloc_out);
4716  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4717  {
4718  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4719  VPID_SET_NULL (vpid_alloc_out);
4720  goto exit;
4721  }
4722  }
4723  else if (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE)
4724  {
4725  /* we need to update header statistics regarding numbers of table and user pages */
4726  fhead->n_page_ftab--;
4727  fhead->n_page_user++;
4728 
4729  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVFL_FHEAD_CONVERT_FTAB_TO_USER, NULL, page_fhead, NULL_OFFSET, 0, 0,
4730  NULL, NULL);
4731  }
4732  }
4733 
4734  /* done */
4735 
4736 exit:
4737  if (page_part_ftab_first != NULL)
4738  {
4739  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_part_ftab_first);
4740  }
4741 
4742  return error_code;
4743 }
4744 
4745 /*
4746  * file_rv_fhead_convert_ftab_to_user_page () - recovery update header when converting a table page to user page
4747  *
4748  * return : NO_ERROR
4749  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
4750  * rcv (in) : recovery data
4751  */
4752 int
4753 file_rv_fhead_convert_ftab_to_user_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
4754 {
4755  FILE_HEADER *fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) rcv->pgptr;
4756 
4757  fhead->n_page_ftab--;
4758  fhead->n_page_user++;
4759 
4760  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, rcv->pgptr, DONT_FREE);
4761 
4762  return NO_ERROR;
4763 }
4764 
4765 /*
4766  * file_rv_fhead_convert_user_to_ftab_page () - recovery update header when converting a user page to table page
4767  *
4768  * return : NO_ERROR
4769  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
4770  * rcv (in) : recovery data
4771  */
4772 int
4773 file_rv_fhead_convert_user_to_ftab_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
4774 {
4775  FILE_HEADER *fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) rcv->pgptr;
4776 
4777  fhead->n_page_ftab++;
4778  fhead->n_page_user--;
4779 
4780  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, rcv->pgptr, DONT_FREE);
4781 
4782  return NO_ERROR;
4783 }
4784 
4785 /*
4786  * file_table_append_full_sector_page () - append a new page to full sectors table
4787  *
4788  * return : error code
4789  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
4790  * page_fhead (in) : page file header
4791  * vpid_new (in) : new page VPID
4792  */
4793 static int
4794 file_table_append_full_sector_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, const VPID * vpid_new)
4795 {
4796  /* add newly allocated page to full table extdata; this page was requested while adding a new full sector */
4797  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
4798  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_new_ftab = NULL;
4799  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_full_ftab = NULL;
4800  FILE_HEADER *fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
4801 
4802  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4803 
4804  /* small optimization: insert the page at the beginning of the list; it will be easier to access
4805  * when adding the following new full sectors;
4806  * extdata_new_ftab->vpid_next = extdata_full_ftab->vpid_next; extdata_full_ftab->vpid_next = new_vpid;
4807  */
4808  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_full_ftab);
4809 
4810  /* fix new table page */
4811  page_ftab = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, vpid_new, NEW_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
4812  if (page_ftab == NULL)
4813  {
4814  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
4815  return error_code;
4816  }
4817  pgbuf_set_page_ptype (thread_p, page_ftab, PAGE_FTAB);
4818 
4819  /* init new table extensible data */
4820  extdata_new_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
4821  file_extdata_init (sizeof (VSID), DB_PAGESIZE, extdata_new_ftab);
4822  VPID_COPY (&extdata_new_ftab->vpid_next, &extdata_full_ftab->vpid_next);
4823 
4824  pgbuf_log_new_page (thread_p, page_ftab, file_extdata_size (extdata_new_ftab), PAGE_FTAB);
4825  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
4826 
4827  /* Log and link the page in previous table. */
4828  file_log_extdata_set_next (thread_p, extdata_full_ftab, page_fhead, vpid_new);
4829  VPID_COPY (&extdata_full_ftab->vpid_next, vpid_new);
4830 
4831  file_log ("file_table_append_full_sector_page", "%s", "page has been added to full sectors table \n");
4832  return NO_ERROR;
4833 }
4834 
4835 /*
4836  * file_table_add_full_sector () - Add a new sector to full table
4837  *
4838  * return : Error code
4839  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
4840  * page_fhead (in) : File header page
4841  * vsid (in) : Sector ID
4842  */
4843 static int
4844 file_table_add_full_sector (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, const VSID * vsid)
4845 {
4846  bool found = false;
4847  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
4848  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
4849  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_full_ftab;
4850  PAGE_PTR page_extdata = NULL;
4851  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
4852  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4853  int pos = -1;
4854 
4855  /* how it works:
4856  * add VSID to full table. first we try to find free space in the existing extensible data components. if there is no
4857  * free space, we allocate a new table page and append it to full table.
4858  *
4859  * note: temporary files does not keep a full table. temporary files only keep partial table (and full sectors are
4860  * never moved)
4861  * note: this must be called in the context of a page allocation and should be under a system operation
4862  */
4863 
4864  assert (page_fhead != NULL);
4865  assert (vsid != NULL);
4866  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
4867 
4868  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
4869  assert (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
4870 
4871  /* get full table in file header */
4872  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_full_ftab);
4873  /* search for full table component with free space */
4874  error_code = file_extdata_find_not_full (thread_p, &extdata_full_ftab, &page_ftab, &found);
4875  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4876  {
4877  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4878  goto exit;
4879  }
4880 
4881  if (!found)
4882  {
4883  /* no free space. add a new page to full table. */
4884  VPID vpid_ftab_new = VPID_INITIALIZER;
4885 
4886  /* unfix the last page that remained fixed from file_extdata_find_not_null */
4887  if (page_ftab != NULL)
4888  {
4889  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
4890  }
4891 
4892  error_code = file_perm_alloc (thread_p, page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE_FULL_SECTOR, &vpid_ftab_new);
4893  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
4894  {
4895  ASSERT_ERROR ();
4896  goto exit;
4897  }
4898  assert (!VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_ftab_new));
4899 
4900  /* fix newly allocated table page. note that this is an old page, file_perm_alloc already initialized it. */
4901  page_ftab = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_ftab_new, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
4902  if (page_ftab == NULL)
4903  {
4904  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
4905  goto exit;
4906  }
4907 
4908  /* the new full table component is used */
4909  extdata_full_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
4910  }
4911 
4912  page_extdata = page_ftab != NULL ? page_ftab : page_fhead;
4913 
4914  /* add the new VSID to full table. note that we keep sectors ordered. */
4915  file_extdata_find_ordered (extdata_full_ftab, vsid, disk_compare_vsids, &found, &pos);
4916  if (found)
4917  {
4918  /* ups, duplicate! */
4919  assert_release (false);
4920  error_code = ER_FAILED;
4921  goto exit;
4922  }
4923  file_extdata_insert_at (extdata_full_ftab, pos, 1, vsid);
4924 
4925  /* log the change. */
4926  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_extdata);
4927  file_log_extdata_add (thread_p, extdata_full_ftab, page_extdata, pos, 1, vsid);
4928 
4929  file_log ("file_table_add_full_sector",
4930  "add sector %d|%d at position %d in file %d|%d, full table page %d|%d, "
4931  "prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d, \n"
4932  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("full table component"),
4933  VSID_AS_ARGS (vsid), pos, VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_extdata, &save_lsa),
4934  FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_full_ftab));
4935 
4936  /* done */
4937  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
4938 
4939 exit:
4940  if (page_ftab != NULL)
4941  {
4942  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab);
4943  }
4944  return error_code;
4945 }
4946 
4947 /*
4948  * file_rv_dump_vfid_and_vpid () - Dump recovery data when VFID and VPID are logged (used for several cases).
4949  *
4950  * return : Void
4951  * fp (in) : Dump output
4952  * length (in) : Recovery data length
4953  * data (in) : Recovery data
4954  */
4955 void
4956 file_rv_dump_vfid_and_vpid (FILE * fp, int length, void *data)
4957 {
4958  VFID *vfid = NULL;
4959  VPID *vpid = NULL;
4960  char *rcv_data = (char *) data;
4961  int offset = 0;
4962 
4963  vfid = (VFID *) (rcv_data + offset);
4964  offset += sizeof (*vfid);
4965 
4966  vpid = (VPID *) (rcv_data + offset);
4967  offset += sizeof (*vpid);
4968 
4969  assert (offset == length);
4970 
4971  fprintf (fp, "VFID = %d|%d \nVPID = %d|%d.\n", VFID_AS_ARGS (vfid), VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid));
4972 }
4973 
4974 /*
4975  * file_perm_alloc () - Allocate a new page in permament file.
4976  *
4977  * return : Error code
4978  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
4979  * page_fhead (in) : File header page
4980  * alloc_type (in) : User/table page
4981  * vpid_alloc_out (out) : VPID of allocated page
4982  */
4983 static int
4984 file_perm_alloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TYPE alloc_type, VPID * vpid_alloc_out)
4985 {
4986  FILE_HEADER *fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
4987  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab = NULL;
4988  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *partsect;
4989  int offset_to_alloc_bit;
4990  bool was_empty = false;
4991  bool is_full = false;
4992  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
4993  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
4994 
4995  /* how it works:
4996  * the file header (without considering numerable files) is split into two tables: partial table and full table.
4997  * to allocate new pages, the full is not interesting. to do a very fast allocation, we just pick a page in the first
4998  * partial sector.
4999  *
5000  * if there is no partial sector (all sectors are full), we need to expand the file (by calling file_perm_expand).
5001  * new sectors are reserved and we can pick a page from these sectors.
5002  *
5003  * if the partial sector becomes full, we must move it to full table.
5004  *
5005  * note: this is not for temporary files. temporary file allocation is different.
5006  * note: this does not handle user page table for numerable files.
5007  * note: this should always be called under a system operation. the system operation should always be committed before
5008  * file header page is unfixed.
5009  *
5010  * todo: we might consider to do lazy moves to full table. rather than moving the full sector immediately, we let it
5011  * in partial table until something happens (e.g. the section of partial table in file header becomes entirely
5012  * full).
5013  */
5014 
5015  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
5016  assert (page_fhead != NULL);
5017 
5018  file_log ("file_perm_alloc", "%s", FILE_ALLOC_TYPE_STRING (alloc_type));
5019 
5020  if (fhead->n_page_free == 0)
5021  {
5022  /* no free pages. we need to expand file. */
5023  error_code = file_perm_expand (thread_p, page_fhead);
5024  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5025  {
5026  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5027  goto exit;
5028  }
5029  }
5030  assert (fhead->n_page_free > 0);
5031  assert (fhead->n_sector_partial > 0);
5032 
5033  /* get partial table in file header */
5034  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
5035  if (file_extdata_is_empty (extdata_part_ftab))
5036  {
5037  /* we know we have free pages, so we should have partial sectors in other table pages */
5038  error_code = file_table_move_partial_sectors_to_header (thread_p, page_fhead, alloc_type, vpid_alloc_out);
5039  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5040  {
5041  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5042  goto exit;
5043  }
5044  if (!VPID_ISNULL (vpid_alloc_out))
5045  {
5046  /* table page has been reused. */
5047  goto exit;
5048  }
5049  }
5050 
5051  /* we must have partial sectors in header! */
5052  assert (!file_extdata_is_empty (extdata_part_ftab));
5053 
5054  /* allocate a new page in first partial sector */
5055  partsect = (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) file_extdata_start (extdata_part_ftab);
5056 
5057  /* should not be full */
5058  assert (!file_partsect_is_full (partsect));
5059 
5060  /* was partial sector actually empty? we keep this as a statistic for now */
5061  was_empty = file_partsect_is_empty (partsect);
5062 
5063  /* allocate a page in this partial sector */
5064  if (!file_partsect_alloc (partsect, vpid_alloc_out, &offset_to_alloc_bit))
5065  {
5066  /* should not happen, this is a logic error. */
5067  assert_release (false);
5068  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5069  goto exit;
5070  }
5071 
5072  assert (file_partsect_is_bit_set (partsect, offset_to_alloc_bit));
5073  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
5074 
5075  /* log allocation */
5076  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVFL_PARTSECT_ALLOC, NULL, page_fhead,
5077  (PGLENGTH) ((char *) partsect - page_fhead),
5078  sizeof (offset_to_alloc_bit), sizeof (offset_to_alloc_bit),
5079  &offset_to_alloc_bit, &offset_to_alloc_bit);
5080 
5081  file_log ("file_perm_alloc",
5082  "allocated page %d|%d in file %d|%d page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d, "
5083  "set bit at offset %d in partial sector at offset %d \n"
5084  FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("partsect after"),
5085  VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_alloc_out), VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self),
5086  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_lsa), offset_to_alloc_bit,
5087  (PGLENGTH) ((char *) partsect - page_fhead), FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (partsect));
5088 
5089  if (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE_FULL_SECTOR)
5090  {
5091  /* we need to add append page before we have to move yet another sector to full. otherwise we'll loop here. */
5092  error_code = file_table_append_full_sector_page (thread_p, page_fhead, vpid_alloc_out);
5093  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5094  {
5095  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5096  goto exit;
5097  }
5098  }
5099 
5100  is_full = file_partsect_is_full (partsect);
5101 
5102  /* update header statistics */
5103  file_header_alloc (fhead, alloc_type, was_empty, is_full);
5104  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
5105  file_log_fhead_alloc (thread_p, page_fhead, alloc_type, was_empty, is_full);
5106 
5107  file_log ("file_perm_alloc",
5108  "update header in file %d|%d, header page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d, "
5109  "after %s, was_empty = %s, is_full = %s, \n" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG,
5110  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_lsa),
5111  FILE_ALLOC_TYPE_STRING (alloc_type), was_empty ? "true" : "false",
5112  is_full ? "true" : "false", FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead));
5113 
5114  /* we need to first update header and then move full partial sector to full table. we might need a new page and we
5115  * must know if no free pages are available to expand the file */
5116  if (is_full)
5117  {
5118  /* move to full table. */
5119  VSID vsid_full;
5120 
5121  assert (file_partsect_is_full (partsect));
5122 
5123  /* save VSID before removing from partial table */
5124  vsid_full = partsect->vsid;
5125 
5126  /* remove from partial table first. adding to full table may need a new page and it expects to find one in first
5127  * partial sector. */
5128  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
5129  file_log_extdata_remove (thread_p, extdata_part_ftab, page_fhead, 0, 1);
5130  file_extdata_remove_at (extdata_part_ftab, 0, 1);
5131 
5132  file_log ("file_perm_alloc",
5133  "removed full partial sector from position 0 in file %d|%d, header page %d|%d, "
5134  "prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d, \n"
5135  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("partial table after alloc"),
5136  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_lsa),
5137  FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_ftab));
5138 
5139  /* add to full table */
5140  error_code = file_table_add_full_sector (thread_p, page_fhead, &vsid_full);
5141  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5142  {
5143  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5144  goto exit;
5145  }
5146  }
5147 
5148  /* done */
5149 
5150  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
5151 
5152 exit:
5153  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_FILE_NUM_PAGE_ALLOCS);
5154 
5155  return error_code;
5156 }
5157 
5158 /*
5159  * file_init_page_type () - initialize new permanent page by setting its type
5160  *
5161  * return : NO_ERROR
5162  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
5163  * page (in) : new page
5164  * args (in) : PAGE_TYPE *
5165  */
5166 int
5167 file_init_page_type (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page, void *args)
5168 {
5169  PAGE_TYPE ptype = *(PAGE_TYPE *) args;
5170 
5171  return file_init_page_type_internal (thread_p, page, ptype, false);
5172 }
5173 
5174 /*
5175  * file_init_temp_page_type () - initialize new temporary page by setting its type
5176  *
5177  * return : NO_ERROR
5178  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
5179  * page (in) : new page
5180  * args (in) : PAGE_TYPE *
5181  */
5182 int
5183 file_init_temp_page_type (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page, void *args)
5184 {
5185  PAGE_TYPE ptype = *(PAGE_TYPE *) args;
5186 
5187  return file_init_page_type_internal (thread_p, page, ptype, true);
5188 }
5189 
5190 /*
5191  * file_init_page_type_internal () - initialize new page by setting its type
5192  *
5193  * return : NO_ERROR
5194  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
5195  * page (in) : new page
5196  * ptype (in) : page type
5197  * is_temp (in) : true if temporary page, false if permanent
5198  */
5199 STATIC_INLINE int
5200 file_init_page_type_internal (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page, PAGE_TYPE ptype, bool is_temp)
5201 {
5202  pgbuf_set_page_ptype (thread_p, page, ptype);
5203  if (!is_temp)
5204  {
5205  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVPGBUF_NEW_PAGE, NULL, page, (PGLENGTH) ptype, 0, 0, NULL, NULL);
5206  }
5207  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page, DONT_FREE);
5208  return NO_ERROR;
5209 }
5210 
5211 /*
5212  * file_alloc () - Allocate an user page for file.
5213  *
5214  * return : Error code
5215  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
5216  * vfid (in) : File identifier
5217  * f_init (in) : init page function (must not be NULL for permanent page allocation)
5218  * f_init_args (in) : arguments for init page function
5219  * vpid_out (out) : VPID of page.
5220  * page_out (out) : if not null, it will output newly allocated page.
5221  */
5222 int
5223 file_alloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, FILE_INIT_PAGE_FUNC f_init, void *f_init_args, VPID * vpid_out,
5224  PAGE_PTR * page_out)
5225 {
5226 #define UNDO_DATA_SIZE (sizeof (VFID) + sizeof (VPID))
5227  VPID vpid_fhead;
5228  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
5229  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
5230  bool is_sysop_started = false;
5231  char undo_log_data_buf[UNDO_DATA_SIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT];
5232  char *undo_log_data = PTR_ALIGN (undo_log_data_buf, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
5233  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
5234 
5235  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
5236  assert (vpid_out != NULL);
5237 
5238  VPID_SET_NULL (vpid_out);
5239  if (page_out != NULL)
5240  {
5241  *page_out = NULL;
5242  }
5243 
5244  /* fix header */
5245  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
5246  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
5247  if (page_fhead == NULL)
5248  {
5249  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5250  return error_code;
5251  }
5252 
5253  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
5254  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
5255 
5256  file_log ("file_alloc", "allocate new %s page. \n" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG,
5257  FILE_PERM_TEMP_STRING (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead)), FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead));
5258 
5259  if (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
5260  {
5261  /* allocate page */
5262  error_code = file_temp_alloc (thread_p, page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE, vpid_out);
5263  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5264  {
5265  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5266  goto exit;
5267  }
5268  }
5269  else
5270  {
5271  /* start a nested system operation. we will end it with commit & undo. this must be atomic. */
5272  log_sysop_start_atomic (thread_p);
5273  is_sysop_started = true;
5274 
5275  /* allocate page */
5276  error_code = file_perm_alloc (thread_p, page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE, vpid_out);
5277  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5278  {
5279  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5280  goto exit;
5281  }
5282 
5283  /* make undo data for system op commit */
5284  VFID_COPY ((VFID *) undo_log_data, vfid);
5285  VPID_COPY ((VPID *) (undo_log_data + sizeof (VFID)), vpid_out);
5286  }
5287 
5288  assert (!VPID_ISNULL (vpid_out));
5289 
5290  if (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead))
5291  {
5292  /* we also have to add page to user page table */
5293  error_code = file_numerable_add_page (thread_p, page_fhead, vpid_out);
5294  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5295  {
5296  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5297  goto exit;
5298  }
5299  }
5300 
5301  if (f_init)
5302  {
5303  /* initialize page */
5304  PAGE_PTR page_alloc = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, vpid_out, NEW_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
5305  if (page_alloc == NULL)
5306  {
5307  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5308  goto exit;
5309  }
5310  error_code = f_init (thread_p, page_alloc, f_init_args);
5311  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5312  {
5313  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5314  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_alloc);
5315  goto exit;
5316  }
5317  if (page_out != NULL)
5318  {
5319  *page_out = page_alloc;
5320  }
5321  else
5322  {
5323  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_alloc);
5324  }
5325  }
5326  else
5327  {
5328  assert (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
5329  if (page_out != NULL)
5330  {
5331  *page_out = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, vpid_out, NEW_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
5332  if (*page_out == NULL)
5333  {
5334  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5335  goto exit;
5336  }
5337  }
5338  }
5339 
5340  /* done */
5341  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
5342 
5343 exit:
5344  if (is_sysop_started)
5345  {
5346  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5347  {
5348  /* abort system operation. */
5349  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
5350  }
5351  else
5352  {
5353  /* commit and undo (to deallocate) */
5354  log_sysop_end_logical_undo (thread_p, RVFL_ALLOC, NULL, UNDO_DATA_SIZE, undo_log_data);
5355  }
5356  }
5357 
5358  /* allocation should be completed; check header */
5359  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
5360 
5361  if (error_code != NO_ERROR && page_out != NULL && *page_out != NULL)
5362  {
5363  /* don't leak page. */
5364  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, *page_out);
5365  }
5366 
5367  if (page_fhead != NULL)
5368  {
5369  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_fhead);
5370  }
5371 
5372  return error_code;
5373 #undef UNDO_DATA_SIZE
5374 }
5375 
5376 /*
5377  * file_alloc_multiple () - Allocate multiple pages at once.
5378  *
5379  * return : Error code.
5380  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry.
5381  * vfid (in) : File identifier.
5382  * f_init (in) : New page init function.
5383  * f_init_args (in) : Arguments for init function.
5384  * npages (in) : Number of pages to allocate.
5385  * vpids_out (out) : VPIDS for allocated pages.
5386  */
5387 int
