5388 file_alloc_multiple (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid,
5389  FILE_INIT_PAGE_FUNC f_init, void *f_init_args, int npages, VPID * vpids_out)
5390 {
5391  VPID *vpid_iter;
5392  VPID local_vpid = VPID_INITIALIZER;
5393  int iter;
5394  VPID vpid_fhead;
5395  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
5396  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
5397  bool is_temp;
5398  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
5399 
5400  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
5401  assert (npages >= 1);
5402 
5403  /* fix header */
5404  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
5405  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
5406  if (page_fhead == NULL)
5407  {
5408  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5409  return error_code;
5410  }
5411 
5412  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
5413  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
5414  /* keep header while allocating all pages. we have a great chance to allocate all pages in the same sectors */
5415 
5416  is_temp = FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead);
5417  if (!is_temp)
5418  {
5419  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
5420 
5421  /* start a system op. we may abort page allocations if an error occurs. */
5422  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
5423  }
5424 
5425  /* do not leak pages! if not numerable, it should use all allocated VPIDS */
5426  assert (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead) || vpids_out != NULL);
5427 
5428  for (iter = 0; iter < npages; iter++)
5429  {
5430  vpid_iter = vpids_out ? vpids_out + iter : &local_vpid;
5431  error_code = file_alloc (thread_p, vfid, f_init, f_init_args, vpid_iter, NULL);
5432  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5433  {
5434  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5435  goto exit;
5436  }
5437  }
5438  /* done */
5439  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
5440 
5441 exit:
5442  if (!is_temp)
5443  {
5444  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
5445  if (error_code == NO_ERROR)
5446  {
5447  /* caller will decide what happens with allocated pages */
5448  log_sysop_attach_to_outer (thread_p);
5449  }
5450  else
5451  {
5452  /* undo allocations */
5453  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
5454  }
5455  }
5456 
5457  if (page_fhead != NULL)
5458  {
5459  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
5460  }
5461 
5462  return error_code;
5463 }
5464 
5465 /*
5466  * file_alloc_sticky_first_page () - Allocate first file page and make it sticky. It is usually used as special headers
5467  * and should never be deallocated.
5468  *
5469  * return : Error code
5470  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
5471  * vfid (in) : File identifier
5472  * f_init (in) : init page function (must not be NULL for permanent page allocation)
5473  * f_init_args (in) : arguments for init page function
5474  * vpid_out (out) : Allocated page VPID
5475  * page_out (out) : if not null, it will output newly allocated page.
5476  */
5477 int
5478 file_alloc_sticky_first_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, FILE_INIT_PAGE_FUNC f_init, void *f_init_args,
5479  VPID * vpid_out, PAGE_PTR * page_out)
5480 {
5481  VPID vpid_fhead;
5482  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
5483  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
5484  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
5485  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
5486 
5487  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
5488  assert (vpid_out != NULL);
5489 
5490  VPID_SET_NULL (vpid_out);
5491  if (page_out != NULL)
5492  {
5493  *page_out = NULL;
5494  }
5495 
5496  /* fix header */
5497  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
5498  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
5499  if (page_fhead == NULL)
5500  {
5501  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5502  return error_code;
5503  }
5504 
5505  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
5506  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
5507 
5508  assert (fhead->n_page_user == 0);
5509  assert (VPID_ISNULL (&fhead->vpid_sticky_first));
5510 
5511  error_code = file_alloc (thread_p, vfid, f_init, f_init_args, vpid_out, page_out);
5512  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5513  {
5514  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5515  goto exit;
5516  }
5517 
5518  /* save VPID */
5519  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
5520  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVFL_FHEAD_STICKY_PAGE, NULL,
5521  page_fhead, 0, sizeof (VPID), sizeof (VPID), &fhead->vpid_sticky_first, vpid_out);
5522  fhead->vpid_sticky_first = *vpid_out;
5523  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
5524 
5525  /* done */
5526  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
5527  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
5528 
5529  file_log ("file_alloc_sticky_first_page",
5530  "set vpid_sticky_first to %d|%d in file %d|%d, header page %d|%d, "
5531  "prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d", VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_out),
5532  VFID_AS_ARGS (vfid), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_lsa));
5533 
5534 exit:
5535  if (page_fhead != NULL)
5536  {
5537  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
5538  }
5539  return error_code;
5540 }
5541 
5542 /*
5543  * file_rv_fhead_sticky_page () - Recovery sticky page VPID in file header.
5544  *
5545  * return : NO_ERROR
5546  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
5547  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
5548  */
5549 int
5550 file_rv_fhead_sticky_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
5551 {
5552  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = rcv->pgptr;
5553  FILE_HEADER *fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
5554  VPID *vpid = (VPID *) rcv->data;
5555 
5556  assert (rcv->length == sizeof (*vpid));
5557 
5558  fhead->vpid_sticky_first = *vpid;
5559  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
5560 
5561  file_log ("file_rv_fhead_sticky_page",
5562  "set vpid_sticky_first to %d|%d in file %d|%d, header page %d|%d, lsa %lld|%d",
5563  VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid), VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_fhead));
5564  return NO_ERROR;
5565 }
5566 
5567 /*
5568  * file_get_sticky_first_page () - Get VPID of first page. It should be a sticky page.
5569  *
5570  * return : Error code
5571  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
5572  * vfid (in) : File identifier
5573  * vpid_out (out) : VPID of sticky first page
5574  */
5575 int
5576 file_get_sticky_first_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, VPID * vpid_out)
5577 {
5578  VPID vpid_fhead;
5579  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
5580  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
5581  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
5582 
5583  /* fix header */
5584  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
5585  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
5586  if (page_fhead == NULL)
5587  {
5588  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5589  return error_code;
5590  }
5591 
5592  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
5593  if (LOG_ISRESTARTED ())
5594  {
5595  /* sometimes called before recovery... we cannot guarantee the header is sane at this point. */
5596  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
5597  }
5598 
5599  *vpid_out = fhead->vpid_sticky_first;
5600  if (VPID_ISNULL (vpid_out))
5601  {
5602  assert_release (false);
5603  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
5604  return ER_FAILED;
5605  }
5606 
5607  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
5608  return NO_ERROR;
5609 }
5610 
5611 /*
5612  * file_dealloc () - Deallocate a file page.
5613  *
5614  * return : Error code
5615  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
5616  * vfid (in) : File identifier
5617  * vpid (in) : Page identifier
5618  * file_type_hint (in) : Hint for file type. Usually caller knows exactly what kind of file he deallocates the page
5619  * from. Since deallocate is different based on page type (permanent/temporary, numerable),
5620  * and we don't always have to fix header page, it is good to tell dealloc what to do from the
5621  * start.
5622  */
5623 int
5624 file_dealloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, const VPID * vpid, FILE_TYPE file_type_hint)
5625 {
5626 #define LOG_DATA_SIZE (sizeof (VFID) + sizeof (VPID))
5627  VPID vpid_fhead;
5628  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
5629  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
5630  char log_data_buffer[LOG_DATA_SIZE + MAX_ALIGNMENT];
5631  char *log_data = PTR_ALIGN (log_data_buffer, MAX_ALIGNMENT);
5632  LOG_DATA_ADDR log_addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
5633  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_user_page_ftab = NULL;
5634  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
5635  PAGE_PTR page_extdata = NULL;
5636  bool found = false;
5637  int pos = -1;
5638  VPID *vpid_found;
5639  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
5640  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
5641 
5642  /* how it works:
5643  *
5644  * permanent files: we don't actually deallocate page here. we postpone the deallocation after commit, since we don't
5645  * want anyone to reuse it until we are really sure the page is no longer used.
5646  *
5647  * temporary files: we do not deallocate the page.
5648  *
5649  * numerable files: we mark the page for
5650  */
5651 
5652  /* todo: add known is_temp/is_numerable */
5653 
5654  /* read file type from header if caller doesn't know it. debug always reads the type from file header to check caller
5655  * is not wrong. */
5656 #if defined (NDEBUG)
5657  if (file_type_hint == FILE_UNKNOWN_TYPE
5658  || file_type_hint == FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH || file_type_hint == FILE_EXTENDIBLE_HASH_DIRECTORY)
5659 #endif /* NDEBUG */
5660  {
5661  /* this should be avoided in release */
5662  vpid_fhead.volid = vfid->volid;
5663  vpid_fhead.pageid = vfid->fileid;
5664 
5665  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
5666  if (page_fhead == NULL)
5667  {
5668  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5669  goto exit;
5670  }
5671  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
5672  /* check file type hint is not incorrect.
5673  * note: sometimes the caller may not know if file is FILE_HEAP or FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS. it doesn't make a
5674  * difference here, so it is accepted to give the generic FILE_HEAP hint. */
5675  assert (file_type_hint == FILE_UNKNOWN_TYPE || file_type_hint == fhead->type
5676  || (file_type_hint == FILE_HEAP && fhead->type == FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS));
5677  file_type_hint = fhead->type;
5678 
5679  assert (!VPID_EQ (&fhead->vpid_sticky_first, vpid));
5680  }
5681 
5682  if ((fhead != NULL && !FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead)) || file_type_hint != FILE_TEMP)
5683  {
5684  /* for all files, we add a postpone record and do the actual deallocation at run postpone. */
5685  VFID_COPY ((VFID *) log_data, vfid);
5686  VPID_COPY ((VPID *) (log_data + sizeof (VFID)), vpid);
5687  log_append_postpone (thread_p, RVFL_DEALLOC, &log_addr, LOG_DATA_SIZE, log_data);
5688 
5689  file_log ("file_dealloc", "file %s %d|%d dealloc vpid %d|%d postponed",
5690  file_type_to_string (file_type_hint), VFID_AS_ARGS (vfid), VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid));
5691  }
5692  else
5693  {
5694  /* we do not deallocate pages from temporary files */
5695  }
5696 
5697  if (!FILE_TYPE_CAN_BE_NUMERABLE (file_type_hint))
5698  {
5699  /* we don't need to do anything now. the actual deallocation is postponed (or skipped altogether). */
5700  goto exit;
5701  }
5702 
5703  if (page_fhead == NULL)
5704  {
5705  vpid_fhead.volid = vfid->volid;
5706  vpid_fhead.pageid = vfid->fileid;
5707 
5708  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
5709  if (page_fhead == NULL)
5710  {
5711  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5712  goto exit;
5713  }
5714  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
5715  }
5716 
5717  assert (page_fhead != NULL);
5718  assert (fhead != NULL);
5719  assert (!VPID_EQ (&fhead->vpid_sticky_first, vpid));
5720 
5721  if (!FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead))
5722  {
5723  /* we don't need to do anything now. the actual deallocation is postponed (or skipped altogether). */
5724  goto exit;
5725  }
5726 
5727  /* search for VPID in user page table */
5728  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_user_page_ftab);
5729  error_code = file_extdata_search_item (thread_p, &extdata_user_page_ftab, vpid, file_compare_vpids, false, true,
5730  &found, &pos, &page_ftab);
5731  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5732  {
5733  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5734  goto exit;
5735  }
5736  if (!found)
5737  {
5738  /* not found?? corrupted table! */
5739  assert_release (false);
5740  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5741  goto exit;
5742  }
5743 
5744  /* check not marked as deleted */
5745  vpid_found = (VPID *) file_extdata_at (extdata_user_page_ftab, pos);
5746  if (FILE_USER_PAGE_IS_MARKED_DELETED (vpid_found))
5747  {
5748  /* already marked as deleted? I don't think so! */
5749  assert_release (false);
5750  error_code = ER_FAILED;
5751  goto exit;
5752  }
5753 
5754  /* mark page as deleted */
5755  FILE_USER_PAGE_MARK_DELETED (vpid_found);
5756 
5757  page_extdata = page_ftab != NULL ? page_ftab : page_fhead;
5758  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_extdata);
5759 
5760  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_extdata, DONT_FREE);
5761  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
5762  {
5763  /* log it */
5764  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
5765 
5766  addr.pgptr = page_extdata;
5767  addr.offset = (PGLENGTH) (((char *) vpid_found) - addr.pgptr);
5768  log_append_undoredo_data (thread_p, RVFL_USER_PAGE_MARK_DELETE, &addr, LOG_DATA_SIZE, 0, log_data, NULL);
5769  }
5770 
5771  file_log ("file_dealloc",
5772  "marked page %d|%d as deleted in file %d|%d, page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, "
5773  "crt_lsa %lld_%d, at offset %d ", VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_found),
5774  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_extdata, &save_lsa),
5775  (PGLENGTH) (((char *) vpid_found) - page_extdata));
5776 
5777  /* update file header */
5778  file_header_update_mark_deleted (thread_p, page_fhead, 1);
5779 
5780  file_log ("file_dealloc", "file %d|%d marked vpid %|%d as deleted", VFID_AS_ARGS (vfid), VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid));
5781 
5782  if (FILE_CACHE_LAST_FIND_NTH (fhead))
5783  {
5784  /* reset cached search location */
5785  VPID_SET_NULL (&fhead->vpid_find_nth_last);
5786  fhead->first_index_find_nth_last = 0;
5787  }
5788 
5789  /* done */
5790  assert (error_code != NO_ERROR);
5791 
5792 exit:
5793  if (page_fhead != NULL)
5794  {
5795  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
5796  }
5797  if (page_ftab != NULL)
5798  {
5799  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab);
5800  }
5801 
5802  return error_code;
5803 
5804 #undef LOG_DATA_SIZE
5805 }
5806 
5807 /*
5808  * file_perm_dealloc () - Deallocate page from file tables.
5809  *
5810  * return : Error code
5811  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
5812  * page_fhead (in) : File header page
5813  * vpid_dealloc (in) : VPID of page being deallocated
5814  * alloc_type (in) : User/table page allocation type
5815  */
5816 static int
5817 file_perm_dealloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, const VPID * vpid_dealloc, FILE_ALLOC_TYPE alloc_type)
5818 {
5819  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
5820  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab;
5821  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_full_ftab;
5822  bool found;
5823  int position;
5824  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
5825  VSID vsid_dealloc;
5826  bool is_empty = false;
5827  bool was_full = false;
5828  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
5829  int offset_to_dealloc_bit;
5830  PAGE_PTR page_dealloc = NULL;
5831  LOG_LSA save_page_lsa;
5832  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
5833 
5834  /* how it works:
5835  * the deallocation should find sector of page and clear the bit of page in sector page bitmap. if the sector was
5836  * full, it should be moved to partial table.
5837  *
5838  * caller should have started a system operation! all table changes should be committed before file header is unfixed.
5839  *
5840  * note: this is only for permanent files. temporary files do not deallocate pages.
5841  * note: this does not handle user page table.
5842  * note: this should always be called under a system operation.
5843  */
5844 
5845  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
5846 
5847  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
5848  assert (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
5849  assert (!VPID_EQ (&fhead->vpid_sticky_first, vpid_dealloc));
5850 
5851  /* find page sector in one of the partial or full tables */
5852  vsid_dealloc.volid = vpid_dealloc->volid;
5853  vsid_dealloc.sectid = SECTOR_FROM_PAGEID (vpid_dealloc->pageid);
5854 
5855  file_log ("file_perm_dealloc",
5856  "file %d|%d de%s %d|%d (search for VSID %d|%d) \n" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG,
5857  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), FILE_ALLOC_TYPE_STRING (alloc_type), VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_dealloc),
5858  VSID_AS_ARGS (&vsid_dealloc), FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead));
5859 
5860  /* search partial table. */
5861  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
5862  error_code = file_extdata_search_item (thread_p, &extdata_part_ftab, &vsid_dealloc, disk_compare_vsids, true, true,
5863  &found, &position, &page_ftab);
5864  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5865  {
5866  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5867  goto exit;
5868  }
5869 
5870  if (found)
5871  {
5872  /* clear the bit for page. */
5873  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *partsect = (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) file_extdata_at (extdata_part_ftab, position);
5874 
5875  offset_to_dealloc_bit = file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (partsect, vpid_dealloc->pageid);
5876 
5877  file_partsect_clear_bit (partsect, offset_to_dealloc_bit);
5878  is_empty = file_partsect_is_empty (partsect);
5879 
5880  addr.pgptr = page_ftab != NULL ? page_ftab : page_fhead;
5881  addr.offset = (PGLENGTH) (((char *) partsect) - addr.pgptr);
5882  save_page_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (addr.pgptr);
5883 
5884  log_append_undoredo_data (thread_p, RVFL_PARTSECT_DEALLOC, &addr,
5885  sizeof (offset_to_dealloc_bit), sizeof (offset_to_dealloc_bit),
5886  &offset_to_dealloc_bit, &offset_to_dealloc_bit);
5887 
5888  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, addr.pgptr, DONT_FREE);
5889 
5890  file_log ("file_perm_dealloc",
5891  "dealloc page %d|%d in file %d|%d page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d, "
5892  "clear bit at offset %d in partsect at offset %d \n"
5893  FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("partsect after"),
5894  VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_dealloc), VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self),
5895  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (addr.pgptr, &save_page_lsa), offset_to_dealloc_bit,
5896  addr.offset, FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (partsect));
5897 
5898  if (page_ftab != NULL)
5899  {
5900  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
5901  }
5902  }
5903  else
5904  {
5905  /* not in partial table. */
5906  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR partsect_new;
5907  VPID vpid_merged = VPID_INITIALIZER;
5908  bool is_merged_page_from_sector = false;
5909 
5910  assert (page_ftab == NULL);
5911 
5912  /* remove from full table */
5913 
5914  was_full = true;
5915  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_full_ftab);
5916  error_code = file_extdata_find_and_remove_item (thread_p, extdata_full_ftab, page_fhead, &vsid_dealloc,
5917  disk_compare_vsids, true, NULL, &vpid_merged);
5918  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5919  {
5920  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5921  goto exit;
5922  }
5923  if (!VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_merged))
5924  {
5925  /* full table page was merged. we need to deallocate the merged page too, unless it belong to the same sector
5926  * as deallocated page. in that case, we only need to remove its bit from the sector we are moving to partial
5927  * table. */
5928  if (VSID_IS_SECTOR_OF_VPID (&vsid_dealloc, &vpid_merged))
5929  {
5930  is_merged_page_from_sector = true;
5931  /* we'll deal with it below */
5932  }
5933  else
5934  {
5935  /* deallocate page. */
5936  error_code = file_perm_dealloc (thread_p, page_fhead, &vpid_merged, FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE);
5937  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5938  {
5939  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5940  return error_code;
5941  }
5942  }
5943  }
5944 
5945  /* add to partial table. */
5946 
5947  /* create the partial sector structure without the bit for page */
5948  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
5949  partsect_new.vsid = vsid_dealloc;
5950  partsect_new.page_bitmap = FILE_FULL_PAGE_BITMAP;
5951  offset_to_dealloc_bit = file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (&partsect_new, vpid_dealloc->pageid);
5952  file_partsect_clear_bit (&partsect_new, offset_to_dealloc_bit);
5953  if (is_merged_page_from_sector)
5954  {
5955  /* we also need to remove merged page from this sector. */
5956  offset_to_dealloc_bit = file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (&partsect_new, vpid_merged.pageid);
5957  file_partsect_clear_bit (&partsect_new, offset_to_dealloc_bit);
5958 
5959  file_log ("file_perm_dealloc",
5960  "merged full table page %d|%d also belongs to sector being moved to partial table \n",
5961  VPID_AS_ARGS (&vpid_merged));
5962 
5963  /* need to update file header */
5964  file_header_dealloc (fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE, false, false);
5965  save_page_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
5966  file_log_fhead_dealloc (thread_p, page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE, false, false);
5967 
5968  file_log ("file_perm_dealloc",
5969  "update header in file %d|%d, header page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d, "
5970  "after simulating the deallocation of full table page \n" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG,
5971  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_page_lsa),
5972  FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead));
5973 
5974  /* deallocate page */
5975  page_dealloc = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_merged, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
5976  if (page_dealloc == NULL)
5977  {
5978  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
5979  return error_code;
5980  }
5981 
5982  pgbuf_dealloc_page (thread_p, page_dealloc);
5983  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_FILE_NUM_PAGE_DEALLOCS);
5984  }
5985 
5986  /* find free space */
5987  error_code = file_extdata_find_not_full (thread_p, &extdata_part_ftab, &page_ftab, &found);
5988  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
5989  {
5990  ASSERT_ERROR ();
5991  goto exit;
5992  }
5993  /* where is extdata_part_ftab? */
5994  addr.pgptr = page_ftab != NULL ? page_ftab : page_fhead;
5995 
5996  if (found)
5997  {
5998  /* found free space in table */
5999 
6000  /* find the correct position for new partial sector to keep the table ordered */
6001  file_extdata_find_ordered (extdata_part_ftab, &vsid_dealloc, disk_compare_vsids, &found, &position);
6002  if (found)
6003  {
6004  /* ups, duplicate! */
6005  assert_release (false);
6006  error_code = ER_FAILED;
6007  goto exit;
6008  }
6009  save_page_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (addr.pgptr);
6010  file_log_extdata_add (thread_p, extdata_part_ftab, addr.pgptr, position, 1, &partsect_new);
6011  file_extdata_insert_at (extdata_part_ftab, position, 1, &partsect_new);
6012 
6013  file_log ("file_perm_dealloc",
6014  "add new partsect at position %d in file %d|%d, page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, "
6015  "crt_lsa %lld|%d \n"
6016  FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("new partial sector")
6017  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("partial table component"), position,
6018  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self),
6019  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (addr.pgptr, &save_page_lsa),
6020  FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (&partsect_new), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_ftab));
6021 
6022  if (page_ftab != NULL)
6023  {
6024  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
6025  }
6026  }
6027  else
6028  {
6029  /* no free space in partial table. we need to add a new page. */
6030  VPID vpid_ftab_new = VPID_INITIALIZER;
6031 
6032  error_code = file_perm_alloc (thread_p, page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE, &vpid_ftab_new);
6033  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6034  {
6035  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6036  goto exit;
6037  }
6038  assert (!VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_ftab_new));
6039 
6040  /* set next VPID in last extensible component */
6041  assert (VPID_ISNULL (&extdata_part_ftab->vpid_next));
6042  file_log_extdata_set_next (thread_p, extdata_part_ftab, addr.pgptr, &vpid_ftab_new);
6043  VPID_COPY (&extdata_part_ftab->vpid_next, &vpid_ftab_new);
6044  if (page_ftab != NULL)
6045  {
6046  /* no longer needed */
6047  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
6048  }
6049 
6050  /* fix new table page */
6051  page_ftab = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_ftab_new, NEW_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6052  if (page_ftab == NULL)
6053  {
6054  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
6055  goto exit;
6056  }
6057  pgbuf_set_page_ptype (thread_p, page_ftab, PAGE_FTAB);
6058 
6059  /* init new extensible data and add new partial sector */
6060  extdata_part_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
6061  file_extdata_init (sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR), DB_PAGESIZE, extdata_part_ftab);
6062  file_extdata_append (extdata_part_ftab, &partsect_new);
6063  pgbuf_log_new_page (thread_p, page_ftab, file_extdata_size (extdata_part_ftab), PAGE_FTAB);
6064 
6065  file_log ("file_perm_dealloc",
6066  "file %d|%d moved to new partial table page %d|%d \n"
6067  FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("new partial sector")
6068  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("partial table component"),
6069  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self),
6070  VPID_AS_ARGS (&vpid_ftab_new),
6071  FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (&partsect_new), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_ftab));
6072 
6073  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
6074  }
6075  }
6076 
6077  /* we should have freed any other file table pages */
6078  assert (page_ftab == NULL);
6079 
6080  /* almost done. We need to update header statistics */
6081  file_header_dealloc (fhead, alloc_type, is_empty, was_full);
6082  save_page_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
6083  file_log_fhead_dealloc (thread_p, page_fhead, alloc_type, is_empty, was_full);
6084 
6085  file_log ("file_perm_dealloc",
6086  "update header in file %d|%d, header page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d, "
6087  "after de%s, is_empty = %s, was_full = %s, \n" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG,
6088  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_page_lsa),
6089  FILE_ALLOC_TYPE_STRING (alloc_type), is_empty ? "true" : "false", was_full ? "true" : "false",
6090  FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead));
6091 
6092  /* deallocate page */
6093  page_dealloc = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, vpid_dealloc, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6094  if (page_dealloc == NULL)
6095  {
6096  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
6097  goto exit;
6098  }
6099 
6100  pgbuf_dealloc_page (thread_p, page_dealloc);
6101  perfmon_inc_stat (thread_p, PSTAT_FILE_NUM_PAGE_DEALLOCS);
6102 
6103  /* done */
6104  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
6105 
6106 exit:
6107  if (page_ftab != NULL)
6108  {
6109  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab);
6110  }
6111 
6112  return error_code;
6113 }
6114 
6115 /*
6116  * file_rv_dealloc_internal () - Actual deallocation at recovery.
6117  *
6118  * return : Error code
6119  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
6120  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
6121  * compensate_or_run_postpone (in) : Compensate if this is called for undo, run postpone if this is called for postpone.
6122  */
6123 static int
6124 file_rv_dealloc_internal (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv, bool compensate_or_run_postpone)
6125 {
6126  VPID vpid_fhead;
6127  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
6128  VFID *vfid;
6129  VPID *vpid_dealloc;
6130  int offset = 0;
6131  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
6132  bool is_sysop_started = false;
6133  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6134 
6135  /* how it works:
6136  * deallocates a page in either of two contexts:
6137  * 1. undoing a page allocation.
6138  * 2. doing (actual) page deallocation on do postpone phase.
6139  *
6140  * this should clear the page bit in file tables (partial or full) by calling file_perm_dealloc.
6141  * also we remove the VPID from user page table.
6142  */
6143 
6144  /* recovery data: file identifier + page identifier */
6145  vfid = (VFID *) (rcv->data + offset);
6146  offset += sizeof (*vfid);
6147 
6148  vpid_dealloc = (VPID *) (rcv->data + offset);
6149  offset += sizeof (*vpid_dealloc);
6150 
6151  assert (offset == rcv->length);
6152 
6153  /* get file header */
6154  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
6155  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6156  if (page_fhead == NULL)
6157  {
6158  /* should not be interrupted */
6159  assert_release (false);
6160  return ER_FAILED;
6161  }
6162 
6163  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
6164  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
6165 
6166  if (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
6167  {
6168  /* no need to actually deallocate page. should not even be here. */
6169  assert (false);
6170  goto exit;
6171  }
6172 
6173  /* so, we do need a system operation here. the system operation will end, based on context, with commit & compensate
6174  * or with commit & run postpone. */
6175  log_sysop_start_atomic (thread_p);
6176  is_sysop_started = true;
6177 
6178  /* clear page bit by calling file_perm_dealloc */
6179  error_code = file_perm_dealloc (thread_p, page_fhead, vpid_dealloc, FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE);
6180  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6181  {
6182  /* We cannot allow errors during recovery! */
6183  assert_release (false);
6184  error_code = ER_FAILED;
6185  goto exit;
6186  }
6187 
6188  if (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead))
6189  {
6190  /* remove VPID from user page table. */
6191  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_user_page_ftab;
6192  VPID vpid_removed = VPID_INITIALIZER;
6193  VPID vpid_merged = VPID_INITIALIZER;
6194 
6195  /* remove from user table */
6196  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_user_page_ftab);
6197  error_code = file_extdata_find_and_remove_item (thread_p, extdata_user_page_ftab, page_fhead, vpid_dealloc,
6198  file_compare_vpids, false, &vpid_removed, &vpid_merged);
6199  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6200  {
6201  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6202  goto exit;
6203  }
6204 
6205  if (!VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_merged))
6206  {
6207  /* user page table shrank */
6208  error_code = file_perm_dealloc (thread_p, page_fhead, &vpid_merged, FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE);
6209  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6210  {
6211  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6212  goto exit;
6213  }
6214  }
6215 
6216  /* is mark deleted? */
6217  if (FILE_USER_PAGE_IS_MARKED_DELETED (&vpid_removed))
6218  {
6219  /* update file header */
6220  file_header_update_mark_deleted (thread_p, page_fhead, -1);
6221  }
6222  }
6223 
6224  /* done */
6225  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
6226 
6227 exit:
6228  /* system operation must be committed before releasing header page. */
6229  if (is_sysop_started)
6230  {
6231  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6232  {
6233  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
6234  }
6235  else
6236  {
6237  if (compensate_or_run_postpone == FILE_RV_DEALLOC_COMPENSATE)
6238  {
6239  log_sysop_end_logical_compensate (thread_p, &rcv->reference_lsa);
6240  }
6241  else
6242  {
6243  log_sysop_end_logical_run_postpone (thread_p, &rcv->reference_lsa);
6244  }
6245  }
6246  }
6247 
6248  /* deallocation should be completed; check header */
6249  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
6250 
6251  if (page_fhead != NULL)
6252  {
6253  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
6254  }
6255  return error_code;
6256 }
6257 
6258 /*
6259  * file_rv_dealloc_on_undo () - Deallocate the page on undo (we need to use compensate on system op commit)
6260  *
6261  * return : Error code
6262  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
6263  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
6264  */
6265 int
6266 file_rv_dealloc_on_undo (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
6267 {
6268  file_log ("file_rv_dealloc_on_undo", "lsa = %lld|%d", LSA_AS_ARGS (&rcv->reference_lsa));
6269 
6270  return file_rv_dealloc_internal (thread_p, rcv, FILE_RV_DEALLOC_COMPENSATE);
6271 }
6272 
6273 /*
6274  * file_rv_dealloc_on_postpone () - Deallocate the page on do postpone (we need to use run postpone on system op commit)
6275  *
6276  * return : Error code
6277  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
6278  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
6279  */
6280 int
6281 file_rv_dealloc_on_postpone (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
6282 {
6283  file_log ("file_rv_dealloc_on_postpone", "lsa = %lld|%d", LSA_AS_ARGS (&rcv->reference_lsa));
6284 
6285  return file_rv_dealloc_internal (thread_p, rcv, FILE_RV_DEALLOC_RUN_POSTPONE);
6286 }
6287 
6288 /*
6289  * file_get_num_user_pages () - Output number of user pages in file
6290  *
6291  * return : Error code
6292  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
6293  * vfid (in) : File identifier
6294  * n_user_pages_out (out) : Output number of user pages
6295  */
6296 int
6297 file_get_num_user_pages (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, int *n_user_pages_out)
6298 {
6299  VPID vpid_fhead;
6300  PAGE_PTR page_fhead;
6301  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
6302  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6303 
6304  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
6305  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6306  if (page_fhead == NULL)
6307  {
6308  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
6309  return error_code;
6310  }
6311 
6312  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
6313  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
6314 
6315  *n_user_pages_out = fhead->n_page_user;
6316  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
6317 
6318  return NO_ERROR;
6319 }
6320 
6321 /*
6322  * file_check_vpid () - check vpid is one of the file's user pages
6323  *
6324  * return : DISK_INVALID if page does not belong to file, DISK_ERROR for errors and DISK_VALID for successful
6325  * check
6326  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
6327  * vfid (in) : file identifier
6328  * vpid_lookup (in) : checked VPID
6329  */
6330 DISK_ISVALID
6331 file_check_vpid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, const VPID * vpid_lookup)
6332 {
6333  VPID vpid_fhead;
6334  PAGE_PTR page_fhead;
6335  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
6336  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
6337  VSID vsid_lookup;
6338  bool found;
6339  int pos;
6340  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab;
6341  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_full_ftab;
6342  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_user_page_ftab;
6343  DISK_ISVALID isvalid = DISK_VALID;
6344 
6345  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
6346  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6347  if (page_fhead == NULL)
6348  {
6349  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6350  return DISK_ERROR;
6351  }
6352 
6353  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
6354  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
6355 
6356  /* first search the VPID in sector tables: partial, then full. */
6357  VSID_FROM_VPID (&vsid_lookup, vpid_lookup);
6358 
6359  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
6360  if (file_extdata_search_item (thread_p, &extdata_part_ftab, &vsid_lookup, disk_compare_vsids, true, false, &found,
6361  &pos, &page_ftab) != NO_ERROR)
6362  {
6363  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6364  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
6365  goto exit;
6366  }
6367  if (found)
6368  {
6369  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *partsect;
6370 
6371  partsect = (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) file_extdata_at (extdata_part_ftab, pos);
6372  if (file_partsect_is_bit_set (partsect, file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (partsect, vpid_lookup->pageid)))
6373  {
6374  /* ok */
6375  /* fall through */
6376  }
6377  else
6378  {
6379  /* not ok */
6380  assert_release (false);
6381  isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
6382  goto exit;
6383  }
6384  }
6385  else
6386  {
6387  /* Search in full table */
6388  if (page_ftab != NULL)
6389  {
6390  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
6391  }
6392  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_full_ftab);
6393  if (file_extdata_search_item (thread_p, &extdata_full_ftab, &vsid_lookup, disk_compare_vsids, true, false,
6394  &found, &pos, &page_ftab) != NO_ERROR)
6395  {
6396  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6397  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
6398  goto exit;
6399  }
6400  if (!found)
6401  {
6402  /* not ok */
6403  assert_release (false);
6404  isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
6405  goto exit;
6406  }
6407  }
6408  if (page_ftab != NULL)
6409  {
6410  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
6411  }
6412 
6413  if (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead))
6414  {
6415  /* Search in user page table */
6416  VPID *vpid_in_table;
6417 
6418  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_user_page_ftab);
6419  if (file_extdata_search_item (thread_p, &extdata_user_page_ftab, vpid_lookup, file_compare_vpids, false, false,
6420  &found, &pos, &page_ftab) != NO_ERROR)
6421  {
6422  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6423  isvalid = DISK_ERROR;
6424  goto exit;
6425  }
6426  if (!found)
6427  {
6428  /* not ok */
6429  assert_release (false);
6430  isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
6431  goto exit;
6432  }
6433  /* check not marked as deleted */
6434  vpid_in_table = (VPID *) file_extdata_at (extdata_user_page_ftab, pos);
6435  if (FILE_USER_PAGE_IS_MARKED_DELETED (vpid_in_table))
6436  {
6437  /* not ok */
6438  assert_release (false);
6439  isvalid = DISK_INVALID;
6440  goto exit;
6441  }
6442  /* ok */
6443  }
6444 
6445  /* page is part of file */
6446  assert (isvalid == DISK_VALID);
6447 
6448 exit:
6449  if (page_ftab != NULL)
6450  {
6451  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab);
6452  }
6453  if (page_fhead != NULL)
6454  {
6455  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
6456  }
6457  return isvalid;
6458 }
6459 
6460 /*
6461  * file_get_type () - Get file type for VFID.
6462  *
6463  * return : Error code
6464  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
6465  * vfid (in) : File identifier
6466  * ftype_out (out) : Output file type
6467  */
6468 int
6469 file_get_type (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, FILE_TYPE * ftype_out)
6470 {
6471  VPID vpid_fhead;
6472  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
6473  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
6474 
6475  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
6476  assert (ftype_out != NULL);
6477 
6478  /* read from file header */
6479  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
6480  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6481  if (page_fhead == NULL)
6482  {
6483  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6484 
6485  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
6486  return error_code;
6487  }
6488 
6489  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
6490  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
6491 
6492  *ftype_out = fhead->type;
6493  assert (*ftype_out != FILE_UNKNOWN_TYPE);
6494 
6495  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
6496 
6497  return NO_ERROR;
6498 }
6499 
6500 /*
6501  * file_is_temp () - is file temporary?
6502  *
6503  * return : error code
6504  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
6505  * vfid (in) : file identifier
6506  * is_temp (out) : true for temporary, false otherwise
6507  */
6508 int
6509 file_is_temp (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, bool * is_temp)
6510 {
6511  VPID vpid_fhead;
6512  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
6513  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
6514 
6515  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
6516  assert (is_temp != NULL);
6517 
6518  /* read from file header */
6519  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
6520  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6521  if (page_fhead == NULL)
6522  {
6523  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6524  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
6525  return error_code;
6526  }
6527  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
6528  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
6529 
6530  *is_temp = FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead);
6531 
6532  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
6533 
6534  return NO_ERROR;
6535 }
6536 
6537 /*
6538  * file_table_collect_ftab_pages () - collect file table pages
6539  *
6540  * return : error code
6541  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
6542  * page_fhead (in) : file header page
6543  * collect_numerable (in) : true to collect also user page table, false otherwise
6544  * collector_out (out) : output collected table pages
6545  */
6546 STATIC_INLINE int
6547 file_table_collect_ftab_pages (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, bool collect_numerable,
6548  FILE_FTAB_COLLECTOR * collector_out)
6549 {
6550  VPID vpid_fhead;
6551  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
6552  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_ftab;
6553  int error_code;
6554 
6555  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
6556 
6557  /* init collector */
6558  collector_out->partsect_ftab =
6559  (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) db_private_alloc (thread_p, sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR) * fhead->n_page_ftab);
6560  if (collector_out->partsect_ftab == NULL)
6561  {
6562  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1,
6563  sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR) * fhead->n_page_ftab);
6564  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
6565  }
6566 
6567  /* add page header */
6568  pgbuf_get_vpid (page_fhead, &vpid_fhead);
6569  VSID_FROM_VPID (&collector_out->partsect_ftab[0].vsid, &vpid_fhead);
6570  collector_out->partsect_ftab[0].page_bitmap = FILE_EMPTY_PAGE_BITMAP;
6571  file_partsect_set_bit (&collector_out->partsect_ftab[0],
6572  file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (&collector_out->partsect_ftab[0], vpid_fhead.pageid));
6573  collector_out->nsects = 1;
6574  collector_out->npages = 1;
6575 
6576  file_log ("file_temp_reset_user_pages",
6577  "init collector with page %d|%d \n "
6578  FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("partsect"), VPID_AS_ARGS (&vpid_fhead),
6579  FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (collector_out->partsect_ftab));
6580 
6581  /* add other pages in partial sector table */
6582  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
6583  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, file_extdata_collect_ftab_pages, collector_out, NULL,
6584  NULL, false, NULL, NULL);
6585  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6586  {
6587  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6588  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, collector_out->partsect_ftab);
6589  return error_code;
6590  }
6591 
6592  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
6593  {
6594  /* add other pages from full sector table */
6595  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
6596  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, file_extdata_collect_ftab_pages, collector_out,
6597  NULL, NULL, false, NULL, NULL);
6598  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6599  {
6600  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6601  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, collector_out->partsect_ftab);
6602  return error_code;
6603  }
6604  }
6605 
6606  if (collect_numerable && FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead))
6607  {
6608  /* add other pages from user-page table */
6609  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
6610  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, file_extdata_collect_ftab_pages, collector_out,
6611  NULL, NULL, false, NULL, NULL);
6612  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6613  {
6614  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6615  db_private_free_and_init (thread_p, collector_out->partsect_ftab);
6616  return error_code;
6617  }
6618  }
6619 
6620  return NO_ERROR;
6621 }
6622 
6623 /*
6624  * file_extdata_collect_ftab_pages () - FILE_EXTDATA_FUNC to collect pages used for file table
6625  *
6626  * return : NO_ERROR
6627  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
6628  * extdata (in) : extensible data
6629  * stop (in) : ignored
6630  * args (in/out) : FILE_FTAB_COLLECTOR * - file table page collector
6631  */
6632 static int
6633 file_extdata_collect_ftab_pages (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, bool * stop, void *args)
6634 {
6635  FILE_FTAB_COLLECTOR *collect = (FILE_FTAB_COLLECTOR *) args;
6636  VSID vsid_this;
6637  int idx_sect = 0;
6638 
6639  if (!LSA_ISNULL (&extdata->vpid_next))
6640  {
6641  VSID_FROM_VPID (&vsid_this, &extdata->vpid_next);
6642 
6643  /* find in collected sectors */
6644  for (idx_sect = 0; idx_sect < collect->nsects; idx_sect++)
6645  {
6646  if (disk_compare_vsids (&vsid_this, &collect->partsect_ftab->vsid) == 0)
6647  {
6648  break;
6649  }
6650  }
6651 
6652  if (idx_sect == collect->nsects)
6653  {
6654  /* not found, append new sector */
6655  collect->partsect_ftab[collect->nsects].vsid = vsid_this;
6656  collect->partsect_ftab[collect->nsects].page_bitmap = FILE_EMPTY_PAGE_BITMAP;
6657  collect->nsects++;
6658 
6659  file_log ("file_extdata_collect_ftab_pages",
6660  "add new vsid %d|%d, nsects = %d", VSID_AS_ARGS (&vsid_this), collect->nsects);
6661  }
6662  file_partsect_set_bit (&collect->partsect_ftab[idx_sect],
6663  file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (&collect->partsect_ftab[idx_sect],
6664  extdata->vpid_next.pageid));
6665 
6666  file_log ("file_extdata_collect_ftab_pages",
6667  "collect ftab page %d|%d, \n" FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("partsect"),
6668  VPID_AS_ARGS (&extdata->vpid_next), FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (&collect->partsect_ftab[idx_sect]));
6669  collect->npages++;
6670  }
6671 
6672  return NO_ERROR;
6673 }
6674 
6675 /*
6676  * file_table_collector_has_page () - check if page is in collected file table pages
6677  *
6678  * return : true if page is file table page, false otherwise
6679  * collector (in) : file table pages collector
6680  * vpid (in) : page id
6681  */
6682 STATIC_INLINE bool
6683 file_table_collector_has_page (FILE_FTAB_COLLECTOR * collector, VPID * vpid)
6684 {
6685  int iter;
6686  VSID vsid;
6687 
6688  VSID_FROM_VPID (&vsid, vpid);
6689 
6690  for (iter = 0; iter < collector->nsects; iter++)
6691  {
6692  if (VSID_EQ (&vsid, &collector->partsect_ftab[iter].vsid))
6693  {
6694  return file_partsect_is_bit_set (&collector->partsect_ftab[iter],
6695  file_partsect_pageid_to_offset (&collector->partsect_ftab[iter],
6696  vpid->pageid));
6697  }
6698  }
6699 
6700  return false;
6701 }
6702 
6703 /*
6704  * file_sector_map_pages () - FILE_EXTDATA_ITEM_FUNC used for mapping a function on all user pages
6705  *
6706  * return : error code
6707  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
6708  * data (in) : FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR or VSID
6709  * index (in) : ignored
6710  * stop (out) : output true when to stop the mapping
6711  * args (in) : map context
6712  */
6713 static int
6714 file_sector_map_pages (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const void *data, int index, bool * stop, void *args)
6715 {
6716  FILE_MAP_CONTEXT *context = (FILE_MAP_CONTEXT *) args;
6717  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR partsect = FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR_INITIALIZER;
6718  int iter;
6719  VPID vpid;
6720  PAGE_PTR page = NULL;
6721  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6722 
6723  assert (context != NULL);
6724  assert (context->stop == false);
6725  assert (context->func != NULL);
6726  assert (context->latch_mode == PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE || context->latch_mode == PGBUF_LATCH_READ);
6727  assert (context->latch_cond == PGBUF_CONDITIONAL_LATCH || context->latch_cond == PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6728 
6729  /* how this works:
6730  * get all allocated pages from sector in file table. data can be either a partial sector (vsid + allocation bitmap)
6731  * or a vsid (full sector - all its pages are allocated).
6732  * for each page, we have to check first it is not a table page. we only want to map the function for user pages.
6733  *
6734  * if the page cannot be fixed conditionally, it is simply skipped. careful when using unconditional latch in server
6735  * mode. there is a risk of dead-latches.
6736  *
6737  * map function can keep the page, but it must set the page pointer to NULL.
6738  */
6739 
6740  /* hack to know this is partial table or full table */
6741  if (context->is_partial)
6742  {
6743  partsect = *(FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) data;
6744  }
6745  else
6746  {
6747  partsect.vsid = *(VSID *) data;
6748  }
6749 
6750  vpid.volid = partsect.vsid.volid;
6751  for (iter = 0, vpid.pageid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (partsect.vsid.sectid); iter < FILE_ALLOC_BITMAP_NBITS;
6752  iter++, vpid.pageid++)
6753  {
6754  if (context->is_partial && !file_partsect_is_bit_set (&partsect, iter))
6755  {
6756  /* not allocated */
6757  continue;
6758  }
6759 
6760  if (file_table_collector_has_page (&context->ftab_collector, &vpid))
6761  {
6762  /* skip table pages */
6763  continue;
6764  }
6765 
6766  page = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid, OLD_PAGE, context->latch_mode, context->latch_cond);
6767  if (page == NULL)
6768  {
6769  if (context->latch_cond == PGBUF_CONDITIONAL_LATCH)
6770  {
6771  /* exit gracefully */
6772  return NO_ERROR;
6773  }
6774  /* error */
6775  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
6776  return error_code;
6777  }
6778 
6779  assert (pgbuf_get_page_ptype (thread_p, page) != PAGE_FTAB);
6780 
6781  /* call map function */
6782  error_code = context->func (thread_p, &page, stop, context->args);
6783  if (page != NULL)
6784  {
6785  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page);
6786  }
6787  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6788  {
6789  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6790  return error_code;
6791  }
6792 
6793  if (*stop)
6794  {
6795  /* early out */
6796  context->stop = true;
6797  return NO_ERROR;
6798  }
6799  }
6800 
6801  return NO_ERROR;
6802 }
6803 
6804 /*
6805  * file_map_pages () - map given function on all user pages
6806  *
6807  * return : error code
6808  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
6809  * vfid (in) : file identifier
6810  * latch_mode (in) : latch mode
6811  * latch_cond (in) : latch condition
6812  * func (in) : map function
6813  * args (in) : map function arguments
6814  */
6815 int
6816 file_map_pages (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, PGBUF_LATCH_MODE latch_mode,
6817  PGBUF_LATCH_CONDITION latch_cond, FILE_MAP_PAGE_FUNC func, void *args)
6818 {
6819  VPID vpid_fhead;
6820  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
6821  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
6822  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_ftab;
6823  FILE_MAP_CONTEXT context;
6824  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6825 
6826  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
6827  assert (latch_mode == PGBUF_LATCH_READ || latch_mode == PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
6828  assert (func != NULL);
6829 
6830  /* how it works:
6831  * get all user pages in partial sector table and full sector table and apply function. the file_sector_map_pages
6832  * is first mapped on entries of partial table and then on full table.
6833  *
6834  * note that file header is read-latched during the whole time. this means page allocations/deallocations are blocked
6835  * during the process. careful when using the function in server-mode. it is not advisable to be used for hot and
6836  * large files.
6837  *
6838  * function must be mapped on user pages only. as a first step we have to collect file table pages. while mapping
6839  * function on pages, these are skipped.
6840  */
6841 
6842 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
6843  /* we cannot use unconditional latch. allocations can sometimes keep latch on a file page and then try to lock
6844  * header/table. we may cause dead latch.
6845  */
6846  assert (latch_cond == PGBUF_CONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6847  latch_cond = PGBUF_CONDITIONAL_LATCH;
6848 #endif /* SERVER_MODE */
6849 
6850  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
6851  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6852  if (page_fhead == NULL)
6853  {
6854  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
6855  return error_code;
6856  }
6857  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
6858  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
6859 
6860  /* init map context */
6861  context.func = func;
6862  context.args = args;
6863  context.latch_cond = latch_cond;
6864  context.latch_mode = latch_mode;
6865  context.stop = false;
6866  context.ftab_collector.partsect_ftab = NULL;
6867 
6868  /* collect table pages */
6869  error_code = file_table_collect_ftab_pages (thread_p, page_fhead, true, &context.ftab_collector);
6870  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6871  {
6872  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6873  goto exit;
6874  }
6875 
6876  /* map over partial sectors table */
6877  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
6878  context.is_partial = true;
6879  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, NULL, NULL, file_sector_map_pages, &context, false,
6880  NULL, NULL);
6881  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6882  {
6883  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6884  goto exit;
6885  }
6886  if (context.stop)
6887  {
6888  goto exit;
6889  }
6890 
6891  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
6892  {
6893  /* map over full table */
6894  context.is_partial = false;
6895  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
6896  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, NULL, NULL, file_sector_map_pages, &context,
6897  false, NULL, NULL);
6898  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6899  {
6900  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6901  goto exit;
6902  }
6903  }
6904 
6905  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
6906 
6907 exit:
6908  if (page_fhead != NULL)
6909  {
6910  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
6911  }
6912  if (context.ftab_collector.partsect_ftab != NULL)
6913  {
6914  db_private_free (thread_p, context.ftab_collector.partsect_ftab);
6915  }
6916 
6917  return error_code;
6918 }
6919 
6920 /*
6921  * file_table_check () - check file table is valid
6922  *
6923  * return : DISK_INVALID for unexpected errors, DISK_ERROR for expected errors,
6924  * DISK_VALID for successful check
6925  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
6926  * vfid (in) : file identifier
6927  * disk_map_clone (in/out) : clone of disk sector table maps used in stand-alone mode only to cross-check reserved
6928  * sectors
6929  */
6930 static DISK_ISVALID
6931 file_table_check (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, DISK_VOLMAP_CLONE * disk_map_clone)
6932 {
6933  VPID vpid_fhead;
6934  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
6935  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
6936  FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR collector;
6937 #if defined (SA_MODE)
6938  int iter_vsid;
6939 #endif /* SA_MODE */
6940 
6941  DISK_ISVALID valid = DISK_VALID;
6942  DISK_ISVALID allvalid = DISK_VALID;
6943  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
6944 
6945 #if defined (SA_MODE)
6946  assert (disk_map_clone != NULL);
6947 #endif /* SA_MODE */
6948 
6949  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
6950  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
6951  if (page_fhead == NULL)
6952  {
6953  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6954  return DISK_ERROR;
6955  }
6956  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
6957  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
6958 
6959  error_code = file_table_collect_all_vsids (thread_p, page_fhead, &collector);
6960  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6961  {
6962  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6963  goto exit;
6964  }
6965 
6966  if (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead))
6967  {
6968  /* check all pages in user table belong to collected page */
6969  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_user_page_ftab;
6970 
6971  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_user_page_ftab);
6972  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_user_page_ftab, NULL, NULL,
6973  file_table_check_page_is_in_sectors, &collector, false, NULL, NULL);
6974  if (error_code == ER_FAILED)
6975  {
6976  /* set for unexpected cases */
6977  allvalid = DISK_INVALID;
6978  /* fall through: also check sectors are reserved */
6979  }
6980  else if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
6981  {
6982  ASSERT_ERROR ();
6983  goto exit;
6984  }
6985  }
6986 
6987  /* check all sectors are reserved. if the file is very big, this can take a while. don't keep header page fixed */
6988  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_fhead);
6989 
6990 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
6991  valid = disk_check_sectors_are_reserved (thread_p, collector.vsids, collector.n_vsids);
6992  if (valid != DISK_VALID && allvalid == DISK_VALID)
6993  {
6994  allvalid = valid;
6995  }
6996 #else /* !SERVER_MODE */ /* SA_MODE */
6997  for (iter_vsid = 0; iter_vsid < collector.n_vsids; iter_vsid++)
6998  {
6999  valid = disk_map_clone_clear (&collector.vsids[iter_vsid], disk_map_clone);
7000  if (valid == DISK_INVALID)
7001  {
7002  allvalid = DISK_INVALID;
7003  }
7004  else
7005  {
7006  assert (valid == DISK_VALID);
7007  }
7008  }
7009 #endif /* SA_MODE */
7010 
7011 exit:
7012  if (page_fhead != NULL)
7013  {
7014  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
7015  }
7016 
7017  if (error_code != NO_ERROR && allvalid == DISK_VALID)
7018  {
7019  allvalid = DISK_ERROR;
7020  }
7021 
7022  if (collector.vsids != NULL)
7023  {
7024  db_private_free (thread_p, collector.vsids);
7025  }
7026  return allvalid;
7027 }

7029 /*
7030  * file_dump () - file dump
7031  *
7032  * return : error code
7033  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
7034  * vfid (in) : file identifier
7035  * fp (in) : output file
7036  */
7037 int
7038 file_dump (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, FILE * fp)
7039 {
7040  VPID vpid_fhead;
7041  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
7042  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
7043  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7044 
7045  fprintf (fp, "\n\n Dumping file %d|%d \n", VFID_AS_ARGS (vfid));
7046 
7047  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
7048  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
7049  if (page_fhead == NULL)
7050  {
7051  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
7052  return error_code;
7053  }
7054  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
7055 
7056  file_header_dump (thread_p, fhead, fp);
7057 
7058  error_code = file_table_dump (thread_p, fhead, fp);
7059  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7060  {
7061  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7062  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
7063  return error_code;
7064  }
7065 
7066  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
7067  return NO_ERROR;
7068 }
7069 
7070 /*
7071  * file_table_dump () - dump file table
7072  *
7073  * return : error code
7074  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
7075  * fhead (in) : file header
7076  * fp (in) : output file
7077  */
7078 STATIC_INLINE int
7079 file_table_dump (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const FILE_HEADER * fhead, FILE * fp)
7080 {
7081  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7082  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_ftab = NULL;
7083 
7084  fprintf (fp, "FILE TABLE: \n");
7085  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
7086  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, file_partial_table_extdata_dump, fp,
7087  file_partial_table_item_dump, fp, false, NULL, NULL);
7088  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7089  {
7090  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7091  return error_code;
7092  }
7093 
7094  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
7095  {
7096  FILE_HEADER_GET_FULL_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
7097  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, file_full_table_extdata_dump, fp,
7098  file_full_table_item_dump, fp, false, NULL, NULL);
7099  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7100  {
7101  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7102  return error_code;
7103  }
7104  }
7105 
7106  if (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead))
7107  {
7108  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_ftab);
7109  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_ftab, file_full_table_extdata_dump, fp,
7110  file_full_table_item_dump, fp, false, NULL, NULL);
7111  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7112  {
7113  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7114  return error_code;
7115  }
7116  }
7117 
7118  return NO_ERROR;
7119 }
7120 
7121 /*
7122  * file_partial_table_extdata_dump () - dump an extensible data from partial table
7123  *
7124  * return : NO_ERROR
7125  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
7126  * extdata (in) : extensible data
7127  * stop (in) : not used
7128  * args (in) : FILE *
7129  */
7130 static int
7131 file_partial_table_extdata_dump (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, bool * stop, void *args)
7132 {
7133  FILE *fp = (FILE *) args;
7134 
7135  fprintf (fp, FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("partial table component"), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata));
7136  return NO_ERROR;
7137 }
7138 
7139 /*
7140  * file_partial_table_item_dump () - dump an item from partial table
7141  *
7142  * return : NO_ERROR
7143  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
7144  * data (in) : FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *
7145  * index (in) : item index
7146  * stop (in) : not used
7147  * args (in) : FILE *
7148  */
7149 static int
7150 file_partial_table_item_dump (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const void *data, int index, bool * stop, void *args)
7151 {
7152  FILE *fp = (FILE *) args;
7153  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *partsect;
7154  int iter;
7155  int line_count;
7156  VPID vpid;
7157 
7158  partsect = (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) data;
7159  fprintf (fp, FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("partially allocated sector"), FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (partsect));
7160 
7161  vpid.volid = partsect->vsid.volid;
7162  fprintf (fp, "\t\t allocated pages:");
7163  line_count = 0;
7164  for (iter = 0, vpid.pageid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (partsect->vsid.sectid); iter < DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES;
7165  iter++, vpid.pageid++)
7166  {
7167  if (file_partsect_is_bit_set (partsect, iter))
7168  {
7169  if (line_count++ % 8 == 0)
7170  {
7171  fprintf (fp, "\n\t\t\t");
7172  }
7173  fprintf (fp, "%5d|%10d ", VPID_AS_ARGS (&vpid));
7174  }
7175  }
7176 
7177  fprintf (fp, "\n\t\t reserved pages:");
7178  line_count = 0;
7179  for (iter = 0, vpid.pageid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (partsect->vsid.sectid); iter < DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES;
7180  iter++, vpid.pageid++)
7181  {
7182  if (!file_partsect_is_bit_set (partsect, iter))
7183  {
7184  if (line_count++ % 8 == 0)
7185  {
7186  fprintf (fp, "\n\t\t\t");
7187  }
7188  fprintf (fp, "%5d|%10d ", VPID_AS_ARGS (&vpid));
7189  }
7190  }
7191  fprintf (fp, "\n");
7192 
7193  return NO_ERROR;
7194 }

7224 static int

7231  VPID vpid;
