7297 /*
7298  * file_spacedb () - get space usage information
7299  *
7300  * return : error code
7301  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
7302  * spacedb (out) : output space usage information
7303  */
7304 int
7305 file_spacedb (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, SPACEDB_FILES * spacedb)
7306 {
7307  int i;
7308  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7309 
7310  /* init */
7311  memset (spacedb, 0, sizeof (SPACEDB_FILES) * SPACEDB_FILE_COUNT);
7312 
7313  /* temporary files stats are already cached. */
7314  spacedb[SPACEDB_TEMP_FILE] = file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp;
7315 
7316  /* use file tracker to get info on permanent purpose files */
7317  error_code = file_tracker_spacedb (thread_p, spacedb);
7318  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7319  {
7320  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7321  return error_code;
7322  }
7323 
7324  /* compute total */
7325  memset (&spacedb[SPACEDB_TOTAL_FILE], 0, sizeof (spacedb[SPACEDB_TOTAL_FILE]));
7326  for (i = 0; i < SPACEDB_TOTAL_FILE; i++)
7327  {
7328  spacedb[SPACEDB_TOTAL_FILE].nfile += spacedb[i].nfile;
7329  spacedb[SPACEDB_TOTAL_FILE].npage_ftab += spacedb[i].npage_ftab;
7330  spacedb[SPACEDB_TOTAL_FILE].npage_user += spacedb[i].npage_user;
7331  spacedb[SPACEDB_TOTAL_FILE].npage_reserved += spacedb[i].npage_reserved;
7332  }
7333  return NO_ERROR;
7334 }
7335 
7336 /************************************************************************/
7337 /* Numerable files section. */
7338 /************************************************************************/
7339 
7340 /*
7341  * file_numerable_add_page () - Add a page at the end of user page table. This is part of the implementation for
7342  * numerable files.
7343  *
7344  * return : Error code
7345  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
7346  * page_fhead (in) : File header page
7347  * vpid (in) : VPID of page to add to use page table.
7348  */
7349 static int
7350 file_numerable_add_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, const VPID * vpid)
7351 {
7352  FILE_HEADER *fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
7353  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_user_page_ftab = NULL;
7354  VPID vpid_fhead;
7355  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
7356  PAGE_PTR page_extdata = NULL;
7357  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
7358  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7359 
7360  assert (fhead != NULL);
7361  assert (vpid != NULL && !VPID_ISNULL (vpid));
7362  assert (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead));
7363 
7364  /* how it works:
7365  * we need to add the page at the end of user page table. the order of pages in numerable files is the same as their
7366  * allocation order, so we always add a page at the end.
7367  *
7368  * note: fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab is a hint to last page in user page table, where the VPID should be added.
7369  */
7370 
7371  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (&fhead->self, &vpid_fhead);
7372 
7373  /* we have a hint on where the page must be added */
7374  if (VPID_EQ (&fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab, &vpid_fhead))
7375  {
7376  /* hint points to file header */
7377  page_extdata = page_fhead;
7378  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_user_page_ftab);
7379  }
7380  else
7381  {
7382  /* hint points to another table page. */
7383  page_ftab =
7384  pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
7385  if (page_ftab == NULL)
7386  {
7387  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
7388  goto exit;
7389  }
7390  page_extdata = page_ftab;
7391  extdata_user_page_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
7392  }
7393 
7394  file_log ("file_numerable_add_page",
7395  "file %d|%d add page %d|%d to user page table \n"
7396  FILE_HEAD_FULL_MSG
7397  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("last user page table component"),
7398  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid),
7399  FILE_HEAD_FULL_AS_ARGS (fhead), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_user_page_ftab));
7400 
7401  if (file_extdata_is_full (extdata_user_page_ftab))
7402  {
7403  /* no more room for new pages. allocate a new table page. */
7404  VPID vpid_ftab_new = VPID_INITIALIZER;
7405 
7406  if (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
7407  {
7408  /* we can have temporary numerable files */
7409  error_code = file_temp_alloc (thread_p, page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE, &vpid_ftab_new);
7410  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7411  {
7412  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7413  goto exit;
7414  }
7415  }
7416  else
7417  {
7418  error_code = file_perm_alloc (thread_p, page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TABLE_PAGE, &vpid_ftab_new);
7419  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7420  {
7421  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7422  goto exit;
7423  }
7424  }
7425  assert (!VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_ftab_new));
7426 
7427  /* create a link from previous page table. */
7428  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
7429  {
7430  /* log setting next page */
7431  file_log_extdata_set_next (thread_p, extdata_user_page_ftab, page_extdata, &vpid_ftab_new);
7432  }
7433  else
7434  {
7435  /* just set dirty */
7436  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_extdata, DONT_FREE);
7437  }
7438  VPID_COPY (&extdata_user_page_ftab->vpid_next, &vpid_ftab_new);
7439  if (page_ftab != NULL)
7440  {
7441  /* we don't need it anymore */
7442  pgbuf_set_dirty_and_free (thread_p, page_ftab);
7443  }
7444 
7445  /* fix new table page */
7446  page_ftab = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_ftab_new, NEW_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
7447  if (page_ftab == NULL)
7448  {
7449  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
7450  goto exit;
7451  }
7452  page_extdata = page_ftab;
7453  pgbuf_set_page_ptype (thread_p, page_ftab, PAGE_FTAB);
7454 
7455  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_fhead);
7456  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
7457  {
7458  /* log that we are going to change fhead->vpid_last_page_ftab. */
7459  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVFL_FHEAD_SET_LAST_USER_PAGE_FTAB, NULL, page_fhead, 0, sizeof (VPID),
7460  sizeof (VPID), &fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab, &vpid_ftab_new);
7461  }
7462 
7463  VPID_COPY (&fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab, &vpid_ftab_new);
7464  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
7465 
7466  file_log ("file_numerable_add_page",
7467  "file %d|%d added new page %d|%d to user table; "
7468  "updated vpid_last_user_page_ftab in header page %d|%d, prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d ",
7469  VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self), VPID_AS_ARGS (&vpid_ftab_new),
7470  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_fhead, &save_lsa));
7471 
7472  /* initialize new page table */
7473  extdata_user_page_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
7474  file_extdata_init (sizeof (VPID), DB_PAGESIZE, extdata_user_page_ftab);
7475 
7476  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
7477  {
7478  /* log changes. */
7479  pgbuf_log_new_page (thread_p, page_ftab, file_extdata_size (extdata_user_page_ftab), PAGE_FTAB);
7480  }
7481  else
7482  {
7483  /* just set dirty */
7484  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_ftab, DONT_FREE);
7485  }
7486  }
7487 
7488  assert (!file_extdata_is_full (extdata_user_page_ftab));
7489  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_extdata);
7490  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
7491  {
7492  /* log changes */
7493  file_log_extdata_add (thread_p, extdata_user_page_ftab, page_extdata,
7494  file_extdata_item_count (extdata_user_page_ftab), 1, vpid);
7495  }
7496  else
7497  {
7498  /* just set dirty */
7499  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_extdata, DONT_FREE);
7500  }
7501  file_extdata_append (extdata_user_page_ftab, vpid);
7502 
7503  file_log ("file_numerable_add_page",
7504  "add page %d|%d to position %d in file %d|%d, page %d|%d, prev_lsa = %lld|%d, crt_lsa = %lld|%d \n"
7505  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("last user page table component") FILE_HEAD_FULL_MSG, VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid),
7506  file_extdata_item_count (extdata_user_page_ftab) - 1, VFID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->self),
7507  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_extdata, &save_lsa), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_user_page_ftab),
7508  FILE_HEAD_FULL_AS_ARGS (fhead));
7509 
7510  /* done */
7511  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
7512 
7513 exit:
7514  if (page_ftab != NULL)
7515  {
7516  assert (page_ftab != page_fhead);
7517  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab);
7518  }
7519 
7520  return error_code;
7521 }
7522 
7523 /*
7524  * file_extdata_find_nth_vpid () - Function callable by file_extdata_apply_funcs. An optimal way of finding nth page
7525  * when there is no page marked as deleted.
7526  *
7527  * return : NO_ERROR
7528  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
7529  * extdata (in) : Extensible data
7530  * stop (in) : Output true when search must be stopped
7531  * args (in) : FILE_FIND_NTH_CONTEXT *
7532  */
7533 static int
7534 file_extdata_find_nth_vpid (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, bool * stop, void *args)
7535 {
7536  FILE_FIND_NTH_CONTEXT *find_nth_context = (FILE_FIND_NTH_CONTEXT *) args;
7537  int count_vpid = file_extdata_item_count (extdata);
7538 
7539  if (count_vpid <= find_nth_context->nth)
7540  {
7541  /* not in this extensible data. continue searching. */
7542  find_nth_context->nth -= count_vpid;
7543  find_nth_context->first_index += count_vpid;
7544  }
7545  else
7546  {
7547  /* nth VPID is in this extensible data. get it and stop searching */
7548  VPID_COPY (find_nth_context->vpid_nth, (VPID *) file_extdata_at (extdata, find_nth_context->nth));
7549  assert (!FILE_USER_PAGE_IS_MARKED_DELETED (find_nth_context->vpid_nth));
7550  *stop = true;
7551  }
7552 
7553  return NO_ERROR;
7554 }
7555 
7556 /*
7557  * file_extdata_find_nth_vpid_and_skip_marked () - Function callable by file_extdata_apply_funcs. Used to find the nth
7558  * VPID not marked as deleted (numerable files).
7559  *
7560  * return : NO_ERROR
7561  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
7562  * data (in) : Pointer in user page table (VPID *).
7563  * index (in) : Not used.
7564  * stop (out) : Output true when nth page is reached.
7565  * args (in/out) : FILE_FIND_NTH_CONTEXT *
7566  */
7567 static int
7568 file_extdata_find_nth_vpid_and_skip_marked (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p,
7569  const void *data, int index, bool * stop, void *args)
7570 {
7571  FILE_FIND_NTH_CONTEXT *find_nth_context = (FILE_FIND_NTH_CONTEXT *) args;
7572  VPID *vpidp = (VPID *) data;
7573 
7574  if (FILE_USER_PAGE_IS_MARKED_DELETED (vpidp))
7575  {
7576  /* skip marked deleted */
7577  return NO_ERROR;
7578  }
7579 
7580  if (find_nth_context->nth == 0)
7581  {
7582  /* found nth */
7583  *find_nth_context->vpid_nth = *vpidp;
7584  *stop = true;
7585  }
7586  else
7587  {
7588  /* update nth */
7589  find_nth_context->nth--;
7590  }
7591 
7592  return NO_ERROR;
7593 }
7594 
7595 /*
7596  * file_numerable_find_nth () - Find nth page VPID in numerable file.
7597  *
7598  * return : Error code
7599  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
7600  * vfid (in) : File identifier
7601  * nth (in) : Index of page
7602  * auto_alloc (in) : True to allow file extension.
7603  * f_init (in) : init page function (must not be NULL for permanent page allocation)
7604  * f_init_args (in) : arguments for init page function
7605  * vpid_nth (out) : VPID at index
7606  */
7607 int
7608 file_numerable_find_nth (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, int nth, bool auto_alloc,
7609  FILE_INIT_PAGE_FUNC f_init, void *f_init_args, VPID * vpid_nth)
7610 {
7611  VPID vpid_fhead;
7612  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
7613  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
7614  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_user_page_ftab = NULL;
7615  PAGE_PTR page_ftab_start = NULL;
7616  PAGE_PTR page_ftab_nth_location = NULL;
7617  FILE_FIND_NTH_CONTEXT find_nth_context;
7618  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7619 
7620  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
7621  assert (nth >= 0);
7622  assert (vpid_nth != NULL);
7623 
7624  VPID_SET_NULL (vpid_nth);
7625 
7626  /* how it works:
7627  * iterate through user page table, skipping pages marked as deleted, and decrement counter until it reaches 0.
7628  * save the VPID found on the nth position.
7629  * if there are no marked deleted pages, we can skip entire extensible data components and go directly to nth page.
7630  */
7631 
7632  /* get file header */
7633  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
7634  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
7635  if (page_fhead == NULL)
7636  {
7637  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
7638  goto exit;
7639  }
7640  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
7641  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
7642  assert (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead));
7643  assert (nth < fhead->n_page_user || (auto_alloc && nth == fhead->n_page_user));
7644 
7645  if (auto_alloc && nth == (fhead->n_page_user - fhead->n_page_mark_delete))
7646  {
7647  /* we need new page */
7648  /* todo: can this be simplified? */
7649  error_code = pgbuf_promote_read_latch (thread_p, &page_fhead, PGBUF_PROMOTE_SHARED_READER);
7650  if (error_code == ER_PAGE_LATCH_PROMOTE_FAIL)
7651  {
7652  /* re-fix page */
7653  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
7654  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
7655  if (page_fhead == NULL)
7656  {
7657  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
7658  goto exit;
7659  }
7660  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
7661  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
7662  if (auto_alloc && nth == (fhead->n_page_user - fhead->n_page_mark_delete))
7663  {
7664  error_code = file_alloc (thread_p, vfid, f_init, f_init_args, vpid_nth, NULL);
7665  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7666  {
7667  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7668  }
7669  goto exit;
7670  }
7671  }
7672  else if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7673  {
7674  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7675  goto exit;
7676  }
7677  else if (page_fhead == NULL)
7678  {
7679  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
7680  goto exit;
7681  }
7682 
7683  error_code = file_alloc (thread_p, vfid, f_init, f_init_args, vpid_nth, NULL);
7684  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7685  {
7686  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7687  }
7688 
7689  goto exit;
7690  }
7691 
7692  /* iterate in user page table */
7693  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_user_page_ftab);
7694  find_nth_context.vpid_nth = vpid_nth;
7695  find_nth_context.nth = nth;
7696 
7697  if (fhead->n_page_mark_delete > 0)
7698  {
7699  /* we don't know where the marked deleted pages are... we need to iterate through all pages and skip the marked
7700  * deleted. */
7701  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_user_page_ftab, NULL, NULL,
7702  file_extdata_find_nth_vpid_and_skip_marked, &find_nth_context, false,
7703  NULL, NULL);
7704  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7705  {
7706  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7707  goto exit;
7708  }
7709  }
7710  else
7711  {
7712  if (FILE_CACHE_LAST_FIND_NTH (fhead) && !VPID_ISNULL (&fhead->vpid_find_nth_last)
7713  && !VPID_EQ (&vpid_fhead, &fhead->vpid_find_nth_last) && nth >= fhead->first_index_find_nth_last)
7714  {
7715  /* start searching from last search location */
7716  page_ftab_start =
7717  pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &fhead->vpid_find_nth_last, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
7718  if (page_ftab_start == NULL)
7719  {
7720  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
7721  goto exit;
7722  }
7723  extdata_user_page_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab_start;
7724  find_nth_context.first_index = fhead->first_index_find_nth_last;
7725  find_nth_context.nth -= fhead->first_index_find_nth_last;
7726  }
7727  else
7728  {
7729  /* no last search location or it could not be used. start searching from the beginning. */
7730  find_nth_context.first_index = 0;
7731  }
7732  /* we can go directly to the right VPID. */
7733  error_code = file_extdata_apply_funcs (thread_p, extdata_user_page_ftab, file_extdata_find_nth_vpid,
7734  &find_nth_context, NULL, NULL, false, NULL, &page_ftab_nth_location);
7735  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7736  {
7737  ASSERT_ERROR ();
7738  goto exit;
7739  }
7740 
7741  if (FILE_CACHE_LAST_FIND_NTH (fhead))
7742  {
7743  /* note that we consider this file cannot be accessed concurrently. therefore we do not promote to write latch
7744  * and we do not set page dirty to update the cached search location. */
7745  if (page_ftab_nth_location == NULL)
7746  {
7747  /* it was found in the starting page */
7748  page_ftab_nth_location = page_ftab_start != NULL ? page_ftab_start : page_fhead;
7749  }
7750  pgbuf_get_vpid (page_ftab_nth_location, &fhead->vpid_find_nth_last);
7751  fhead->first_index_find_nth_last = find_nth_context.first_index;
7752 
7753  file_log ("file_numerable_find_nth", "update fhead.fist_index_find_nth_last to %d "
7754  "and fhead->vpid_find_nth_last to %d|%d while searching nth=%d in file %d|%d",
7755  fhead->first_index_find_nth_last, VPID_AS_ARGS (&fhead->vpid_find_nth_last), nth,
7756  VFID_AS_ARGS (vfid));
7757  }
7758  }
7759 
7760  if (VPID_ISNULL (vpid_nth))
7761  {
7762  /* should not happen */
7763  assert_release (false);
7764  error_code = ER_FAILED;
7765  goto exit;
7766  }
7767 
7768  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
7769 
7770 exit:
7771  if (page_ftab_nth_location != NULL && page_ftab_nth_location != page_ftab_start
7772  && page_ftab_nth_location != page_fhead)
7773  {
7774  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab_nth_location);
7775  }
7776  if (page_ftab_start != NULL)
7777  {
7778  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab_start);
7779  }
7780  if (page_fhead != NULL)
7781  {
7782  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
7783  }
7784 
7785  return error_code;
7786 }
7787 
7788 /*
7789  * file_rv_user_page_mark_delete () - Recover page mark delete.
7790  *
7791  * return : Error code
7792  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
7793  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
7794  */
7795 int
7796 file_rv_user_page_mark_delete (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
7797 {
7798  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = rcv->pgptr;
7799  VPID *vpid_ptr = NULL;
7800 
7801  vpid_ptr = (VPID *) (page_ftab + rcv->offset);
7802  assert (!FILE_USER_PAGE_IS_MARKED_DELETED (vpid_ptr));
7803  FILE_USER_PAGE_MARK_DELETED (vpid_ptr);
7804 
7805  file_log ("file_rv_user_page_mark_delete",
7806  "marked deleted vpid %d|%d in page %d|%d lsa %lld|%d at offset %d",
7807  VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_ptr), PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_ftab), rcv->offset);
7808 
7809  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_ftab, DONT_FREE);
7810  return NO_ERROR;
7811 }
7812 
7813 /*
7814  * file_rv_user_page_unmark_delete_logical () - Recover page unmark delete (logical)
7815  *
7816  * return : Error code
7817  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
7818  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
7819  */
7820 int
7821 file_rv_user_page_unmark_delete_logical (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
7822 {
7823  PAGE_PTR page_fhead;
7824  PAGE_PTR page_ftab;
7825  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
7826  VFID *vfid;
7827  VPID *vpid;
7828  VPID *vpid_in_table;
7829  VPID vpid_fhead;
7830  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_user_page_ftab;
7831  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
7832  bool found = false;
7833  int position = -1;
7834  int offset = 0;
7835  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
7836  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7837 
7838  /* how it works
7839  * when we mark a page as deleted in user page table and unfix file header, the user page table can be modified by
7840  * concurrent transactions. if allocations are always appended at the end, deallocations will remove VPID's from
7841  * user page table and can sometime merge pages. which means that by the time we get to undo our change, the location
7842  * of this page becomes uncertain.
7843  *
7844  * therefore, removing mark for deletion should lookup VPID in table.
7845  */
7846 
7847  vfid = (VFID *) (rcv->data + offset);
7848  offset += sizeof (*vfid);
7849 
7850  vpid = (VPID *) (rcv->data + offset);
7851  offset += sizeof (*vpid);
7852 
7853  assert (offset == rcv->length);
7854 
7855  vpid_fhead.volid = vfid->volid;
7856  vpid_fhead.pageid = vfid->fileid;
7857  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
7858  if (page_fhead == NULL)
7859  {
7860  /* Should not be interrupted. */
7861  assert_release (false);
7862  return ER_FAILED;
7863  }
7864 
7865  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
7866 
7867  assert (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead));
7868  assert (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
7869 
7870  /* search for VPID in user page table */
7871  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_user_page_ftab);
7872  error_code =
7873  file_extdata_search_item (thread_p, &extdata_user_page_ftab, vpid,
7874  file_compare_vpids, false, true, &found, &position, &page_ftab);
7875  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
7876  {
7877  /* errors not expected during recovery. */
7878  assert_release (false);
7879  goto exit;
7880  }
7881  if (!found)
7882  {
7883  /* should be found. */
7884  assert_release (false);
7885  error_code = ER_FAILED;
7886  goto exit;
7887  }
7888 
7889  /* go to VPID in current extensible data */
7890  vpid_in_table = (VPID *) file_extdata_at (extdata_user_page_ftab, position);
7891  assert (FILE_USER_PAGE_IS_MARKED_DELETED (vpid_in_table));
7892 
7893  FILE_USER_PAGE_CLEAR_MARK_DELETED (vpid_in_table);
7894  assert (VPID_EQ (vpid, vpid_in_table));
7895 
7896  /* compensate logging. */
7897  addr.pgptr = page_ftab != NULL ? page_ftab : page_fhead;
7898  addr.offset = (PGLENGTH) (((char *) vpid_in_table) - addr.pgptr);
7899  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (addr.pgptr);
7900  log_append_compensate (thread_p, RVFL_USER_PAGE_MARK_DELETE_COMPENSATE, pgbuf_get_vpid_ptr (addr.pgptr), addr.offset,
7901  addr.pgptr, 0, NULL, LOG_FIND_CURRENT_TDES (thread_p));
7902 
7903  file_log ("file_rv_user_page_unmark_delete_logical",
7904  "unmark delete vpid %d|%d in file %d|%d, page %d|%d, "
7905  "prev_lsa %lld|%d, crt_lsa %lld|%d, at offset %d",
7906  VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_in_table), VFID_AS_ARGS (vfid), PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (addr.pgptr, &save_lsa),
7907  addr.offset);
7908 
7909  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, addr.pgptr, DONT_FREE);
7910 
7911  /* done */
7912  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
7913 
7914 exit:
7915  if (page_ftab != NULL)
7916  {
7917  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab);
7918  }
7919  if (page_fhead != NULL)
7920  {
7921  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
7922  }
7923  return error_code;
7924 }
7925 
7926 /*
7927  * file_rv_user_page_unmark_delete_physical () - Recover page unmark delete (physical)
7928  *
7929  * return : Error code
7930  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
7931  * rcv (in) : Recovery data
7932  */
7933 int
7934 file_rv_user_page_unmark_delete_physical (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
7935 {
7936  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = rcv->pgptr;
7937  VPID *vpid_ptr = NULL;
7938 
7939  /* note: this is used to compensate undo of mark delete. this time the location of VPID is known */
7940 
7941  vpid_ptr = (VPID *) (page_ftab + rcv->offset);
7942  assert (FILE_USER_PAGE_IS_MARKED_DELETED (vpid_ptr));
7943 
7944  FILE_USER_PAGE_CLEAR_MARK_DELETED (vpid_ptr);
7945 
7946  file_log ("file_rv_user_page_unmark_delete_physical",
7947  "unmark delete vpid %d|%d in page %d|%d, lsa %lld|%d, "
7948  "at offset %d", VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_ptr), PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (page_ftab), rcv->offset);
7949 
7950  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_ftab, DONT_FREE);
7951  return NO_ERROR;
7952 }
7953 
7954 /*
7955  * file_table_check_page_is_in_sectors () - FILE_EXTDATA_ITEM_FUNC to check user page table is in one of the sectors
7956  *
7957  * return : error code
7958  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
7959  * data (in) : user page table entry
7960  * index (in) : index of user page table entry
7961  * stop (in) : not used
7962  * args (in) : FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR *
7963  */
7964 static int
7965 file_table_check_page_is_in_sectors (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const void *data, int index, bool * stop, void *args)
7966 {
7967  FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR *collector = (FILE_VSID_COLLECTOR *) args;
7968  VPID vpid = *(VPID *) data;
7969  VSID vsid_of_vpid;
7970 
7971  FILE_USER_PAGE_CLEAR_MARK_DELETED (&vpid);
7972  VSID_FROM_VPID (&vsid_of_vpid, &vpid);
7973 
7974  if (bsearch (&vsid_of_vpid, collector->vsids, collector->n_vsids, sizeof (VSID), disk_compare_vsids) == NULL)
7975  {
7976  /* not found! */
7977  assert_release (false);
7978  return ER_FAILED;
7979  }
7980  return NO_ERROR;
7981 }
7982 
7983 /*
7984  * file_numerable_truncate () - truncate numerable files to a smaller number of pages
7985  *
7986  * return : error code
7987  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
7988  * vfid (in) : file identifier
7989  * npages (in) : desired number of pages
7990  */
7991 int
7992 file_numerable_truncate (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, DKNPAGES npages)
7993 {
7994  VPID vpid_fhead;
7995  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
7996  FILE_HEADER *fhead;
7997  VPID vpid;
7998  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
7999 
8000  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
8001  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
8002  if (page_fhead == NULL)
8003  {
8004  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
8005  return ER_FAILED;
8006  }
8007  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
8008 
8009  if (!FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead))
8010  {
8011  /* cannot truncate */
8012  assert_release (false);
8013  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8014  goto exit;
8015  }
8016 
8017  if (fhead->n_page_mark_delete != 0)
8018  {
8019  /* I am not sure what we should do in this case. We give up truncating and in debug it will crash. */
8020  assert (false);
8021  return NO_ERROR;
8022  }
8023 
8024  while (fhead->n_page_user > npages)
8025  {
8026  /* maybe this can be done in a more optimal way... but for now it will have to do */
8027  error_code = file_numerable_find_nth (thread_p, vfid, npages, false, NULL, NULL, &vpid);
8028  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8029  {
8030  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8031  goto exit;
8032  }
8033  error_code = file_dealloc (thread_p, vfid, &vpid, fhead->type);
8034  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8035  {
8036  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8037  goto exit;
8038  }
8039  }
8040  assert (fhead->n_page_user == npages);
8041  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
8042 
8043 exit:
8044  if (page_fhead != NULL)
8045  {
8046  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
8047  }
8048  return error_code;
8049 }
8050 
8051 /************************************************************************/
8052 /* Temporary files section. */
8053 /************************************************************************/
8054 
8055 /*
8056  * file_temp_alloc () - Allocate a new page in temporary file.
8057  *
8058  * return : Error code
8059  * thread_p (in) : Thread entry
8060  * page_fhead (in) : File header page
8061  * alloc_type (in) : User/table page
8062  * vpid_alloc_out (out) : Output allocated page VPID.
8063  */
8064 static int
8065 file_temp_alloc (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_fhead, FILE_ALLOC_TYPE alloc_type, VPID * vpid_alloc_out)
8066 {
8067  FILE_HEADER *fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
8068  VPID vpid_fhead;
8069  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab = NULL;
8070  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
8071  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *partsect = NULL;
8072  bool was_empty = false;
8073  bool is_full = false;
8074  /* we don't have rollback, so don't interrupt */
8075  bool save_check_interrupt = logtb_set_check_interrupt (thread_p, false);
8076  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
8077 
8078  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
8079  assert (FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead));
8080  assert (page_fhead != NULL);
8081  assert (vpid_alloc_out != NULL);
8082 
8083  /* how it works
8084  * temporary files, compared to permanent files, have a simplified design. they do not keep two different tables
8085  * (partial and full). they only keep the partial table, and when sectors become full, they remain in the partial
8086  * table.
8087  * the second difference is that temporary files never deallocate pages. since they are temporary, and soon to be
8088  * freed (or cached for reuse), there is no point in deallocating pages.
8089  * the simplified design was chosen because temporary files are never logged. and it is hard to undo changes without
8090  * logging when errors happen (e.g. interrupted transaction).
8091  *
8092  * all we have to do to allocate a page is to try to allocate from last used sector. if that sector is full, advance
8093  * to next sector. if no new sectors, reserve a new one. that's all.
8094  */
8095 
8096  file_log ("file_temp_alloc", "%s", FILE_ALLOC_TYPE_STRING (alloc_type));
8097 
8098  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (&fhead->self, &vpid_fhead);
8099 
8100  /* get page for last allocated partial table */
8101  if (VPID_EQ (&vpid_fhead, &fhead->vpid_last_temp_alloc))
8102  {
8103  /* partial table in header */
8104  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
8105  }
8106  else
8107  {
8108  page_ftab =
8109  pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &fhead->vpid_last_temp_alloc, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
8110  if (page_ftab == NULL)
8111  {
8112  assert_release (false);
8113  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8114  goto exit;
8115  }
8116  extdata_part_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
8117  }
8118 
8119  if (fhead->n_page_free == 0)
8120  {
8121  /* expand file by one sector */
8122  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR partsect_new = FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR_INITIALIZER;
8123 
8124  /* reserve a sector */
8125  error_code =
8126  disk_reserve_sectors (thread_p, DB_TEMPORARY_DATA_PURPOSE, fhead->volid_last_expand, 1, &partsect_new.vsid);
8127  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8128  {
8129  assert_release (false);
8130  goto exit;
8131  }
8132 
8133  file_log ("file_temp_alloc",
8134  "no free pages" FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_MSG "\texpand file with VSID = %d|%d ",
8135  FILE_HEAD_ALLOC_AS_ARGS (fhead), VSID_AS_ARGS (&partsect_new.vsid));
8136 
8137  assert (extdata_part_ftab != NULL);
8138  if (file_extdata_is_full (extdata_part_ftab))
8139  {
8140  /* we need a new page. */
8141  /* we will use first page of newly reserved sector. */
8142  VPID vpid_ftab_new;
8143  PAGE_PTR page_ftab_new = NULL;
8144 
8145  vpid_ftab_new.volid = partsect_new.vsid.volid;
8146  vpid_ftab_new.pageid = SECTOR_FIRST_PAGEID (partsect_new.vsid.sectid);
8147  file_partsect_set_bit (&partsect_new, 0);
8148 
8149  /* fix new file table page */
8150  page_ftab_new = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_ftab_new, NEW_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
8151  if (page_ftab_new == NULL)
8152  {
8153  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8154 
8155  /* todo: unreserve sector */
8156  goto exit;
8157  }
8158  pgbuf_set_page_ptype (thread_p, page_ftab_new, PAGE_FTAB);
8159 
8160  /* set link to previous page. */
8161  VPID_COPY (&extdata_part_ftab->vpid_next, &vpid_ftab_new);
8162 
8163  /* we don't need old file table page anymore */
8164  assert (page_ftab != page_fhead);
8165  if (page_ftab != NULL)
8166  {
8167  pgbuf_set_dirty_and_free (thread_p, page_ftab);
8168  }
8169 
8170  VPID_COPY (&fhead->vpid_last_temp_alloc, &vpid_ftab_new);
8171  fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc = 0;
8172  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
8173 
8174  page_ftab = page_ftab_new;
8175  extdata_part_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
8176  file_extdata_init (sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR), DB_PAGESIZE, extdata_part_ftab);
8177 
8178  file_log ("file_temp_alloc",
8179  "used newly reserved sector's first page %d|%d for partial table.", VPID_AS_ARGS (&vpid_ftab_new));
8180 
8181  /* update temporary file stats - DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES -1 reserved pages and 1 file table page. */
8182  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_reserved, DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES - 1);
8183  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_ftab, 1);
8184  }
8185  else
8186  {
8187  /* update temporary file stats - DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES reserved pages */
8188  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_reserved, DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES);
8189  }
8190  assert (!file_extdata_is_full (extdata_part_ftab));
8191  assert (file_extdata_item_count (extdata_part_ftab) == fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc);
8192  file_extdata_append (extdata_part_ftab, &partsect_new);
8193 
8194  fhead->n_sector_partial++;
8195  fhead->n_sector_total++;
8196  fhead->n_page_free += DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES;
8197  fhead->n_page_total += DISK_SECTOR_NPAGES;
8198  if (partsect_new.page_bitmap == FILE_EMPTY_PAGE_BITMAP)
8199  {
8200  fhead->n_sector_empty++;
8201  }
8202  else
8203  {
8204  fhead->n_page_free--;
8205  fhead->n_page_ftab++;
8206  }
8207 
8208  file_log ("file_temp_alloc",
8209  "new partial sector added to partial extensible data:\n"
8210  FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("newly reserved sector")
8211  FILE_EXTDATA_MSG ("last partial table component"),
8212  FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (&partsect_new), FILE_EXTDATA_AS_ARGS (extdata_part_ftab));
8213  }
8214  assert (fhead->n_page_free > 0);
8215 
8216  if (fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc == file_extdata_item_count (extdata_part_ftab))
8217  {
8218  VPID vpid_next;
8219 
8220  /* must be full */
8221  assert (file_extdata_is_full (extdata_part_ftab));
8222  /* we must have another extensible data */
8223  assert (!VPID_ISNULL (&extdata_part_ftab->vpid_next));
8224 
8225  /* move allocation cursor to next partial table page */
8226  vpid_next = extdata_part_ftab->vpid_next;
8227  if (page_ftab != NULL)
8228  {
8229  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
8230  }
8231  page_ftab = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
8232  if (page_ftab == NULL)
8233  {
8234  assert_release (false);
8235  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8236  goto exit;
8237  }
8238  extdata_part_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
8239 
8240  fhead->vpid_last_temp_alloc = vpid_next;
8241  fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc = 0;
8242  }
8243 
8244  assert (extdata_part_ftab != NULL);
8245  assert (fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc < file_extdata_item_count (extdata_part_ftab));
8246  partsect = (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) file_extdata_at (extdata_part_ftab, fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc);
8247 
8248  /* Allocate the page. */
8249  was_empty = file_partsect_is_empty (partsect);
8250  if (!file_partsect_alloc (partsect, vpid_alloc_out, NULL))
8251  {
8252  /* full sector? that is unexpected. we must have a logic error. */
8253  assert_release (false);
8254  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8255  goto exit;
8256  }
8257  if (file_partsect_is_full (partsect))
8258  {
8259  is_full = true;
8260  fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc++;
8261  }
8262 
8263  file_header_alloc (fhead, alloc_type, was_empty, is_full);
8264  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
8265 
8266  file_log ("file_temp_alloc", "%s %d|%d successful. \n" FILE_HEAD_FULL_MSG
8267  FILE_PARTSECT_MSG ("partial sector after alloc"),
8268  FILE_ALLOC_TYPE_STRING (alloc_type),
8269  VPID_AS_ARGS (vpid_alloc_out), FILE_HEAD_FULL_AS_ARGS (fhead), FILE_PARTSECT_AS_ARGS (partsect));
8270 
8271  if (page_ftab != NULL)
8272  {
8273  assert (page_ftab != page_fhead);
8274  pgbuf_set_dirty_and_free (thread_p, page_ftab);
8275  }
8276 
8277  /* update temporary file stats */
8278  if (alloc_type == FILE_ALLOC_USER_PAGE)
8279  {
8280  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_user, 1);
8281  }
8282  else
8283  {
8284  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_ftab, 1);
8285  }
8286  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_reserved, -1);
8287 
8288  /* done */
8289  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
8290 
8291 exit:
8292  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
8293  if (page_ftab != NULL)
8294  {
8295  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_ftab);
8296  }
8297  (void) logtb_set_check_interrupt (thread_p, save_check_interrupt);
8298  return error_code;
8299 }
8300 
8301 /*
8302  * file_temp_set_type () - set new type in existing temporary file
8303  *
8304  * return : error code
8305  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
8306  * vfid (in) : file identifier
8307  * ftype (in) : new file type
8308  */
8309 STATIC_INLINE int
8310 file_temp_set_type (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, VFID * vfid, FILE_TYPE ftype)
8311 {
8312  VPID vpid_fhead;
8313  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
8314  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
8315  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
8316 
8317  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
8318  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
8319  if (page_fhead == NULL)
8320  {
8321  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
8322  return error_code;
8323  }
8324  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
8325  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
8326 
8327  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
8328  {
8329  /* we cannot change type */
8330  assert_release (false);
8331  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8332  goto exit;
8333  }
8334 
8335  fhead->type = ftype;
8336  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
8337 
8338 exit:
8339  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
8340  return error_code;
8341 }
8342 
8343 /*
8344  * file_temp_reset_user_pages () - reset all user pages in temporary file.
8345  *
8346  * return : error code
8347  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
8348  * vfid (in) : file identifier
8349  */
8350 static int
8351 file_temp_reset_user_pages (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid)
8352 {
8353  VPID vpid_fhead;
8354  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
8355  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
8356  FILE_FTAB_COLLECTOR collector = FILE_FTAB_COLLECTOR_INITIALIZER;
8357  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_part_ftab = NULL;
8358  PAGE_PTR page_ftab = NULL;
8359  FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *partsect = NULL;
8360  int idx_sect = 0;
8361  VPID vpid_next;
8362  int nsect_part_new;
8363  int nsect_full_new;
8364  int nsect_empty_new;
8365  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_user_page_ftab;
8366  bool save_interrupt;
8367  bool found = false;
8368  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
8369 
8370  /* don't let this be interrupted, because we might ruin the file */
8371  save_interrupt = logtb_set_check_interrupt (thread_p, false);
8372 
8373  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (vfid, &vpid_fhead);
8374  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
8375  if (page_fhead == NULL)
8376  {
8377  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
8378  goto exit;
8379  }
8380  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
8381  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
8382 
8383  if (!FILE_IS_TEMPORARY (fhead))
8384  {
8385  assert_release (false);
8386  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8387  goto exit;
8388  }
8389 
8390  if (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (fhead))
8391  {
8392  /* reset user page table */
8393  FILE_HEADER_GET_USER_PAGE_FTAB (fhead, extdata_user_page_ftab);
8394  VPID_SET_NULL (&extdata_user_page_ftab->vpid_next);
8395  extdata_user_page_ftab->n_items = 0;
8396  fhead->vpid_last_user_page_ftab = vpid_fhead;
8397  fhead->vpid_find_nth_last = vpid_fhead;
8398  fhead->first_index_find_nth_last = 0;
8399  }
8400 
8401  /* collect table pages */
8402  error_code = file_table_collect_ftab_pages (thread_p, page_fhead, false, &collector);
8403  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8404  {
8405  assert_release (false);
8406  goto exit;
8407  }
8408 
8409  /* count partial, full, empty */
8410  nsect_full_new = 0;
8411  for (idx_sect = 0; idx_sect < collector.nsects; idx_sect++)
8412  {
8413  if (collector.partsect_ftab[idx_sect].page_bitmap == FILE_FULL_PAGE_BITMAP)
8414  {
8415  nsect_full_new++;
8416  }
8417  }
8418  nsect_part_new = collector.nsects - nsect_full_new;
8419  nsect_empty_new = fhead->n_sector_total - collector.nsects;
8420  nsect_part_new += nsect_empty_new;
8421 
8422  /* reset partial table sectors, but leave file table pages allocated */
8423  page_ftab = page_fhead;
8424  FILE_HEADER_GET_PART_FTAB (fhead, extdata_part_ftab);
8425  while (true)
8426  {
8427  assert (extdata_part_ftab != NULL);
8428 
8429  for (partsect = (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) file_extdata_start (extdata_part_ftab);
8430  partsect < (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR *) file_extdata_end (extdata_part_ftab); partsect++)
8431  {
8432  /* does it have file table pages? */
8433  found = false;
8434  for (idx_sect = 0; idx_sect < collector.nsects; idx_sect++)
8435  {
8436  if (disk_compare_vsids (&partsect->vsid, &collector.partsect_ftab[idx_sect].vsid) == 0)
8437  {
8438  /* get bitmap from collector */
8439  partsect->page_bitmap = collector.partsect_ftab[idx_sect].page_bitmap;
8440 
8441  /* sector cannot be found again. remove it from collector */
8442  if (idx_sect < collector.nsects - 1)
8443  {
8444  memmove (&collector.partsect_ftab[idx_sect],
8445  &collector.partsect_ftab[idx_sect + 1],
8446  (collector.nsects - 1 - idx_sect) * sizeof (FILE_PARTIAL_SECTOR));
8447  }
8448  collector.nsects--;
8449  found = true;
8450  break;
8451  }
8452  }
8453  if (!found)
8454  {
8455  /* not found in collector, must be empty sector */
8456  partsect->page_bitmap = FILE_EMPTY_PAGE_BITMAP;
8457  }
8458  }
8459 
8460  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_ftab, DONT_FREE);
8461 
8462  vpid_next = extdata_part_ftab->vpid_next;
8463  if (page_ftab != page_fhead)
8464  {
8465  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_ftab);
8466  }
8467  page_ftab = NULL;
8468  if (VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_next))
8469  {
8470  break;
8471  }
8472  page_ftab = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
8473  if (page_ftab == NULL)
8474  {
8475  assert_release (false);
8476  error_code = ER_FAILED;
8477  goto exit;
8478  }
8479  extdata_part_ftab = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_ftab;
8480  }
8481  /* partial table sectors have been reset */
8482 
8483  /* update header */
8484  fhead->n_sector_empty = nsect_empty_new;
8485  fhead->n_sector_partial = nsect_part_new;
8486  fhead->n_sector_full = nsect_full_new;
8487 
8488  /* also update temporary files global stats */
8489  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_ftab, collector.npages - fhead->n_page_ftab);
8490  fhead->n_page_ftab = collector.npages;
8491  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_user, -fhead->n_page_user);
8492  fhead->n_page_user = 0;
8493  ATOMIC_INC_32 (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp.npage_reserved,
8494  fhead->n_page_total - fhead->n_page_ftab - fhead->n_page_free);
8495  fhead->n_page_free = fhead->n_page_total - fhead->n_page_ftab;
8496 
8497  /* reset pointers used for allocations */
8498  fhead->vpid_last_temp_alloc = vpid_fhead;
8499  fhead->offset_to_last_temp_alloc = 0;
8500 
8501  file_log ("file_temp_reset_user_pages", "finished \n" FILE_HEAD_FULL_MSG, FILE_HEAD_FULL_AS_ARGS (fhead));
8502 
8503  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_fhead, DONT_FREE);
8504  /* done */
8505  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
8506 
8507 exit:
8508  assert (page_ftab == NULL);
8509 
8510  if (page_fhead != NULL)
8511  {
8512  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
8513  }
8514 
8515  (void) logtb_set_check_interrupt (thread_p, save_interrupt);
8516 
8517  if (collector.partsect_ftab != NULL)
8518  {
8519  db_private_free (thread_p, collector.partsect_ftab);
8520  }
8521 
8522  return error_code;
8523 }
8524 
8525 /*
8526  * file_temp_preserve () - preserve temporary file
8527  *
8528  * return :
8529  * THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p (in) :
8530  * const VFID * vfid (in) :
8531  */
8532 void
8533 file_temp_preserve (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid)
8534 {
8535  /* to preserve the file, we need to remove it from transaction list */
8536  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *entry = NULL;
8537 
8538  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
8539 
8540  entry = file_tempcache_pop_tran_file (thread_p, vfid);
8541  if (entry == NULL)
8542  {
8543  assert_release (false);
8544  }
8545  else
8546  {
8547  file_tempcache_retire_entry (entry);
8548  }
8549 }
8550 
8551 /************************************************************************/
8552 /* Temporary cache section */
8553 /************************************************************************/
8554 
8555 /*
8556  * file_tempcache_init () - init temporary file cache
8557  *
8558  * return : ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY or NO_ERROR
8559  */
8560 static int
8561 file_tempcache_init (void)
8562 {
8563  int memsize = 0;
8564 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
8565  int ntrans = logtb_get_number_of_total_tran_indices () + 1;
8566 #else
8567  int ntrans = 1;
8568 #endif
8569 
8570  assert (file_Tempcache == NULL);
8571 
8572  /* allocate file_Tempcache */
8573  memsize = sizeof (FILE_TEMPCACHE);
8574  file_Tempcache = (FILE_TEMPCACHE *) malloc (memsize);
8575  if (file_Tempcache == NULL)
8576  {
8577  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, memsize);
8578  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
8579  }
8580 
8581  /* initialize free entry list... used to avoid entry allocation/deallocation */
8582  file_Tempcache->free_entries = NULL;
8583  file_Tempcache->nfree_entries_max = ntrans * 8; /* I set 8 per transaction, maybe there is a better value */
8584  file_Tempcache->nfree_entries = 0;
8585 
8586  /* initialize temporary file cache. we keep two separate lists for numerable and regular files */
8587  file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable = NULL;
8588  file_Tempcache->cached_numerable = NULL;
8589  file_Tempcache->ncached_max = prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_MAX_ENTRIES_IN_TEMP_FILE_CACHE);
8590  file_Tempcache->ncached_not_numerable = 0;
8591  file_Tempcache->ncached_numerable = 0;
8592 
8593  /* initialize mutex used to protect temporary file cache and entry allocation/deallocation */
8594  pthread_mutex_init (&file_Tempcache->mutex, NULL);
8595 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
8596  file_Tempcache->owner_mutex = -1;
8597 #endif
8598 
8599  /* allocate transaction temporary files lists */
8600  memsize = ntrans * sizeof (FILE_TEMPCACHE *);
8601  file_Tempcache->tran_files = (FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY **) malloc (memsize);
8602  if (file_Tempcache->tran_files == NULL)
8603  {
8604  pthread_mutex_destroy (&file_Tempcache->mutex);
8605  free_and_init (file_Tempcache);
8606  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, memsize);
8607  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
8608  }
8609  memset (file_Tempcache->tran_files, 0, memsize);
8610 
8611  /* stats */
8612  memset (&file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp, 0, sizeof (file_Tempcache->spacedb_temp));
8613 
8614  /* all ok */
8615  return NO_ERROR;
8616 }
8617 
8618 /*
8619  * file_tempcache_final () - free temporary files cache resources
8620  *
8621  * return : void
8622  */
8623 static void
8624 file_tempcache_final (void)
8625 {
8626  int tran = 0;
8627  int ntrans;
8628 
8629  if (file_Tempcache == NULL)
8630  {
8631  return;
8632  }
8633 
8634 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
8635  ntrans = logtb_get_number_of_total_tran_indices ();
8636 #else
8637  ntrans = 1;
8638 #endif
8639 
8640  file_tempcache_lock ();
8641 
8642  /* free all transaction lists... they should be empty anyway, but be conservative */
8643  for (tran = 0; tran < ntrans; tran++)
8644  {
8645  if (file_Tempcache->tran_files[tran] != NULL)
8646  {
8647  /* should be empty */
8648  assert (false);
8649  file_tempcache_free_entry_list (&file_Tempcache->tran_files[tran]);
8650  }
8651  }
8652  free_and_init (file_Tempcache->tran_files);
8653 
8654  /* temporary volumes are removed, we don't have to destroy files */
8655  file_tempcache_free_entry_list (&file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable);
8656  file_tempcache_free_entry_list (&file_Tempcache->cached_numerable);
8657 
8658  file_tempcache_free_entry_list (&file_Tempcache->free_entries);
8659 
8660  file_tempcache_unlock ();
8661 
8662  pthread_mutex_destroy (&file_Tempcache->mutex);
8663 
8664  free_and_init (file_Tempcache);
8665 }
8666 
8667 /*
8668  * file_tempcache_free_entry_list () - free entry list and set it to NULL
8669  *
8670  * return : void
8671  * list (in/out) : list to free. it becomes NULL.
8672  */
8673 STATIC_INLINE void
8674 file_tempcache_free_entry_list (FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY ** list)
8675 {
8676  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *entry;
8677  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *next;
8678 
8679  file_tempcache_check_lock ();
8680 
8681  for (entry = *list; entry != NULL; entry = next)
8682  {
8683  next = entry->next;
8684  free (entry);
8685  }
8686  *list = NULL;
8687 }
8688 
8689 /*
8690  * file_tempcache_alloc_entry () - allocate a new file temporary cache entry
8691  *
8692  * return : error code
8693  * entry (out) : entry from free entries or newly allocated
8694  */
8695 STATIC_INLINE int
8696 file_tempcache_alloc_entry (FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY ** entry)
8697 {
8698  file_tempcache_check_lock ();
8699 
8700  if (file_Tempcache->free_entries != NULL)
8701  {
8702  assert (file_Tempcache->nfree_entries > 0);
8703 
8704  *entry = file_Tempcache->free_entries;
8705  file_Tempcache->free_entries = file_Tempcache->free_entries->next;
8706  file_Tempcache->nfree_entries--;
8707  }
8708  else
8709  {
8710  *entry = (FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *) malloc (sizeof (FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY));
8711  if (*entry == NULL)
8712  {
8713  er_set (ER_ERROR_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY, 1, sizeof (FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY));
8714  return ER_OUT_OF_VIRTUAL_MEMORY;
8715  }
8716  }
8717 
8718  (*entry)->next = NULL;
8719  VFID_SET_NULL (&(*entry)->vfid);
8720  (*entry)->ftype = FILE_UNKNOWN_TYPE;
8721 
8722  return NO_ERROR;
8723 }
8724 
8725 /*
8726  * file_tempcache_retire_entry () - retire entry to free entry list (if not maxed) or deallocate
8727  *
8728  * return : void
8729  * entry (in) : retired entry
8730  */
8731 STATIC_INLINE void
8732 file_tempcache_retire_entry (FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY * entry)
8733 {
8734  /* we lock to change free entry list */
8735  file_tempcache_lock ();
8736 
8737  if (file_Tempcache->nfree_entries < file_Tempcache->nfree_entries_max)
8738  {
8739  entry->next = file_Tempcache->free_entries;
8740  file_Tempcache->free_entries = entry;
8741  file_Tempcache->nfree_entries++;
8742  }
8743  else
8744  {
8745  free (entry);
8746  }
8747 
8748  file_tempcache_unlock ();
8749 }
8750 
8751 /*
8752  * file_tempcache_lock () - lock temporary cache mutex
8753  *
8754  * return : void
8755  */
8756 STATIC_INLINE void
8757 file_tempcache_lock (void)
8758 {
8759  assert (file_Tempcache->owner_mutex != thread_get_current_entry_index ());
8760  pthread_mutex_lock (&file_Tempcache->mutex);
8761  assert (file_Tempcache->owner_mutex == -1);
8762 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
8763  file_Tempcache->owner_mutex = thread_get_current_entry_index ();
8764 #endif /* !NDEBUG */
8765 }
8766 
8767 /*
8768  * file_tempcache_unlock () - unlock temporary cache mutex
8769  *
8770  * return : void
8771  */
8772 STATIC_INLINE void
8773 file_tempcache_unlock (void)
8774 {
8775  assert (file_Tempcache->owner_mutex == thread_get_current_entry_index ());
8776 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
8777  file_Tempcache->owner_mutex = -1;
8778 #endif /* !NDEBUG */
8779  pthread_mutex_unlock (&file_Tempcache->mutex);
8780 }
8781 
8782 /*
8783  * file_tempcache_check_lock () - check temporary cache mutex is locked (for debug)
8784  *
8785  * return : void
8786  */
8787 STATIC_INLINE void
8788 file_tempcache_check_lock (void)
8789 {
8790  assert (file_Tempcache->owner_mutex == thread_get_current_entry_index ());
8791 }
8792 
8793 /*
8794  * file_tempcache_get () - get a file from temporary file cache
8795  *
8796  * return : error code
8797  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
8798  * ftype (in) : file type
8799  * numerable (in) : true for numerable file, false for regular file
8800  * entry (out) : always output an temporary cache entry. caller must check entry VFID to find if cached file was used
8801  */
8802 STATIC_INLINE int
8803 file_tempcache_get (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_TYPE ftype, bool numerable, FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY ** entry)
8804 {
8805  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
8806 
8807  assert (entry != NULL && *entry == NULL);
8808 
8809  file_tempcache_lock ();
8810 
8811  *entry = numerable ? file_Tempcache->cached_numerable : file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable;
8812  if (*entry != NULL && (*entry)->ftype != ftype)
8813  {
8814  /* change type */
8815  error_code = file_temp_set_type (thread_p, &(*entry)->vfid, ftype);
8816  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8817  {
8818  /* could not change it, give up */
8819  *entry = NULL;
8820  }
8821  else
8822  {
8823  (*entry)->ftype = ftype;
8824  }
8825  }
8826 
8827  if (*entry != NULL)
8828  {
8829  /* remove from cache */
8830  if (numerable)
8831  {
8832  assert (*entry == file_Tempcache->cached_numerable);
8833  assert (file_Tempcache->ncached_numerable > 0);
8834 
8835  file_Tempcache->cached_numerable = file_Tempcache->cached_numerable->next;
8836  file_Tempcache->ncached_numerable--;
8837  }
8838  else
8839  {
8840  assert (*entry == file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable);
8841  assert (file_Tempcache->ncached_not_numerable > 0);
8842 
8843  file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable = file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable->next;
8844  file_Tempcache->ncached_not_numerable--;
8845  }
8846 
8847  (*entry)->next = NULL;
8848 
8849  file_log ("file_tempcache_get",
8850  "found in cache temporary file entry "
8851  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_MSG ", %s\n" FILE_TEMPCACHE_MSG,
8852  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_AS_ARGS (*entry), numerable ? "numerable" : "regular", FILE_TEMPCACHE_AS_ARGS);
8853 
8854  file_tempcache_unlock ();
8855  return NO_ERROR;
8856  }
8857 
8858  /* not from cache, get a new entry */
8859  error_code = file_tempcache_alloc_entry (entry);
8860  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
8861  {
8862  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8863  file_tempcache_unlock ();
8864  return error_code;
8865  }
8866 
8867  /* init new entry */
8868  assert (*entry != NULL);
8869  (*entry)->next = NULL;
8870  (*entry)->ftype = ftype;
8871  VFID_SET_NULL (&(*entry)->vfid);
8872 
8873  file_tempcache_unlock ();
8874 
8875  return NO_ERROR;
8876 }
8877 
8878 /*
8879  * file_tempcache_check_duplicate () - check file cache whether it already has the entry to be added
8880  *
8881  * return : true if file is already in file cache, otherwise false
8882  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
8883  * entry (in) : entry of temporary file to be added to file cache
8884  * is_numerable(in) : is numerable temporary file
8885  *
8886  * note it is a debugging function.
8887  */
8888 static bool
8889 file_tempcache_check_duplicate (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY * entry, bool is_numerable)
8890 {
8891  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *p;
8892 
8893  assert (entry != NULL);
8894  assert (!VFID_ISNULL (&entry->vfid));
8895 
8896  if (is_numerable)
8897  {
8898  for (p = file_Tempcache->cached_numerable; p != NULL; p = p->next)
8899  {
8900  if (VFID_EQ (&p->vfid, &entry->vfid))
8901  {
8902  assert (!VFID_EQ (&p->vfid, &entry->vfid));
8903  return true;
8904  }
8905  }
8906  }
8907  else
8908  {
8909  for (p = file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable; p != NULL; p = p->next)
8910  {
8911  if (VFID_EQ (&p->vfid, &entry->vfid))
8912  {
8913  assert (!VFID_EQ (&p->vfid, &entry->vfid));
8914  return true;
8915  }
8916  }
8917  }
8918 
8919  return false;
8920 }
8921 
8922 /*
8923  * file_tempcache_put () - put entry to file cache (if cache is not full and if file passes vetting)
8924  *
8925  * return : true if file was cached, false otherwise
8926  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
8927  * entry (in) : entry of retired temporary file
8928  */
8929 STATIC_INLINE bool
8930 file_tempcache_put (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY * entry)
8931 {
8932  FILE_HEADER fhead;
8933 
8934  assert (entry != NULL);
8935  assert (!VFID_ISNULL (&entry->vfid));
8936  assert (entry->next == NULL);
8937 
8938  fhead.n_page_user = -1;
8939  if (file_header_copy (thread_p, &entry->vfid, &fhead) != NO_ERROR
8940  || fhead.n_page_user > prm_get_integer_value (PRM_ID_MAX_PAGES_IN_TEMP_FILE_CACHE))
8941  {
8942  /* file not valid for cache */
8943  file_log ("file_tempcache_put",
8944  "could not cache temporary file " FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_MSG
8945  ", fhead->n_page_user = %d ", FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_AS_ARGS (entry), fhead.n_page_user);
8946  return false;
8947  }
8948  /* make sure entry has correct type. */
8949  entry->ftype = fhead.type;
8950 
8951  /* lock temporary cache */
8952  file_tempcache_lock ();
8953 
8954  if (file_Tempcache->ncached_not_numerable + file_Tempcache->ncached_numerable < file_Tempcache->nfree_entries_max)
8955  {
8956  /* cache not full */
8957  assert ((file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable == NULL) == (file_Tempcache->ncached_not_numerable == 0));
8958  assert ((file_Tempcache->cached_numerable == NULL) == (file_Tempcache->ncached_numerable == 0));
8959 
8960  /* reset file */
8961  if (file_temp_reset_user_pages (thread_p, &entry->vfid) != NO_ERROR)
8962  {
8963  /* failed to reset file, we cannot cache it */
8964  ASSERT_ERROR ();
8965 
8966  file_log ("file_tempcache_put",
8967  "could not cache temporary file " FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_MSG
8968  ", error during file reset", FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_AS_ARGS (entry));
8969  file_tempcache_unlock ();
8970  return false;
8971  }
8972 
8973  assert (file_tempcache_check_duplicate (thread_p, entry, FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (&fhead)) == false);
8974 
8975  /* add numerable temporary file to cached numerable file list, regular file to not numerable list */
8976  if (FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (&fhead))
8977  {
8978  entry->next = file_Tempcache->cached_numerable;
8979  file_Tempcache->cached_numerable = entry;
8980  file_Tempcache->ncached_numerable++;
8981  }
8982  else
8983  {
8984  entry->next = file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable;
8985  file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable = entry;
8986  file_Tempcache->ncached_not_numerable++;
8987  }
8988 
8989  file_log ("file_tempcache_put",
8990  "cached temporary file " FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_MSG ", %s\n"
8991  FILE_TEMPCACHE_MSG, FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_AS_ARGS (entry),
8992  FILE_IS_NUMERABLE (&fhead) ? "numerable" : "regular", FILE_TEMPCACHE_AS_ARGS);
8993 
8994  file_tempcache_unlock ();
8995 
8996  /* cached */
8997  return true;
8998  }
8999  else
9000  {
9001  /* cache full */
9002  file_log ("file_tempcache_put",
9003  "could not cache temporary file " FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_MSG
9004  ", temporary cache is full \n" FILE_TEMPCACHE_MSG,
9005  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_AS_ARGS (entry), FILE_TEMPCACHE_AS_ARGS);
9006  file_tempcache_unlock ();
9007  return false;
9008  }
9009 }
9010 
9011 /*
9012  * file_get_tempcache_entry_index () - returns entry index of tempcache
9013  *
9014  * return : int
9015  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9016  */
9017 STATIC_INLINE int
9018 file_get_tempcache_entry_index (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
9019 {
9020 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
9021  return logtb_get_current_tran_index ();
9022 #else
9023  return 0;
9024 #endif
9025 }
9026 
9027 /*
9028  * file_tempcache_drop_tran_temp_files () - drop all temporary files created by current transaction
9029  *
9030  * return : void
9031  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9032  */
9033 void
9034 file_tempcache_drop_tran_temp_files (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
9035 {
9036  if (file_Tempcache->tran_files[file_get_tempcache_entry_index (thread_p)] != NULL)
9037  {
9038  file_log ("file_tempcache_drop_tran_temp_files",
9039  "drop %d transaction temporary files", file_get_tran_num_temp_files (thread_p));
9040  file_tempcache_cache_or_drop_entries (thread_p,
9041  &file_Tempcache->tran_files[file_get_tempcache_entry_index (thread_p)]);
9042  }
9043 }
9044 
9045 /*
9046  * file_tempcache_cache_or_drop_entries () - drop all temporary files in the give entry list
9047  *
9048  * return : void
9049  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9050  * entries (in) : temporary files entry list
9051  */
9052 STATIC_INLINE void
9053 file_tempcache_cache_or_drop_entries (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY ** entries)
9054 {
9055  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *temp_file;
9056  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *next = NULL;
9057 
9058  for (temp_file = *entries; temp_file != NULL; temp_file = next)
9059  {
9060  next = temp_file->next;
9061  temp_file->next = NULL;
9062 
9063  if (!file_tempcache_put (thread_p, temp_file))
9064  {
9065  /* was not cached. destroy the file */
9066  file_log ("file_tempcache_cache_or_drop_entries",
9067  "drop entry " FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_MSG, FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_AS_ARGS (temp_file));
9068  if (file_destroy (thread_p, &temp_file->vfid, true) != NO_ERROR)
9069  {
9070  /* file is leaked */
9071  assert_release (false);
9072  /* ignore error and continue free as many files as possible */
9073  }
9074  file_tempcache_retire_entry (temp_file);
9075  }
9076  }
9077  *entries = NULL;
9078 }
9079 
9080 /*
9081  * file_tempcache_pop_tran_file () - pop entry with the given VFID from transaction list
9082  *
9083  * return : popped entry
9084  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9085  * vfid (in) : file identifier
9086  */
9087 STATIC_INLINE FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *
9088 file_tempcache_pop_tran_file (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid)
9089 {
9090  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY **tran_files_p = &file_Tempcache->tran_files[file_get_tempcache_entry_index (thread_p)];
9091  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *entry = NULL, *prev_entry = NULL;
9092 
9093  for (entry = *tran_files_p; entry != NULL; entry = entry->next)
9094  {
9095  if (VFID_EQ (&entry->vfid, vfid))
9096  {
9097  /* remove entry from transaction list */
9098  if (prev_entry != NULL)
9099  {
9100  prev_entry->next = entry->next;
9101  }
9102  else
9103  {
9104  *tran_files_p = entry->next;
9105  }
9106  entry->next = NULL;
9107 
9108  file_log ("file_tempcache_pop_tran_file", "removed entry " FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_MSG,
9109  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_AS_ARGS (entry));
9110 
9111  return entry;
9112  }
9113  prev_entry = entry;
9114  }
9115 
9116  /* should have found it */
9117  assert_release (false);
9118  return NULL;
9119 }
9120 
9121 /*
9122  * file_tempcache_push_tran_file () - push temporary file entry to transaction list
9123  *
9124  * return : void
9125  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9126  * entry (in) : temporary cache entry
9127  */
9128 STATIC_INLINE void
9129 file_tempcache_push_tran_file (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY * entry)
9130 {
9131  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY **tran_files_p = &file_Tempcache->tran_files[file_get_tempcache_entry_index (thread_p)];
9132 
9133  entry->next = *tran_files_p;
9134  *tran_files_p = entry;
9135 
9136  file_log ("file_tempcache_push_tran_file", "pushed entry " FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_MSG,
9137  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY_AS_ARGS (entry));
9138 }
9139 
9140 /*
9141  * file_get_tran_num_temp_files () - returns the number of temp file entries of the given transaction
9142  *
9143  * return : the number of temp files of the given transaction
9144  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9145  */
9146 int
9147 file_get_tran_num_temp_files (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
9148 {
9149  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY **tran_files_p = &file_Tempcache->tran_files[file_get_tempcache_entry_index (thread_p)];
9150  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *entry;
9151  int num = 0;
9152 
9153  for (entry = *tran_files_p; entry != NULL; entry = entry->next)
9154  {
9155  num++;
9156  }
9157  return num;
9158 }
9159 
9160 /*
9161  * file_tempcache_dump () - dump temporary files cache
9162  *
9163  * return : void
9164  * fp (in) : dump output
9165  */
9166 STATIC_INLINE void
9167 file_tempcache_dump (FILE * fp)
9168 {
9169  FILE_TEMPCACHE_ENTRY *cached_files;
9170 
9171  file_tempcache_lock ();
9172 
9173  fprintf (fp, "DUMPING file manager's temporary files cache.\n");
9174  fprintf (fp,
9175  " max files = %d, regular files count = %d, numerable files count = %d.\n\n",
9176  file_Tempcache->ncached_max, file_Tempcache->ncached_not_numerable, file_Tempcache->ncached_numerable);
9177 
9178  if (file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable != NULL)
9179  {
9180  fprintf (fp, " cached regular files: \n");
9181  for (cached_files = file_Tempcache->cached_not_numerable; cached_files != NULL; cached_files = cached_files->next)
9182  {
9183  fprintf (fp, " VFID = %d|%d, file type = %s \n",
9184  VFID_AS_ARGS (&cached_files->vfid), file_type_to_string (cached_files->ftype));
9185  }
9186  fprintf (fp, "\n");
9187  }
9188  if (file_Tempcache->cached_numerable != NULL)
9189  {
9190  fprintf (fp, " cached numerable files: \n");
9191  for (cached_files = file_Tempcache->cached_numerable; cached_files != NULL; cached_files = cached_files->next)
9192  {
9193  fprintf (fp, " VFID = %d|%d, file type = %s \n",
9194  VFID_AS_ARGS (&cached_files->vfid), file_type_to_string (cached_files->ftype));
9195  }
9196  fprintf (fp, "\n");
9197  }
9198 
9199  file_tempcache_unlock ();
9200 
9201  /* todo: to print transaction temporary files we need some kind of synchronization... right now each transaction
9202  * manages its own list freely. */
9203 }
