9205 /************************************************************************/
9206 /* File tracker section */
9207 /************************************************************************/
9208 
9209 /*
9210  * file_tracker_create () - create file tracker.
9211  *
9212  * return : error code
9213  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9214  * vfid_tracker_out (out) : file tracker VFID
9215  */
9216 int
9217 file_tracker_create (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, VFID * vfid_tracker_out)
9218 {
9219  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9220 
9221  /* start sys op */
9222  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
9223 
9224  error_code = file_create_with_npages (thread_p, FILE_TRACKER, 1, NULL, vfid_tracker_out);
9225  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9226  {
9227  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9228  goto exit;
9229  }
9230  error_code = file_alloc_sticky_first_page (thread_p, vfid_tracker_out, file_tracker_init_page, NULL,
9231  &file_Tracker_vpid, NULL);
9232  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9233  {
9234  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9235  goto exit;
9236  }
9237 
9238  /* success */
9239  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
9240 
9241 exit:
9242 
9243  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9244  {
9245  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
9246  VFID_SET_NULL (vfid_tracker_out);
9247  VPID_SET_NULL (&file_Tracker_vpid);
9248  }
9249  else
9250  {
9251  log_sysop_commit (thread_p);
9252 
9253  VFID_COPY (&file_Tracker_vfid, vfid_tracker_out);
9254  }
9255  return error_code;
9256 }
9257 
9258 /*
9259  * file_tracker_load () - load file tracker
9260  *
9261  * return : error code
9262  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9263  * vfid (in) : file tracker file identifier
9264  */
9265 int
9266 file_tracker_load (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid)
9267 {
9268  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9269 
9270  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
9271 
9272  error_code = file_get_sticky_first_page (thread_p, vfid, &file_Tracker_vpid);
9273  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9274  {
9275  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9276  return error_code;
9277  }
9278 
9279  file_Tracker_vfid = *vfid;
9280 
9281  return NO_ERROR;
9282 }
9283 
9284 /*
9285  * file_tracker_init_page () - initialize new file tracker page
9286  *
9287  * return : NO_ERROR
9288  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9289  * page (in) : new page
9290  * args (in) : ignored
9291  */
9292 static int
9293 file_tracker_init_page (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page, void *args)
9294 {
9295  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page;
9296 
9297  pgbuf_set_page_ptype (thread_p, page, PAGE_FTAB);
9298  file_extdata_init (sizeof (FILE_TRACK_ITEM), DB_PAGESIZE, extdata);
9299  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVPGBUF_NEW_PAGE, NULL, page, (PGLENGTH) PAGE_FTAB, 0, sizeof (*extdata), NULL,
9300  page);
9301  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page, DONT_FREE);
9302 
9303  return NO_ERROR;
9304 }
9305 
9306 /*
9307  * file_tracker_register () - register new file in file tracker
9308  *
9309  * return : error code
9310  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9311  * vfid (in) : file identifier
9312  * ftype (in) : file type
9313  * metadata (in) : meta-data about file (if NULL will be initialized as 0).
9314  */
9315 static int
9316 file_tracker_register (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, FILE_TYPE ftype, FILE_TRACK_METADATA * metadata)
9317 {
9318  FILE_TRACK_ITEM item;
9319  PAGE_PTR page_track_head = NULL;
9320  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9321 
9322  assert (vfid != NULL);
9323  assert (sizeof (item.metadata) == sizeof (item.metadata.metadata_size_tracker));
9324  assert (!VPID_ISNULL (&file_Tracker_vpid));
9325  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
9326 
9327  item.volid = vfid->volid;
9328  item.fileid = vfid->fileid;
9329  item.type = (INT16) ftype;
9330 
9331  if (metadata == NULL)
9332  {
9333  /* set 0 */
9334  item.metadata.metadata_size_tracker = 0;
9335  }
9336  else
9337  {
9338  /* set given metadata */
9339  item.metadata = *metadata;
9340  }
9341 
9342  page_track_head = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
9343  if (page_track_head == NULL)
9344  {
9345  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
9346  return error_code;
9347  }
9348 
9349  error_code = file_tracker_register_internal (thread_p, page_track_head, &item);
9350  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9351  {
9352  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9353  }
9354 
9355  /* unfix head */
9356  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_head);
9357 
9358  /* return error code */
9359  return error_code;
9360 }
9361 
9362 /*
9363  * file_tracker_register_internal () - register new file in file tracker internal function. called by register and
9364  * unregister undo.
9365  *
9366  * return : error code
9367  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9368  * page_track_head (in) : tracker header page
9369  * item (in) : item (with file data)
9370  */
9371 static int
9372 file_tracker_register_internal (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_track_head, const FILE_TRACK_ITEM * item)
9373 {
9374  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata = NULL;
9375  PAGE_PTR page_track_other = NULL;
9376  PAGE_PTR page_extdata = NULL;
9377  bool found;
9378  int pos;
9379  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
9380  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9381 
9382  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
9383 
9384  /* find a space to add new item */
9385  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_track_head;
9386  error_code = file_extdata_find_not_full (thread_p, &extdata, &page_track_other, &found);
9387  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9388  {
9389  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9390  goto exit;
9391  }
9392  page_extdata = page_track_other != NULL ? page_track_other : page_track_head;
9393 
9394  if (!found)
9395  {
9396  /* allocate a new page */
9397  VPID vpid_new_page;
9398 
9399  error_code = file_alloc (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vfid, file_tracker_init_page, NULL, &vpid_new_page, NULL);
9400  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9401  {
9402  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9403  goto exit;
9404  }
9405 
9406  /* add link to new page */
9407  file_log_extdata_set_next (thread_p, extdata, page_extdata, &vpid_new_page);
9408  extdata->vpid_next = vpid_new_page;
9409  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_extdata, DONT_FREE);
9410 
9411  if (page_track_other != NULL)
9412  {
9413  /* no longer needed */
9414  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_track_other);
9415  }
9416 
9417  /* initialize new page */
9418  page_track_other = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_new_page, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
9419  if (page_track_other == NULL)
9420  {
9421  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
9422  goto exit;
9423  }
9424  assert (pgbuf_get_page_ptype (thread_p, page_track_other) == PAGE_FTAB);
9425 
9426  page_extdata = page_track_other;
9427  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_extdata;
9428  }
9429 
9430  assert (page_extdata != NULL);
9431  assert (extdata != NULL);
9432  assert (extdata == (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_extdata);
9433  assert (!file_extdata_is_full (extdata));
9434 
9435  file_extdata_find_ordered (extdata, item, file_compare_track_items, &found, &pos);
9436  if (found)
9437  {
9438  /* impossible */
9439  assert_release (false);
9440  error_code = ER_FAILED;
9441  goto exit;
9442  }
9443 
9444  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_extdata);
9445  file_extdata_insert_at (extdata, pos, 1, item);
9446  file_log_extdata_add (thread_p, extdata, page_extdata, pos, 1, item);
9447  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_extdata, DONT_FREE);
9448 
9449  file_log ("file_tracker_register_internal", "added " FILE_TRACK_ITEM_MSG ", to page %d|%d, prev_lsa = %lld|%d, "
9450  "crt_lsa = %lld|%d, at pos %d ", FILE_TRACK_ITEM_AS_ARGS (item),
9451  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_extdata, &save_lsa), pos);
9452 
9453 exit:
9454  if (page_track_other != NULL)
9455  {
9456  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_other);
9457  }
9458  return error_code;
9459 }
9460 
9461 /*
9462  * file_tracker_unregister () - unregister file from tracker
9463  *
9464  * return : error code
9465  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9466  * vfid (in) : file identifier
9467  */
9468 static int
9469 file_tracker_unregister (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid)
9470 {
9471  PAGE_PTR page_track_head = NULL;
9472  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata = NULL;
9473  FILE_TRACK_ITEM item_inout;
9474  VPID vpid_merged = VPID_INITIALIZER;
9475  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9476 
9477  assert (vfid != NULL && !VFID_ISNULL (vfid));
9478  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
9479 
9480  page_track_head = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
9481  if (page_track_head == NULL)
9482  {
9483  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
9484  return error_code;
9485  }
9486  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_track_head;
9487 
9488  /* we still need to start a system op. */
9489  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
9490 
9491  item_inout.volid = vfid->volid;
9492  item_inout.fileid = vfid->fileid;
9493 
9494  error_code = file_extdata_find_and_remove_item (thread_p, extdata, page_track_head, &item_inout,
9495  file_compare_track_items, true, &item_inout, &vpid_merged);
9496  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9497  {
9498  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9499  goto exit;
9500  }
9501 
9502  if (!VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_merged))
9503  {
9504  /* merged page. deallocate it */
9505  file_log ("file_tracker_unregister", "deallocate page %d|%d ", VPID_AS_ARGS (&vpid_merged));
9506 
9507  error_code = file_dealloc (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vfid, &vpid_merged, FILE_TRACKER);
9508  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9509  {
9510  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9511  goto exit;
9512  }
9513  }
9514 
9515  /* success */
9516  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
9517 
9518 exit:
9519  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9520  {
9521  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
9522  }
9523  else
9524  {
9525  log_sysop_end_logical_undo (thread_p, RVFL_TRACKER_UNREGISTER, NULL, sizeof (item_inout), (char *) &item_inout);
9526  }
9527  if (page_track_head != NULL)
9528  {
9529  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_head);
9530  }
9531  return error_code;
9532 }
9533 
9534 /*
9535  * file_rv_tracker_unregister_undo () - undo the unregister of file. may happen if file_destroy is only partially
9536  * executed. since data inside tracker moved from page to page, the unregister
9537  * operation is logged using system ops with logical undo/compensate.
9538  *
9539  * return : error code
9540  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9541  * rcv (in) : recovery data
9542  */
9543 int
9544 file_rv_tracker_unregister_undo (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
9545 {
9546  PAGE_PTR page_track_head;
9547  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9548 
9549  assert (rcv->length == sizeof (FILE_TRACK_ITEM));
9550 
9551  page_track_head = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
9552  if (page_track_head == NULL)
9553  {
9554  assert (false);
9555  return ER_FAILED;
9556  }
9557 
9558  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
9559 
9560  /* undo unregister => register the logged item */
9561  error_code = file_tracker_register_internal (thread_p, page_track_head, (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) rcv->data);
9562  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9563  {
9564  /* not expected */
9565  assert (false);
9566 
9567  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
9568  }
9569  else
9570  {
9571  /* need to finish system op while holding latch on header */
9572  log_sysop_end_logical_compensate (thread_p, &rcv->reference_lsa);
9573  }
9574 
9575  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_track_head);
9576 
9577  return error_code;
9578 }
9579 
9580 /*
9581  * file_tracker_apply_to_file () - search for file tracker item and apply function
9582  *
9583  * return : error code
9584  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9585  * vfid (in) : file identifier
9586  * mode (in) : latch mode for tracker pages
9587  * func (in) : apply function for found item
9588  * args (in) : arguments for applied function
9589  */
9590 static int
9591 file_tracker_apply_to_file (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const VFID * vfid, PGBUF_LATCH_MODE mode,
9592  FILE_TRACK_ITEM_FUNC func, void *args)
9593 {
9594  PAGE_PTR page_track_head = NULL;
9595  PAGE_PTR page_track_other = NULL;
9596  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata;
9597  FILE_TRACK_ITEM item_search;
9598  bool for_write = (mode == PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
9599  bool found = false;
9600  int pos = -1;
9601  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9602 
9603  assert (func != NULL);
9604  assert (mode == PGBUF_LATCH_READ || mode == PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE);
9605 
9606  page_track_head = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vpid, OLD_PAGE, mode, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
9607  if (page_track_head == NULL)
9608  {
9609  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
9610  return error_code;
9611  }
9612  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_track_head;
9613 
9614  item_search.volid = vfid->volid;
9615  item_search.fileid = vfid->fileid;
9616  error_code = file_extdata_search_item (thread_p, &extdata, &item_search, file_compare_track_items, true, for_write,
9617  &found, &pos, &page_track_other);
9618  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9619  {
9620  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9621  goto exit;
9622  }
9623  if (!found)
9624  {
9625  assert_release (false);
9626  error_code = ER_FAILED;
9627  goto exit;
9628  }
9629 
9630  error_code = func (thread_p, page_track_other != NULL ? page_track_other : page_track_head, extdata, pos, NULL, args);
9631  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9632  {
9633  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9634  goto exit;
9635  }
9636 
9637  /* success */
9638  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
9639 
9640 exit:
9641  if (page_track_other != NULL)
9642  {
9643  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_other);
9644  }
9645  if (page_track_head != NULL)
9646  {
9647  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_head);
9648  }
9649  return error_code;
9650 }
9651 
9652 /*
9653  * file_tracker_map () - map item function to all tracked files
9654  *
9655  * return : error code
9656  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9657  * latch_mode (in) : latch mode
9658  * func (in) : function called for each item
9659  * args (in) : arguments for function
9660  */
9661 static int
9662 file_tracker_map (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PGBUF_LATCH_MODE latch_mode, FILE_TRACK_ITEM_FUNC func, void *args)
9663 {
9664  PAGE_PTR page_track_head = NULL;
9665  PAGE_PTR page_track_other = NULL;
9666  PAGE_PTR page_extdata = NULL;
9667  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata;
9668  VPID vpid_next = VPID_INITIALIZER;
9669  bool stop = false;
9670  int index_item;
9671  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9672 
9673  page_track_head = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vpid, OLD_PAGE, latch_mode, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
9674  if (page_track_head == NULL)
9675  {
9676  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
9677  return error_code;
9678  }
9679 
9680  page_extdata = page_track_head;
9681  while (true)
9682  {
9683  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_extdata;
9684  for (index_item = 0; index_item < file_extdata_item_count (extdata); index_item++)
9685  {
9686  error_code = func (thread_p, page_extdata, extdata, index_item, &stop, args);
9687  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9688  {
9689  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9690  goto exit;
9691  }
9692  if (stop)
9693  {
9694  /* early out */
9695  goto exit;
9696  }
9697  }
9698 
9699  vpid_next = extdata->vpid_next;
9700  if (page_track_other != NULL)
9701  {
9702  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_track_other);
9703  }
9704  if (VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_next))
9705  {
9706  break;
9707  }
9708 
9709  page_track_other = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, latch_mode, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
9710  if (page_track_other == NULL)
9711  {
9712  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
9713  goto exit;
9714  }
9715 
9716  page_extdata = page_track_other;
9717  }
9718 
9719  /* success */
9720  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
9721 
9722 exit:
9723  if (page_track_other != NULL)
9724  {
9725  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_other);
9726  }
9727  if (page_track_head != NULL)
9728  {
9729  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_head);
9730  }
9731  return error_code;
9732 }
9733 
9734 /*
9735  * file_rv_tracker_reuse_heap () - recover reuse heap file in tracker
9736  *
9737  * return : NO_ERROR
9738  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9739  * rcv (in) : recovery data
9740  */
9741 int
9742 file_rv_tracker_reuse_heap (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
9743 {
9744  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata = NULL;
9745  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *item = NULL;
9746 
9747  assert (rcv->length == 0);
9748  assert (rcv->pgptr != NULL);
9749  assert (rcv->offset >= 0);
9750 
9751  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) rcv->pgptr;
9752  assert (rcv->offset < file_extdata_item_count (extdata));
9753 
9754  item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) file_extdata_at (extdata, rcv->offset);
9755  assert (item->type == FILE_HEAP);
9756  assert (item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted);
9757 
9758  item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted = false;
9759 
9760  file_log ("file_rv_tracker_reuse_heap", "recovery reuse heap " FILE_TRACK_ITEM_MSG ", in "
9761  PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_MSG ("tracker page"), FILE_TRACK_ITEM_AS_ARGS (item), PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (rcv->pgptr));
9762 
9763  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, rcv->pgptr, DONT_FREE);
9764  return NO_ERROR;
9765 }
9766 
9767 /*
9768  * file_tracker_item_reuse_heap () - reuse heap file if marked as deleted. at the same time, update file descriptor in
9769  * file header (descriptor update must happen with tracker protection to provide
9770  * consistent checks).s
9771  *
9772  * return : error code
9773  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9774  * page_of_item (in) : page of item
9775  * extdata (in) : extensible data
9776  * index_item (in) : index of item
9777  * args (in/out) : FILE_TRACKER_REUSE_HEAP_CONTEXT *
9778  */
9779 static int
9780 file_tracker_item_reuse_heap (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_of_item, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata,
9781  int index_item, bool * stop, void *args)
9782 {
9783  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) file_extdata_at (extdata, index_item);
9784  FILE_TRACKER_REUSE_HEAP_CONTEXT *context = (FILE_TRACKER_REUSE_HEAP_CONTEXT *) args;
9785  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
9786  VPID vpid_fhead;
9787  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
9788  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
9789  FILE_DESCRIPTORS des_new;
9790  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9791 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
9792  bool is_dropped = false;
9793 #endif
9794 
9795  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
9796 
9797  if (item->type != (INT16) FILE_HEAP)
9798  {
9799  return NO_ERROR;
9800  }
9801  if (!item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted)
9802  {
9803  return NO_ERROR;
9804  }
9805 
9806  /* get vfid */
9807  context->hfid_out->vfid.volid = item->volid;
9808  context->hfid_out->vfid.fileid = item->fileid;
9809 
9810 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
9811  /* we need it to check vacuum won't consider this dropped. */
9812  error_code = vacuum_is_file_dropped (thread_p, &is_dropped, &context->hfid_out->vfid,
9813  logtb_get_current_mvccid (thread_p));
9814  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9815  {
9816  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9817  VFID_SET_NULL (&context->hfid_out->vfid);
9818  return error_code;
9819  }
9820  if (is_dropped)
9821  {
9822  file_log ("file_tracker_item_reuse_heap", "can't reuse heap file %d|%d with mvccid %llu because vacuum thinks it "
9823  "is dropped.\n", VFID_AS_ARGS (&context->hfid_out->vfid),
9824  (unsigned long long) logtb_get_current_mvccid (thread_p));
9825  VFID_SET_NULL (&context->hfid_out->vfid);
9826  return NO_ERROR;
9827  }
9828 #endif
9829 
9830  /* reuse this heap. but we need to update its descriptor first. */
9831  FILE_GET_HEADER_VPID (&context->hfid_out->vfid, &vpid_fhead);
9832  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
9833  if (page_fhead == NULL)
9834  {
9835  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
9836  goto exit;
9837  }
9838  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
9839  assert (fhead->type == FILE_HEAP || fhead->type == FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS);
9840  assert (VFID_EQ (&context->hfid_out->vfid, &fhead->self));
9841  assert (VFID_EQ (&context->hfid_out->vfid, &fhead->descriptor.heap.hfid.vfid));
9842  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
9843 
9844  /* get hfid */
9845  *context->hfid_out = fhead->descriptor.heap.hfid;
9846 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
9847  {
9848  /* safeguard: check hfid & sticky first page match */
9849  VPID vpid_heap_header = VPID_INITIALIZER;
9850  error_code = file_get_sticky_first_page (thread_p, &context->hfid_out->vfid, &vpid_heap_header);
9851  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9852  {
9853  ASSERT_ERROR ();
9854  goto exit;
9855  }
9856  assert (context->hfid_out->vfid.volid == vpid_heap_header.volid);
9857  assert (context->hfid_out->hpgid == vpid_heap_header.pageid);
9858  }
9859 #endif /* !NDEBUG */
9860 
9861  /* log & update class_oid */
9862  des_new = fhead->descriptor;
9863  des_new.heap.class_oid = context->class_oid;
9864  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVFL_FILEDESC_UPD, NULL, page_fhead,
9865  (PGLENGTH) ((char *) &fhead->descriptor - page_fhead), sizeof (fhead->descriptor),
9866  sizeof (des_new), &fhead->descriptor, &des_new);
9867  fhead->descriptor = des_new;
9868  pgbuf_set_dirty_and_free (thread_p, page_fhead);
9869 
9870  /* now update mark deleted flag in tracker item */
9871  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_of_item);
9872 
9873  item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted = false;
9874  log_append_undoredo_data2 (thread_p, RVFL_TRACKER_HEAP_REUSE, NULL, page_of_item, index_item,
9875  sizeof (context->hfid_out->vfid), 0, &context->hfid_out->vfid, NULL);
9876  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_of_item, DONT_FREE);
9877 
9878  file_log ("file_tracker_item_reuse_heap", "reuse heap file %d|%d; tracker page %d|%d, prev_lsa = %lld|%d, "
9879  "crt_lsa = %lld|%d, item at pos %d ", VFID_AS_ARGS (&context->hfid_out->vfid),
9880  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_of_item, &save_lsa), index_item);
9881 
9882  /* stop looking */
9883  *stop = true;
9884  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
9885 
9886 exit:
9887  if (page_fhead != NULL)
9888  {
9889  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
9890  }
9891  return error_code;
9892 }
9893 
9894 /*
9895  * file_tracker_reuse_heap () - search for heap file marked as deleted and reuse.
9896  *
9897  * return : error code
9898  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9899  * class_oid (in) : class identifier for new heap file
9900  * hfid_out (out) : HFID of reused file or NULL HFID if no file was found
9901  *
9902  * note: file descriptor will also be updated if heap file is reused
9903  */
9904 int
9905 file_tracker_reuse_heap (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, const OID * class_oid, HFID * hfid_out)
9906 {
9907  FILE_TRACKER_REUSE_HEAP_CONTEXT context;
9908 
9909  assert (hfid_out != NULL);
9910  assert (class_oid != NULL);
9911 
9912  HFID_SET_NULL (hfid_out);
9913  context.hfid_out = hfid_out;
9914  context.class_oid = *class_oid;
9915 
9916  return file_tracker_map (thread_p, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, file_tracker_item_reuse_heap, &context);
9917 }
9918 
9919 /*
9920  * file_tracker_item_mark_heap_deleted () - FILE_TRACK_ITEM_FUNC to mark heap entry as deleted
9921  *
9922  * return : error code
9923  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9924  * page_of_item (in) : page of item
9925  * extdata (in) : extensible data
9926  * index_item (in) : index of item
9927  * stop (in) : not used
9928  * args (in) : FILE_TRACK_MARK_HEAP_DELETED_CONTEXT *
9929  */
9930 static int
9931 file_tracker_item_mark_heap_deleted (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_of_item, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata,
9932  int index_item, bool * stop, void *args)
9933 {
9934  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) file_extdata_at (extdata, index_item);
9935  FILE_TRACK_MARK_HEAP_DELETED_CONTEXT *context = (FILE_TRACK_MARK_HEAP_DELETED_CONTEXT *) args;
9936  LOG_LSA save_lsa;
9937 
9938  assert ((FILE_TYPE) item->type == FILE_HEAP);
9939  assert (!item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted);
9940 
9941  item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted = true;
9942 
9943  save_lsa = *pgbuf_get_lsa (page_of_item);
9944  if (context->is_undo)
9945  {
9946  log_append_compensate_with_undo_nxlsa (thread_p, RVFL_TRACKER_HEAP_MARK_DELETED,
9947  pgbuf_get_vpid_ptr (page_of_item), index_item, page_of_item, 0, NULL,
9948  LOG_FIND_CURRENT_TDES (thread_p), &context->ref_lsa);
9949  }
9950  else
9951  {
9952  LOG_DATA_ADDR addr = LOG_DATA_ADDR_INITIALIZER;
9953  addr.pgptr = page_of_item;
9954  addr.offset = index_item;
9955  log_append_run_postpone (thread_p, RVFL_TRACKER_HEAP_MARK_DELETED, &addr, pgbuf_get_vpid_ptr (page_of_item),
9956  0, NULL, &context->ref_lsa);
9957  }
9958  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, page_of_item, DONT_FREE);
9959 
9960  file_log ("file_tracker_item_mark_heap_deleted", "mark delete heap file %d|%d; "
9961  PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_MSG ("tracker page") ", item at pos %d, on %s, ref_lsa = %lld|%d",
9962  item->volid, item->fileid, PGBUF_PAGE_MODIFY_ARGS (page_of_item, &save_lsa), index_item,
9963  context->is_undo ? "undo" : "postpone", LSA_AS_ARGS (&context->ref_lsa));
9964 
9965  return NO_ERROR;
9966 }
9967 
9968 /*
9969  * file_rv_tracker_mark_heap_deleted () - search for heap file and mark it for delete
9970  *
9971  * return : error code
9972  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
9973  * rcv (in) : recovery data
9974  * is_undo (in) : true if called on undo/rollback, false if called on postpone
9975  */
9976 int
9977 file_rv_tracker_mark_heap_deleted (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv, bool is_undo)
9978 {
9979  VFID *vfid = (VFID *) rcv->data;
9980  FILE_TRACK_MARK_HEAP_DELETED_CONTEXT context;
9981  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
9982 
9983  assert (rcv->length == sizeof (*vfid));
9984  assert (!LSA_ISNULL (&rcv->reference_lsa));
9985 
9986  context.is_undo = is_undo;
9987  context.ref_lsa = rcv->reference_lsa;
9988 
9989  error_code = file_tracker_apply_to_file (thread_p, vfid, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, file_tracker_item_mark_heap_deleted,
9990  &context);
9991  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
9992  {
9993  assert_release (false);
9994  }
9995 
9996  return error_code;
9997 }
9998 
9999 /*
10000  * file_rv_tracker_mark_heap_deleted_compensate_or_run_postpone () - used for recovery as compensate or run postpone
10001  * when heap file is marked as deleted.
10002  *
10003  * return : NO_ERROR
10004  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
10005  * rcv (in) : recovery data
10006  */
10007 int
10008 file_rv_tracker_mark_heap_deleted_compensate_or_run_postpone (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, LOG_RCV * rcv)
10009 {
10010  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata = NULL;
10011  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *item = NULL;
10012 
10013  assert (rcv->length == 0);
10014  assert (rcv->pgptr != NULL);
10015  assert (rcv->offset >= 0);
10016 
10017  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) rcv->pgptr;
10018  assert (rcv->offset < file_extdata_item_count (extdata));
10019 
10020  item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) file_extdata_at (extdata, rcv->offset);
10021  assert (item->type == FILE_HEAP);
10022  assert (!item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted);
10023 
10024  item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted = true;
10025 
10026  file_log ("file_rv_tracker_mark_heap_deleted_compensate_or_run_postpone", "mark heap deleted" FILE_TRACK_ITEM_MSG
10027  ", in " PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_MSG ("tracker page"), FILE_TRACK_ITEM_AS_ARGS (item),
10028  PGBUF_PAGE_STATE_ARGS (rcv->pgptr));
10029 
10030  pgbuf_set_dirty (thread_p, rcv->pgptr, DONT_FREE);
10031  return NO_ERROR;
10032 }
10033 
10034 #if defined (SA_MODE)
10035 /*
10036  * file_tracker_reclaim_marked_deleted () - reclaim all files marked as deleted. this can work only in stand-alone
10037  * mode.
10038  *
10039  * return : error code
10040  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
10041  */
10042 int
10043 file_tracker_reclaim_marked_deleted (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
10044 {
10045  PAGE_PTR page_track_head = NULL;
10046 
10047  PAGE_PTR page_extdata = NULL;
10048  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata = NULL;
10049  PAGE_PTR page_extdata_next = NULL;
10050  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata_next = NULL;
10051  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *item = NULL;
10052  VPID vpid_next;
10053  VFID vfid;
10054  int idx_item;
10055  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
10056 
10057  assert (!VPID_ISNULL (&file_Tracker_vpid));
10058  assert (!VFID_ISNULL (&file_Tracker_vfid));
10059 
10060  /* how this works:
10061  * do two steps:
10062  * 1. go through all tracker items and identify heap file entires marked as deleted. deallocate the files and remove
10063  * the items from tracker.
10064  * 2. loop through tracker pages and try to merge two-by-two.
10065  */
10066 
10067  page_track_head = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
10068  if (page_track_head == NULL)
10069  {
10070  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10071  return error_code;
10072  }
10073 
10074  log_sysop_start (thread_p);
10075 
10076  /* first step: process tracker data, search for files marked deleted, destroy them and remove them from tracker */
10077  page_extdata = page_track_head;
10078 
10079  while (true)
10080  {
10081  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_extdata;
10082  for (idx_item = 0; idx_item < file_extdata_item_count (extdata);)
10083  {
10084  item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) file_extdata_at (extdata, idx_item);
10085  if ((FILE_TYPE) item->type == FILE_HEAP && item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted)
10086  {
10087  /* destroy file */
10088  vfid.volid = item->volid;
10089  vfid.fileid = item->fileid;
10090  error_code = file_destroy (thread_p, &vfid, false);
10091  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10092  {
10093  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10094  goto exit;
10095  }
10096  /* already removed by file_destroy. we don't have to increment idx_item */
10097  }
10098  else
10099  {
10100  /* go to next */
10101  idx_item++;
10102  }
10103  }
10104 
10105  /* go to next extensible data page */
10106  vpid_next = extdata->vpid_next;
10107  if (page_extdata != NULL && page_extdata != page_track_head)
10108  {
10109  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_extdata);
10110  }
10111  page_extdata = NULL;
10112  if (VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_next))
10113  {
10114  /* no next page */
10115  break;
10116  }
10117  page_extdata = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
10118  if (page_extdata == NULL)
10119  {
10120  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
10121  goto exit;
10122  }
10123  /* loop again */
10124  }
10125 
10126  /* try merges */
10127  assert (page_extdata == NULL);
10128  page_extdata = page_track_head;
10129  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_extdata;
10130  while (!VPID_ISNULL (&extdata->vpid_next))
10131  {
10132  page_extdata_next = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &extdata->vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_WRITE,
10133  PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
10134  if (page_extdata_next == NULL)
10135  {
10136  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
10137  goto exit;
10138  }
10139  extdata_next = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_extdata_next;
10140  if (file_extdata_merge_pages (thread_p, extdata_next, page_extdata_next, extdata, page_extdata,
10141  file_compare_track_items, true))
10142  {
10143  /* merged next into current. deallocate next. */
10144  pgbuf_get_vpid (page_extdata_next, &vpid_next);
10145  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_extdata_next);
10146 
10147  error_code = file_dealloc (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vfid, &vpid_next, FILE_TRACKER);
10148  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10149  {
10150  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10151  goto exit;
10152  }
10153 
10154  /* we can try to merge into this page again. fall through without advancing */
10155  }
10156  else
10157  {
10158  /* advance to next page */
10159  if (page_extdata != page_track_head)
10160  {
10161  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_extdata);
10162  }
10163  page_extdata = page_extdata_next;
10164  extdata = extdata_next;
10165  page_extdata_next = NULL;
10166  }
10167  }
10168 
10169  /* finished successfully */
10170  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
10171 
10172 exit:
10173 
10174  assert (log_check_system_op_is_started (thread_p));
10175  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10176  {
10177  log_sysop_abort (thread_p);
10178  }
10179  else
10180  {
10181  log_sysop_commit (thread_p);
10182  }
10183  assert (page_extdata_next == NULL || page_extdata_next != page_track_head);
10184  if (page_extdata_next != NULL)
10185  {
10186  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_extdata_next);
10187  }
10188  if (page_extdata != NULL && page_extdata != page_track_head)
10189  {
10190  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_extdata);
10191  }
10192  if (page_track_head != NULL)
10193  {
10194  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_head);
10195  }
10196  return error_code;
10197 }
10198 #endif /* SA_MODE */
10199 
10200 /*
10201  * file_tracker_get_and_protect () - get a file from tracker. if we want to get b-tree or heap files, we must first
10202  * protect them by locking class.
10203  *
10204  * return : error code
10205  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
10206  * desired_type (in) : desired file type. FILE_UNKNOWN_TYPE for any type.
10207  * item (in) : tracker item
10208  * class_oid (out) : output locked class OID (for b-tree and heap). NULL OID if no class is locked.
10209  * stop (out) : output true when item is accepted
10210  */
10211 STATIC_INLINE int
10212 file_tracker_get_and_protect (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_TYPE desired_type, FILE_TRACK_ITEM * item, OID * class_oid,
10213  bool * stop)
10214 {
10215  VPID vpid_fhead;
10216  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
10217  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
10218  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
10219 
10220  assert (class_oid != NULL && OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
10221 
10222  /* how it works:
10223  * this is part of the tracker iterate without holding latch on tracker during the entire iteration. however, it can
10224  * only work if the files processed outside latch are protected from being destroyed. otherwise, resuming is
10225  * impossible. most file types are not mutable, so they don't need protection. however, for b-tree and heap files we
10226  * need to read class OID from descriptor and try to lock it (conditionally!). this is a best-effort approach, if the
10227  * locking fails, we just skip the file. */
10228 
10229  /* check file type is right */
10230  switch (desired_type)
10231  {
10232  case FILE_UNKNOWN_TYPE:
10233  /* accept any type */
10234  break;
10235  case FILE_HEAP:
10236  case FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS:
10237  /* accept heap or heap reuse slots */
10238  if ((FILE_TYPE) item->type != FILE_HEAP && (FILE_TYPE) item->type != FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS)
10239  {
10240  /* reject */
10241  return NO_ERROR;
10242  }
10243  break;
10244  default:
10245  /* accept the exact file type */
10246  if ((FILE_TYPE) item->type != desired_type)
10247  {
10248  /* reject */
10249  return NO_ERROR;
10250  }
10251  break;
10252  }
10253 
10254  /* now we need to make sure the file is protected. most types are not mutable (cannot be created or destroyed during
10255  * run-time), but b-tree and heap files must be protected by lock. */
10256  switch ((FILE_TYPE) item->type)
10257  {
10258  case FILE_HEAP:
10259  /* these files may be marked for delete. check this is not a deleted file */
10260  if (item->metadata.heap.is_marked_deleted)
10261  {
10262  /* reject */
10263  return NO_ERROR;
10264  }
10265  /* we need to protect with lock. fall through */
10266  break;
10267  case FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS:
10268  case FILE_BTREE:
10269  case FILE_MULTIPAGE_OBJECT_HEAP:
10270  case FILE_BTREE_OVERFLOW_KEY:
10271  /* we need to protect with lock. fall through */
10272  break;
10273  default:
10274  /* immutable file types. no protection required */
10275  *stop = true;
10276  return NO_ERROR;
10277  }
10278 
10279  /* we need to fix file header and read the class oid from descriptor */
10280  vpid_fhead.volid = item->volid;
10281  vpid_fhead.pageid = item->fileid;
10282  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
10283  if (page_fhead == NULL)
10284  {
10285  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
10286  return error_code;
10287  }
10288  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
10289  file_header_sanity_check (thread_p, fhead);
10290 
10291  /* read class OID */
10292  switch ((FILE_TYPE) item->type)
10293  {
10294  case FILE_BTREE:
10295  *class_oid = fhead->descriptor.btree.class_oid;
10296  break;
10297  case FILE_HEAP:
10298  case FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS:
10299  *class_oid = fhead->descriptor.heap.class_oid;
10300  break;
10301  case FILE_MULTIPAGE_OBJECT_HEAP:
10302  *class_oid = fhead->descriptor.heap_overflow.class_oid;
10303  break;
10304  case FILE_BTREE_OVERFLOW_KEY:
10305  *class_oid = fhead->descriptor.btree_key_overflow.class_oid;
10306  break;
10307  default:
10308  assert (false);
10309  break;
10310  }
10311  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_fhead);
10312 
10313  if (OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
10314  {
10315  /* this must be boot_Db_parm file; cannot be deleted so we don't need lock. */
10316  *stop = true;
10317  return NO_ERROR;
10318  }
10319 
10320  /* try conditional lock */
10321  if (lock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, FILE_GET_TRACKER_LOCK_MODE (desired_type),
10322  LK_COND_LOCK) != LK_GRANTED)
10323  {
10324  er_set (ER_NOTIFICATION_SEVERITY, ARG_FILE_LINE, ER_CANNOT_CHECK_FILE, 5, item->volid, item->fileid,
10325  OID_AS_ARGS (class_oid));
10326  OID_SET_NULL (class_oid);
10327  }
10328  else
10329  {
10330  /* stop at this file */
10331  *stop = true;
10332  }
10333 
10334  /* finished */
10335  return NO_ERROR;
10336 }
10337 
10338 /*
10339  * file_tracker_interruptable_iterate () - iterate in file tracker and get a new file of desired type
10340  *
10341  * return : error code
10342  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
10343  * desired_ftype (in) : desired type
10344  * vfid (in) : file identifier and iterator cursor. iterate must start with a NULL identifier
10345  * class_oid (in) : locked class OID (used to protect b-tree and heap files)
10346  */
10347 int
10348 file_tracker_interruptable_iterate (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE_TYPE desired_ftype, VFID * vfid, OID * class_oid)
10349 {
10350  PAGE_PTR page_track_head = NULL;
10351  PAGE_PTR page_track_other = NULL;
10352  PAGE_PTR page_extdata = NULL;
10353  FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *extdata = NULL;
10354  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *item;
10355  bool found = false;
10356  bool stop = false;
10357  int idx_item;
10358  VPID vpid_next;
10359 #if !defined (NDEBUG)
10360  VFID vfid_prev_cursor = *vfid;
10361 #endif /* !NDEBUG */
10362  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
10363 
10364  assert (vfid != NULL);
10365  assert (class_oid != NULL);
10366 
10367  /* how it works:
10368  * start from given VFID and get a new file of desired type. for b-tree and heap files, we also need to lock their
10369  * class OID in order to protect them from being removed. otherwise we could not resume in next iteration. */
10370 
10371  page_track_head = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vpid, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
10372  if (page_track_head == NULL)
10373  {
10374  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
10375  return error_code;
10376  }
10377 
10378  if (!OID_ISNULL (class_oid))
10379  {
10380  /* now that we fixed tracker header page, we no longer need lock protection. */
10381  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, FILE_GET_TRACKER_LOCK_MODE (desired_ftype), true);
10382  OID_SET_NULL (class_oid);
10383  }
10384 
10385  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_track_head;
10386  if (VFID_ISNULL (vfid))
10387  {
10388  /* starting position is first */
10389  idx_item = 0;
10390  page_extdata = page_track_head;
10391  }
10392  else
10393  {
10394  FILE_TRACK_ITEM item_search;
10395  item_search.volid = vfid->volid;
10396  item_search.fileid = vfid->fileid;
10397  error_code =
10398  file_extdata_search_item (thread_p, &extdata, &item_search, file_compare_track_items, true, false, &found,
10399  &idx_item, &page_track_other);
10400  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10401  {
10402  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10403  goto exit;
10404  }
10405  if (!found)
10406  {
10407  /* we are in trouble */
10408  assert_release (false);
10409  error_code = ER_FAILED;
10410  goto exit;
10411  }
10412  page_extdata = page_track_other != NULL ? page_track_other : page_track_head;
10413  /* move to next */
10414  idx_item++;
10415  }
10416 
10417  assert (extdata == (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_extdata);
10418  /* start iterating until stop is issued */
10419  while (true)
10420  {
10421  for (; idx_item < file_extdata_item_count (extdata); idx_item++)
10422  {
10423  item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) file_extdata_at (extdata, idx_item);
10424  error_code = file_tracker_get_and_protect (thread_p, desired_ftype, item, class_oid, &stop);
10425  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10426  {
10427  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10428  goto exit;
10429  }
10430  if (stop)
10431  {
10432  vfid->volid = item->volid;
10433  vfid->fileid = item->fileid;
10434  goto exit;
10435  }
10436  }
10437  vpid_next = extdata->vpid_next;
10438  if (page_track_other != NULL)
10439  {
10440  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_track_other);
10441  }
10442  if (VPID_ISNULL (&vpid_next))
10443  {
10444  /* ended */
10445  break;
10446  }
10447  page_track_other = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_next, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
10448  if (page_track_other == NULL)
10449  {
10450  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
10451  goto exit;
10452  }
10453  page_extdata = page_track_other;
10454  extdata = (FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA *) page_extdata;
10455  idx_item = 0;
10456  }
10457 
10458  /* end of tracker */
10459  VFID_SET_NULL (vfid);
10460  assert (OID_ISNULL (class_oid));
10461  assert (error_code == NO_ERROR);
10462 
10463 exit:
10464  if (page_track_other != NULL)
10465  {
10466  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_other);
10467  }
10468  if (page_track_head != NULL)
10469  {
10470  pgbuf_unfix (thread_p, page_track_head);
10471  }
10472 
10473  /* check cursor is not repeated (unless there is an error) */
10474  assert (error_code != NO_ERROR || VFID_ISNULL (&vfid_prev_cursor) || !VFID_EQ (&vfid_prev_cursor, vfid));
10475 
10476  return error_code;
10477 }

10538 static int
10539 file_tracker_item_dump_capacity (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_of_item, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata,

10551  vpid_fhead.volid = item->volid;

10574 /*
10575  * file_tracker_dump_all_capacities () - dump capacities for all files
10576  *
10577  * return : error code
10578  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
10579  * fp (in) : output file
10580  */
10581 int
10582 file_tracker_dump_all_capacities (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, FILE * fp)
10583 {
10584  int error_code = NO_ERROR;

10779 /*
10780  * file_tracker_check () - check all files have valid tables. stand-alone mode will also cross check with disk sector
10781  * table maps.
10782  *
10783  * return : error code
10784  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
10785  */
10786 DISK_ISVALID
10787 file_tracker_check (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p)
10788 {
10789  DISK_ISVALID allvalid = DISK_VALID;
10790  DISK_ISVALID valid = DISK_VALID;
10791  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
10792 
10793 #if defined (SERVER_MODE)
10794  VFID vfid = VFID_INITIALIZER;
10795  OID class_oid = OID_INITIALIZER;
10796 
10797  valid = file_table_check (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vfid, NULL);
10798  if (valid == DISK_ERROR)
10799  {
10800  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10801  return DISK_ERROR;
10802  }
10803  else if (valid == DISK_INVALID)
10804  {
10805  assert_release (false);
10806  allvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10807  }
10808 
10809  while (true)
10810  {
10811  error_code = file_tracker_interruptable_iterate (thread_p, FILE_UNKNOWN_TYPE, &vfid, &class_oid);
10812  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10813  {
10814  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10815  allvalid = (allvalid == DISK_VALID) ? DISK_ERROR : allvalid;
10816  break;
10817  }
10818  if (VFID_ISNULL (&vfid))
10819  {
10820  /* all files processed */
10821  break;
10822  }
10823  valid = file_table_check (thread_p, &vfid, NULL);
10824  if (valid == DISK_INVALID)
10825  {
10826  assert (false);
10827  allvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10828  }
10829  else if (valid == DISK_ERROR)
10830  {
10831  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10832  allvalid = (allvalid == DISK_VALID) ? DISK_ERROR : allvalid;
10833  break;
10834  }
10835  }
10836 
10837  if (!OID_ISNULL (&class_oid))
10838  {
10839  lock_unlock_object (thread_p, &class_oid, oid_Root_class_oid, SCH_S_LOCK, true);
10840  }
10841 #else /* !SERVER_MODE */ /* SA_MODE */
10842  DISK_VOLMAP_CLONE *disk_map_clone = NULL;
10843 
10844  error_code = disk_map_clone_create (thread_p, &disk_map_clone);
10845  if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10846  {
10847  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10848  return DISK_ERROR;
10849  }
10850 
10851  valid = file_table_check (thread_p, &file_Tracker_vfid, disk_map_clone);
10852  if (valid == DISK_INVALID)
10853  {
10854  assert_release (false);
10855  allvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10856  /* continue checks */
10857  }
10858  else if (valid == DISK_ERROR)
10859  {
10860  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10861  return DISK_ERROR;
10862  }
10863 
10864  error_code = file_tracker_map (thread_p, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, file_tracker_item_check, disk_map_clone);
10865  if (error_code == ER_FAILED)
10866  {
10867  assert_release (false);
10868  disk_map_clone_free (&disk_map_clone);
10869  allvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10870  }
10871  else if (error_code != NO_ERROR)
10872  {
10873  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10874  disk_map_clone_free (&disk_map_clone);
10875  return allvalid == DISK_VALID ? DISK_ERROR : allvalid;
10876  }
10877  else
10878  {
10879  /* check all sectors have been cleared */
10880  valid = disk_map_clone_check_leaks (disk_map_clone);
10881  if (valid == DISK_INVALID)
10882  {
10883  assert_release (false);
10884  allvalid = DISK_INVALID;
10885  }
10886  else if (valid == DISK_ERROR)
10887  {
10888  ASSERT_ERROR ();
10889  allvalid = allvalid == DISK_VALID ? DISK_ERROR : allvalid;
10890  }
10891  disk_map_clone_free (&disk_map_clone);
10892  }
10893 
10894 #endif /* SA_MODE */
10895 
10896  return allvalid;
10897 }
10898 
10899 #if defined (SA_MODE)
10900 /*
10901  * file_tracker_item_check () - check file table and cross-check sector usage with disk sector table maps
10902  *
10903  * return : error code (ER_FAILED for invalid state)
10904  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
10905  * page_of_item (in) : tracker page
10906  * extdata (in) : tracker extensible data
10907  * index_item (in) : item index
10908  * stop (in) : not used
10909  * args (in/out) : DISK_VOLMAP_CLONE *
10910  */
10911 static int
10912 file_tracker_item_check (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_of_item, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata, int index_item,
10913  bool * stop, void *args)
10914 {
10915  DISK_VOLMAP_CLONE *disk_map_clone = (DISK_VOLMAP_CLONE *) args;
10916  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *item;
10917  VFID vfid;
10918  DISK_ISVALID valid = DISK_VALID;
10919  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
10920 
10921  item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) file_extdata_at (extdata, index_item);
10922  vfid.volid = item->volid;
10923  vfid.fileid = item->fileid;
10924 
10925  valid = file_table_check (thread_p, &vfid, disk_map_clone);
10926  if (valid == DISK_INVALID)
10927  {
10928  assert_release (false);
10929  return ER_FAILED;
10930  }
10931  else if (valid == DISK_ERROR)
10932  {
10933  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
10934  return error_code;
10935  }
10936 
10937  return NO_ERROR;
10938 }
10939 #endif /* SA_MODE */

10941 /*
10942  * file_tracker_item_spacedb () - FILE_TRACKER_ITEM_FUNC to collect space information
10943  *
10944  * return : error code
10945  * thread_p (in) : thread entry
10946  * page_of_item (in) : page of item
10947  * extdata (in) : extensible data
10948  * index_item (in) : index of item
10949  * stop (in) : ignored
10950  * args (in/out) : SPACEDB_FILES *
10951  */
10952 static int
10953 file_tracker_item_spacedb (THREAD_ENTRY * thread_p, PAGE_PTR page_of_item, FILE_EXTENSIBLE_DATA * extdata,
10954  int index_item, bool * stop, void *args)
10955 {
10956  FILE_TRACK_ITEM *item;
10957  VPID vpid_fhead;
10958  PAGE_PTR page_fhead = NULL;
10959  FILE_HEADER *fhead = NULL;
10960  SPACEDB_FILES *spacedb = (SPACEDB_FILES *) args;
10961  SPACEDB_FILE_TYPE spacedb_ftype;
10962  int error_code = NO_ERROR;
10963 
10964  item = (FILE_TRACK_ITEM *) file_extdata_at (extdata, index_item);
10965  vpid_fhead.volid = item->volid;
10966  vpid_fhead.pageid = item->fileid;
10967 
10968  page_fhead = pgbuf_fix (thread_p, &vpid_fhead, OLD_PAGE, PGBUF_LATCH_READ, PGBUF_UNCONDITIONAL_LATCH);
10969  if (page_fhead == NULL)
10970  {
10971  ASSERT_ERROR_AND_SET (error_code);
10972  return error_code;
10973  }
10974  fhead = (FILE_HEADER *) page_fhead;
10975 
10976  switch (fhead->type)
10977  {
10978  case FILE_BTREE:
10979  /* index file */
10980  spacedb_ftype = SPACEDB_INDEX_FILE;
10981  break;
10982  case FILE_HEAP:
10983  case FILE_HEAP_REUSE_SLOTS:
10984  /* heap file */
10985  spacedb_ftype = SPACEDB_HEAP_FILE;
10986  break;
10987  default:
10988  /* system file */
10989  spacedb_ftype = SPACEDB_SYSTEM_FILE;
10990  break;
10991  }
10992  spacedb[spacedb_ftype].nfile++;
10993  spacedb[spacedb_ftype].npage_ftab += fhead->n_page_ftab;
10994  spacedb[spacedb_ftype].npage_user += fhead->n_page_user;
10995  spacedb[spacedb_ftype].npage_reserved += fhead->n_page_free;
10996 
10997  pgbuf_unfix_and_init (thread_p, page_fhead);
10998  return NO_ERROR;
10999 }
